between the European Union and the Federal Republic of Yugoslavia on the activities of the European Union Monitoring Mission (EUMM) in the Federal Republic of Yugoslavia
- the European Community Monitoring Mission (ECMM) has been active in the Western Balkans since 1991,
- the European Union and its Member States have offered to establish a European Union Monitoring Mission (EUMM) in the Federal Republic of Yugoslavia and that the Government of the Federal Republic of Yugoslavia has accepted this offer,
- the Council of the European Union, on 22 December 2000, adopted Joint Action 2000 / 811 / CFSP on the European Union Monitoring Mission converting the ECMM into the EUMM, as an instrument of the European Union <unk> s Common Foreign and Security Policy (CFSP) which, building on previous initiatives, should contribute to formulating an effective European Union policy for the Western Balkans,
( 1) Die Überwachungsmission der Europäischen Union, nachstehend <unk> EUMM <unk> genannt, die ursprünglich in der Region als Überwachungsmission der Europäischen Gemeinschaft (ECMM) errichtet wurde, hat ihr Hauptquartier derzeit in Sarajevo und wird ein Missionsbüro in Belgrad sowie auf Entscheidung des Missionsleiters nach Hearing und Zustimmung der Aufnahmepartei gegebenenfalls weitere Büro in der Bundesrepublik Jugoslawien einrichten, um dazu beizutragen, eine wirksame Politik der Europäischen Union für den Westlichen Balkan zu formulieren. The European Union Monitoring Mission, hereinafter referred to as the EUMM, which was originally established in the region as a European Community Monitoring Mission (ECMM), shall have its headquarters in Sarajevo and shall establish a mission office in Belgrade and, by decision of the Head of Mission after consultation and agreement of the host party, further offices in the Federal Republic of Jugoslavia,
( a) monitor political developments and developments in the security situation within their competence;
( b) pay particular attention to border control, issues affecting different ethnic groups and the return of refugees;
( c) submit analytical reports in accordance with the tasks assigned to it;
( d) contribute to the early warning of the Council and to confidence building within the framework of the stabilisation policies pursued by the European Union in the region.
( 2) Die Aufnahmepartei erteilt der EUMM alle Informationen und leistet jede Art von Zusammenarbeit, die zur Erreichung der Ziele der EUMM erforderlich sind. The host Party shall provide the EUMM with all information and shall cooperate in any manner necessary to achieve the objectives of the EUMM.
The host party may appoint a liaison officer to the EUMM.
( 1) Die Aufnahmepartei ergreift alle erforderlichen Maßnahmen für den Schutz und die Sicherheit der EUMM und ihrer Mitglieder. The host Party shall take all necessary measures for the protection and security of the EUMM and its members.
All relevant arrangements proposed by the host Party shall be agreed with the Head of Mission before they are implemented.
( 2) Zur Durchführung ihrer Tätigkeit genießen die EUMM und ihr Personal unter Einbeziehung ihrer Transportmittel und Ausrüstungen die Freiheit, die zur Erfuellung des Auftrags der Mission erforderlich ist. In order to carry out their activities, the EUMM and its staff shall enjoy the freedom of movement required for the purpose of carrying out the mission <unk> s mission, including their means of transport and equipment.
( 3) Das Personal der EUMM kann bei seiner Tätigkeit von einem Dolmetscher und, auf Anforderung der EUMM, von einem von der Aufnahmespartei benannten Begleitoffizier begleitoffizier escort werden. The staff of the EUMM may be accompanied in their activities by an interpreter and, at the request of the EUMM, by an escort officer designated by the host party.
( 4) Die EUMM kann auf ihrem Missionsbüro in Belgrad sowie an anderen Orten, über die der Missionsleiter befindet, die Flagge der Europäischen Union hoist. The EUMM may fly the flag of the European Union at its mission office in Belgrade and at any other location where the Head of Mission is located.
( 5) Fahrzeuge und andere Transportmittel der EUMM tragen ein Erkennungszeichen der Mission, über das die zuständigen Behörden unterrichtet werden. EUMM vehicles and other means of transport shall bear a mission identification badge which shall be communicated to the competent authorities.
( 1) Der Missionsleiter der EUMM wird vom Rat der Europäischen Union ernannt. The Head of Mission of the EUMM shall be appointed by the Council of the European Union.
( 2) Sonstiges EUMM -Personal shall be seconded by the Member States of the European Union.
Personnel shall be allocated to specific uses by the Head of Mission under the supervision of the Secretary-General / High Representative.
Norway and Slovakia, which participate in the EUMM at the time of this Agreement, may also designate EUMM staff, who shall then be seconding parties, as shall the European Union and its Member States.
( 3) Das Personal der EUMM trägt die Bezeichnung <unk> Beobachter <unk>. The staff of the EUMM shall bear the designation <unk> Observer <unk>.
( 4) Die Regierungen der Versandendeparteien benennen Beobachter für die EUMM. The governments of the sending parties shall designate observers for the EUMM.
( 5) Der Missionsleiter bestimmt nach Hearing und Zustimmung der Aufnahmespartei die Anzahl der Beobachter im Rahmen dieses Abkommens. The Head of Mission shall, after consultation and approval by the host party, determine the number of observers under this Agreement.
( 6) Die Beobachter unterlassen alle Handlungen oder Tätigkeiten, die mit der Unparteilichkeit ihrer Aufgaben unvereinbar sind. The observers shall refrain from any action or activity incompatible with the impartiality of their duties.
( 7) Die EUMM kann auf die Unterstützung durch Verwaltungs- und technisches Personal der Entsendeparteien fallgreifen. The EUMM may call upon the assistance of the administrative and technical staff of the posting parties.
The members of the administrative or technical staff of the EUMM shall enjoy, in accordance with the Vienna Convention on Diplomatic Relations, the same status as the administrative and technical staff of the posting parties in embassies.
( 8) Die EUMM kann vor Ort das erfordertigte Hilfspersonal eingestellt. The EUMM may appoint on site the auxiliary staff required.
At the request of the Head of Mission, the host Party shall facilitate the recruitment by the EUMM of qualified local staff.
The auxiliary staff of the EUMM shall enjoy the same status as the local staff in embassies, in accordance with the Vienna Convention on Diplomatic Relations.
( 1) Die Beobachter dürfen keine Waffen tragen. The observers shall not carry weapons.
( 2) Die Beobachter tragen Zivilkleidung mit einem EUMM-Erkennungszeichen. The observers shall wear civilian clothing bearing an EUMM identification mark.
( 1) Die EUMM in der Bundesrepublik Jugoslawien führt ihre Tätigkeit unter der Verantwortung des Missionsleiter aus. EUMM in the Federal Republic of Jugoslavia shall carry out its activities under the responsibility of the Head of Mission.
( 2) Der Missionsleiter bericht dem Rat der Europäischen Union durch den Generalsekretär/ Hohen Vertreter regelmäßig über die Tätigkeit und die Erkenntnisse der EUMM. The Head of Mission shall report regularly to the Council of the European Union, through the Secretary-General / High Representative, on the activities and findings of the EUMM.
( 3) Die Aufgaben der EUMM werden vom Generalsekretär/ Hohen Vertreter in enger Zusammenarbeit mit dem Vorsitz und in Einklang mit der vom Rat verabschiedeten Politik für den Westlichen Balkan festgelegt. The functions of the EUMM shall be determined by the Secretary-General / High Representative in close cooperation with the Presidency and in accordance with the policy for the Western Balkans adopted by the Council.
( 4) Der Missionsleiter unterrichtet die Aufnahmepartei regelmäßig über die Tätigkeit der EUMM. The Head of Mission shall regularly inform the host party of the activities of the EUMM.
( 1) Fahrzeuge und andere Transportmittel der EUMM unterliegen keine Zwangszulassung oder -genehmigung; alle Fahrzeuge sind bei Dritten versicherung. Vehicles and other means of transport of the EUMM shall not be subject to compulsory registration or approval; all vehicles shall be insured with third parties.
( 2) Die EUMM kann Roads, Bridges, Canals und andere Wasserstraße, Hafenanlagen und Flugplätze ohne Zahlung von Gebühren, Maut oder anderen Abgaben benutzt. EUMM may use roads, bridges, canals and other waterways, port facilities and airports without payment of fees, tolls or other charges.
( 3) Die Aufnahmepartei erleichtert der EUMM den Betrieb ihrer eigenen Fahrzeuge und anderen Transportmittel. The host Party shall facilitate the operation of its own vehicles and other means of transport for the EUMM.
( 1) Das EUMM-Personal hat zum Zwecke der Ausübung seiner Tätigkeit zu geringsten Kosten Zugang zu angemessenen Telekommunikationseinrichtungen der Aufnahmepartei, auch zum Zwecke der Kommunikation mit diplomatischen oder konsularischen Vertretern der Entsendeparteien. For the purpose of carrying out its activities, the EUMM staff shall have, at the lowest cost, access to appropriate telecommunications facilities of the host Party, including for the purpose of communicating with diplomatic or consular representatives of the posting parties.
( 2) Die EUMM hat das Recht auf uneingeschränkte Kommunikation mit eigenen Funkgeräten (einschließlich Satelliten-, Mobil- und Handfunk geräte), Telefonen, Telegrafen, Faxgeräten oder anderen Mitteln. EUMM shall have the right to communicate without restriction by means of its own radios (including satellite, mobile and hand-held radios), telephones, telegraphs, fax machines or other means.
The host Party shall provide, after signature of this Agreement, the frequencies on which radios may be operated.
( 1) Die EUMM erhält den Status einer diplomatischen Mission. The EUMM shall have the status of a diplomatic mission.
( 2) Die Beobachter genießen während ihrer Mission in Einklang mit dem Wiener Übereinkommen über diplomatische Beziehungen die Vorrechte und Immunitäten diplomatischer Bediensteter. The observers shall enjoy, during their mission in accordance with the Vienna Convention on Diplomatic Relations, the privileges and immunities of diplomatic officials.
( 3) Das Missionsbüro in Belgrad, andere Büro und alle Transportmittel der EUMM sind unverletzlich. The mission office in Belgrade, other offices and all means of transport of the EUMM shall be inviolable.
( 4) Die Vorrechte und Immunitäten nach diesem Artikel stehen den Beobachter während ihrer Mission zu und danach in Bezug auf Handlungen, die sie zuvor im Rahmen ihrer Mission ausgeführt haben. The privileges and immunities provided for in this Article shall apply to the observers during their mission and thereafter in respect of actions previously performed by them under their mission.
( 5) Die Aufnahmepartei erleichtert alle Bewegungsdes Missionsleiter und des Personals der EUMM. The host Party shall facilitate the movements of the Head of Mission and the staff of the EUMM.
The EUMM shall provide the host party with a list of the members of the EUMM and shall inform the host party in advance of the arrival or departure of EUMM staff.
The EUMM staff shall carry the national passport and an identity card of the EUMM.
( 6) Die Aufnahmepartei erkennt das Recht der Entsendeparteien und der EUMM an, zollfrei und ohne sonstige Beschränkungen die von der EUMM benötigten und zu ihrer ausschließlichen und offizielle Verwendung bestimmten Ausrüstungen, Vorräte, Lieferungen und anderen Güter einzuführen. The host Party shall recognise the right of the posting parties and of the EUMM to introduce, duty free and without other restrictions, the equipment, supplies and other goods required by the EUMM and intended for their exclusive and official use.
The receiving Party shall also recognise its right to buy such items in the territory of the receiving Party and to export or otherwise dispose of such imported or purchased equipment, stocks, supplies and other goods.
The host Party shall also recognise the right of the observers to buy and / or import items for personal use duty free and to export such items.
The Government of the Federal Republic of Yugoslavia declares its readiness to assist the EUMM, upon request, in the search for suitable office space and accommodation.
The participating Parties shall decide on other provisions concerning privileges and immunities, on practical arrangements, including emergency medical assistance and evacuation, and on requirements for travel documents.
This Agreement shall enter into force upon signature.
Its provisions shall be applied provisionally by the receiving Party of the EUMM from the date of initialling until its entry into force by signature.
The Agreement shall remain in force until one of the participating Parties notifies the other Party, within a period of two months, of its intention to request the cessation of such activities.
The Agreement shall replace the Arrangement of 13 July 1991.
PROTOCOL TO THE 1979 AGREEMENT ON FURTHER BORDER TRANSIT OF AIR PROTECTION IN HEAVY METALS
Determined to implement the Convention on long-range transboundary air pollution,
Concerned that emissions of certain heavy metals are carried across national borders and cause damage to ecosystems of environmental and economic importance and may have adverse effects on human health;
Considering that combustion and industrial processes are the primary anthropogenic sources of emissions of heavy metals into the atmosphere;
Aware that heavy metals are natural constituents of the earth <unk> s crust and that many heavy metals, in certain forms and in appropriate concentrations, are vital;
Taking into account existing scientific and technical data on emissions, geochemical processes, atmospheric transport and the effects of heavy metals on human health and the environment, as well as on mitigation procedures and costs;
Aware of the existence of techniques and procedures to reduce air pollution caused by emissions of heavy metals,
Aware that the economic conditions vary from country to country within the competence of the United Nations Economic Commission for Europe (UN-ECE) and that the economy of certain countries is in transition to a market economy;
Determined to take measures to prevent, prevent or minimise emissions of certain heavy metals and their corresponding compounds, taking into account the precautionary principle in accordance with principle 15 of the Rio Declaration on Environment and Development;
Reaffirming that States have the sovereign right, in accordance with the Charter of the United Nations and the principles of international law, to use their own natural resources in accordance with their own environmental and development policies, and the duty to ensure that activities carried out within or under their control do not harm the environment in other States or areas outside their national jurisdictions;
Aware that measures to limit emissions of heavy metals would also contribute to the protection of the environment and human health in areas beyond the competence of UN-ECE, including the Arctic and international waters;
RECOGNISING that the reduction of emissions of certain heavy metals may bring additional benefits to the reduction of emissions of other pollutants;
Aware that further and more effective measures may be needed to limit and reduce emissions of certain heavy metals and that, for example, impact studies may provide a basis for further action;
Considering the important contribution of the private and non-governmental sectors to knowledge of the impacts associated with heavy metals, existing alternatives and abatement techniques and their role in reducing emissions of heavy metals,
Conscious of the measures taken at national level and in international fora to control heavy metals,
<unk> Convention <unk> the Convention on long-range transboundary air pollution adopted at Geneva on 13 November 1979;
<unk> EMEP <unk> the programme for cooperation in the measurement and evaluation of the long-range transmission of air pollutants in Europe;
<unk> executive body
<unk> Commission
<unk> Contracting Parties
6. <unk> geographical scope of EMEP
<unk> heavy metals
<unk> emission
9. <unk> stationary source
10. <unk> new stationary source
It is for the competent national authorities to decide whether a change is essential, taking into account such factors as the environmental benefits of the change;
<unk> Major stationary source category
The objective of this Protocol is to limit, in accordance with the following Articles, anthropogenic emissions of heavy metals which are widely transported across frontiers and which are likely to cause serious harm to human health or the environment.
( 1) Jede Vertragspartei verringert ihre jährlichen Gesamtemissionen aller der in Anhang I aufgeführten Schwermetalle in die Atmosphere vom Stand der Emissionen in einem nach diesem Anhang festgelegten Bezugsjahr durch wirksame Maßnahmen, die ihren besonderen Gegebenheiten angemessen sind. Each Party shall reduce its total annual emissions of all the heavy metals listed in Annex I into the atmosphere from the level of emissions in a reference year specified in this Annex by effective measures appropriate to its particular circumstances.
( 2) Jede Vertragspartei wendet spätestens nach Ablauf der in Anhang IV angegebenen Fristen Folgendes an: Each Contracting Party shall, not later than after the expiry of the periods specified in Annex IV, apply the following:
( a) which, having regard to Annex III, identifies the best available techniques for each new stationary source within a category of major stationary sources for which Annex III identifies the best available techniques;
( b) the limits set out in Annex V to each new stationary source within a category of major stationary sources.
As an alternative, either Party may adopt other emission abatement strategies leading to equivalent total emissions;
( c) which, having regard to Annex III, identifies the best available techniques for each existing stationary source within a category of major stationary sources for which Annex III identifies the best available techniques.
As an alternative, a Contracting Party may adopt other emission abatement strategies leading to equivalent total emission reductions;
( d) the limits set out in Annex V to any existing stationary source within a category of major stationary sources, where technically and economically feasible.
As an alternative, a Contracting Party may adopt other emission abatement strategies that result in equivalent total emission reductions.
( 3) Jede Vertragspartei wendet nach Maßgabe der in Anhang VI festgelegten Bedingungen und Fristen Produktkontrollmaßnahmen an. Each Party shall apply product control measures in accordance with the conditions and deadlines set out in Annex VI.
( 4) Jede Vertragspartei soll unter Berücksichtigung des Anhangs VII die Anwendung zusätzlicher Produktmanagementmaßnahmen erwägen. Each Contracting Party shall, taking into account Annex VII, consider the application of additional product management measures.
( 5) Jede Vertragspartei erstellt und unterhält Emissionsverzeichnisse für die in Anhang I aufgeführten Schwermetalle, wobei für die Vertragsparteien im geographischen Anwendungsbereich des EMEP als Minimum die vom Lenkungsorgan des EMEP festgelegten Methoden zur Anwendung kommen und für die Vertragsparteien außerhalb des geographischen Anwendungsbereichs des EMEP als Leittschnur die im Arbeitslan des Exekutivorgans Developed Methods Serve as a guideline for the Parties outside the geographical scope of EMEP as a minimum of the methods established by the steering body of EMEP.
( 6) Eine Vertragspartei, die nach Anwendung der Absätze 2 und 3 den Anforderungen des Absatzes 1 für ein in Anhang I aufgeführtes Schwermetall nicht entsprechen kann, wird für dieses Schwermetall von ihren Verpflichtungen nach Absatz 1 befreit. A Contracting Party which cannot meet the requirements of paragraph 1 for a heavy metal listed in Annex I after the application of paragraphs 2 and 3 shall be exempt from its obligations under paragraph 1 for this heavy metal.
( 7) Eine Vertragspartei, deren Gesamtfläche 6000000 km2 überschreitet, wird von ihren Verpflichtungen nach Absatz 2 Buchstaben b), c) und d) befreit, wenn sie nachweisen kann, daß sie nicht später als acht Jahre nach dem Inkrafttreten dieses Protokolls ihre jährlichen Gesamtemissionen jedes der in Anhang I aufgeführten Schwermetalle aus den in Anhang II aufgeführten Kategorien von Quellen um mindestens 50 percent gegenüber dem Emissionniveau dieser Kategorien in dem nach Anhang I festgelegten Bezugsjahr verringert haben. Eine Vertragspartei, die nach diesem Absatz handeln möchte, gibt dies bei der Unterzeichnung dieses Protokolls oder beim Beitritt zu diesem Protokoll an. A Party whose total area exceeds 6000000 km2 shall be exempt from its obligations under paragraph 2 (b), (c) and (d) if it can demonstrate that it will not have reduced its total annual
( 1) Die Vertragsparteien erleichtern in Übereinstimmung mit ihren Gesetzen, sonstigen Vorschriften und Gepflogenheiten den Austausch von Technologien und Techniken, die zur Verringerung der Emissionen von Schwermetallen ausgelegt sind, einschließlich - ohne darauf beschränkt zu sein - des Austauschs, mit dem die Entwicklung von Produktmanagementmaßnahmen und die Anwendung bester verfügbarer Techniken unterstützt wird, indem sie insbesondere folgendes fördern: The Parties shall, in accordance with their laws, regulations and practices, facilitate the exchange of technologies and techniques designed to reduce emissions of heavy metals, including, without limitation, exchanges that support the development of product management measures and the application of best available techniques, by promoting in particular the following:
( a) the commercial exchange of available technology;
( b) direct industrial contacts and cooperation, including joint ventures;
( c) the exchange of information and experience; and
( d) the provision of technical assistance.
( 2) Bei der Förderung der in Absatz 1 aufgeführten Tätigkeiten schaffen die Vertragsparteien günstige Bedingungen durch die Erleichterung von Kontakten und Zusammenarbeit zwischen geeigneten Organisationen und Einzelpersonen des privaten und öffentlichen Sektors, die in der Lage sind, Technologien, Konstruktions- und Ingenieurleistungen, Ausrüstungen oder Finanzmittel bereitzustellen. In promoting the activities listed in paragraph 1 of this Article, the Contracting Parties shall create favourable conditions by facilitating contacts and cooperation between appropriate organisations and individuals of the private and public sectors able to providing technology, design and engineering services, equipment or finance.
( 1) Jede Vertragspartei entwickelt unverzüglich Strategien, Politiken und Programme, um ihren Verpflichtungen aus diesem Protokoll nachzukommen. Each Contracting Party shall, without delay, develop strategies, policies and programmes to fulfil its obligations under this Protocol.
( 2) Eine Vertragspartei kann ebenfalls: A Contracting Party may also:
( a) use economic instruments to promote cost effective approaches to the reduction of heavy metal emissions;
( b) promote contracts between the State and industry and voluntary agreements;
( c) support the more efficient use of resources and raw materials;
( d) encourage the use of less polluting energy sources;
( e) take measures to develop and introduce transport systems with a lower environmental impact;
( f) take measures for the gradual replacement of certain heavy metal releasing processes where applicable substitutes are available on an industrial scale;
( g) take measures to develop and use clean processes for the prevention and control of environmental pollution.
( 3) Die Vertragsparteien können strengere als die in diesem Protokoll geforderten Maßnahmen ergreifen. The Contracting Parties may take more stringent measures than those required by this Protocol.
The Parties shall, with an emphasis on the heavy metals listed in Annex I, promote research, development, monitoring and cooperation, inter alia, with respect to:
( a) emissions, long range transport, deposition and modelling thereof, existing concentrations in the biotic and abiotic environment, the elaboration of procedures for the harmonisation of relevant methods;
( b) pollutant paths and inventories in representative ecosystems;
( c) relevant effects on human health and the environment, including the quantification of such effects;
( d) best available techniques and practices and emission limitation procedures currently in use or under development among the Parties;
( e) collection, recovery and, where necessary, disposal of products or waste containing one or more heavy metals;
( f) methods that allow the consideration of socioeconomic factors in the assessment of alternative mitigation strategies;
( g) an impact-based approach integrating relevant information, including information under subparagraphs (a) to (f), on measured or modelled environmental concentrations, transmission pathways and impacts on human health and the environment, for the purpose of formulating future best possible mitigation strategies that take into account economic and technological factors;
( h) alternatives to the use of heavy metals in the products listed in Annexes VI and VII;
( i) collection of information on concentrations of heavy metals in certain products, on the emission potential of such metals during production, processing, trade, use and disposal of the product, and on procedures to reduce such emissions.
( 1) In Übereinstimmung mit ihren Rechtsvorschriften über die Vertraulichkeit gewerblicher Informationen In accordance with their laws on the confidentiality of commercial information
( a) each Contracting Party shall provide to the executive body, through the Executive Secretary of the Commission, periodically, as determined by the Contracting Parties meeting in the executive body, information on the measures it has taken to implement this Protocol;
( b) each Contracting Party within the geographical scope of EMEP shall, through the Executive Secretary of the Commission, at regular intervals to be determined by the Steering Body of EMEP and approved by the Contracting Parties at a meeting of the Executive Body, provide it with information on the level of emissions of the heavy metals listed in Annex I, at least in accordance with the methods and temporal and spatial resolution established by the Steering Body of EMEP.
Parties outside the geographical scope of EMEP shall, upon request, provide similar information to the executive body.
In addition, each Contracting Party shall, where appropriate, collect and report relevant information on its emissions of other heavy metals, taking into account the methodological guidelines and the temporal and spatial resolution of the steering body of EMEP and of the executive body.
( 2) Die nach Absatz 1 Buchstabe a) vorzulegenden Informationen müssen im Einklang mit einem von den Vertragsparteien auf einer Tagung des Exekutivorgans gefassten Entscheidung über Form und Inhalt der Informationen stehen. The information to be submitted in accordance with paragraph 1 (a) of this Article shall be in accordance with a decision taken by the Parties at a meeting of the executive body on the form and content of the information.
The provisions of this Decision shall, if necessary, be reviewed in order to identify additional elements concerning the form or content of the information to be included in the report.
( 3) Rechtzeitig vor jeder Jahrestagung des Exekutivorgans legt das EMEP Informationen über den weiträumigen Transport und die Deposition von Schwermetallen vor. In good time before each annual meeting of the executive body, EMEP shall provide information on the long range transport and deposition of heavy metals.
EMEP shall provide the executive body with calculations of transboundary flows and depositions of heavy metals within the geographical scope of EMEP, using appropriate models and measurements and in good time before each annual meeting of the executive body.
Outside the geographical scope of EMEP, appropriate models shall be used to reflect the particular circumstances of the Contracting Parties to the Convention.
Compliance with the obligations of the Parties under this Protocol shall be regularly reviewed.
The Implementing Committee established by Decision 1997 / 2 of the executive body at its fifteenth session shall carry out such reviews and report to the Contracting Parties meeting in the executive body in accordance with the Annex to that Decision, including its amendments.
Review by the Contracting Parties at meetings of the executive body
( 1) Die Vertragsparteien überprüfen auf den Tagungen des Exekutivorgans nach Artikel 10 Absatz 2 Buchstabe a) des Übereinkommens die von den Vertragsparteien, dem EMEP und anderen Nebenorganen vorgelegten Informationen und die in Artikel 9 dieses Protokolls bezeichneten Berichte des Durchführungsausschuss. The Parties shall, at meetings of the executive body pursuant to Article 10 (2) (a) of the Convention, review the information provided by the Parties, EMEP and other subsidiary bodies and the reports of the Executive Committee referred to in Article 9 of this Protocol.
( 2) Die Vertragsparteien überprüfen auf den Tagungen des Exekutivorgans, welche Fortschritte auf dem Weg zur Erfuellung der Verpflichtungen aus diesem Protokoll gemacht worden sind. The Contracting Parties shall, at the meetings of the executive body, review the progress made towards the fulfilment of the obligations under this Protocol.
( 3) Die Vertragsparteien überprüfen auf den Tagungen des Exekutivorgans, ob die in diesem Protokoll festgelegten Verpflichtungen ausreichend und wirksam sind. The Contracting Parties shall, at meetings of the executive body, verify whether the obligations set out in this Protocol are adequate and effective.
( a) such reviews shall take into account the best available scientific information on the effects of the deposition of heavy metals, assessments of technological developments and changing economic conditions;
( b) such reviews shall be conducted in the light of research, development, monitoring and cooperation under this Protocol;
( i) assess progress towards attaining the objective of this Protocol;
( ii) assess whether additional emission reductions in excess of the levels required by this Protocol are justified in order to further reduce adverse effects on human health or the environment; and
( iii) take into account the extent to which there is a satisfactory basis for the application of an impact approach;
( c) the procedures, methods and timetable for such reviews shall be determined by the Parties at a meeting of the executive body.
( 4) Die Vertragsparteien erstellen anhand der Schlufolgerungen aus den in Absatz 3 bezeichneten Überprüfungen so bald wie möglich nach Abschluss der Überprüfung einen Arbeitlan über weitere Schritte zur Verringerung der Emissionen der in Anhang I aufgeführten Schwermetalle in die Atmosphalle. The Parties shall draw up, on the basis of the conclusions of the reviews referred to in paragraph 3 of this Article, a work plan on further steps to reduce the emissions of the heavy metals listed in Annex I into the atmosphere as soon as possible after the review has been completed.
( 1) Im Fall einer Streitigkeit zwischen zwei oder mehr Vertragsparteien über die Auslegung oder Anwendung dieses Protokolls bemühen sich die betroffenen Vertragsparteien um eine Beilegung der Streitigkeit durch Verhandlungen oder andere friedliche Mittel ihrer Wahl. In the event of a dispute between two or more Contracting Parties concerning the interpretation or application of this Protocol, the Contracting Parties concerned shall seek a settlement of the dispute by negotiation or other peaceful means of their choice.
The parties to the dispute shall inform the executive body of their dispute.
( 2) Bei der Ratifikation, der Annahme oder der Genehmigung dieses Protokolls oder beim Beitritt zu diesem Protokoll oder jederzeit danach kann eine Vertragspartei, die keine Organisation der regionalen Wirtschaftsintegration ist, in einer dem Verwahrer vorgelegten schriftlichen Urkunde erklären, daß sie in Bezug auf jede Streitigkeit über die Auslegung oder Anwendung des Protokolls eines oder beide der folgenden Mittel der Streitbeilegung gegenüber jeder Vertragspartei, welche dieselbe Verpflichtung übernimmt, von Rechts wegen und ohne besondere Übereinkunft als obligatorisch anerkennt: In the event of ratification, acceptance or approval of this Protocol or of accession to this Protocol or at any time thereafter, a Party which is not a regional economic integration organisation may declare in a written instrument submitted to the depositary that, in respect of any dispute concerning the interpretation or application of the Protocol, it recognises one or both of the following means of
( a) submission of the dispute to the International Court of Justice;
( b) arbitration in accordance with procedures decided by the Contracting Parties as soon as possible at a session of the executive body in an Annex concerning arbitration.
A Contracting Party which is a regional economic integration organisation may make a declaration having equivalent effect in respect of arbitration under the procedure provided for in subparagraph (b) of this Article.
( 3) Eine nach Absatz 2 abgegebene Erklärung bleibt in Kraft, bis sie gemäß den darin enthaltenen Bestimmungen erlischt, oder bis zum Ablauf von drei Monaten nach Hinterlegung einer schriftlichen Rücknahmenotifikation beim Verwahrer. A declaration made in accordance with paragraph 2 of this Article shall remain in force until it expires in accordance with the provisions contained therein, or until the expiry of three months after the deposit of a notification of written withdrawal with the depositary.
( 4) Eine neue Erklärung, eine Rücknahmenotifikation oder das Erlöschen einer Erklärung berührt nicht die beim Internationalen Gerichtshof oder bei dem Schiedsgericht anpending Verfahren, sofern die Streitparteien nichts anderes vereinbaren. A new declaration, notification of withdrawal or the lapse of a declaration shall not affect proceedings before the International Court of Justice or the arbitral tribunal, unless the parties to the dispute agree otherwise.
( 5) Vorbehaltlich der Einigung der Streitparteien auf die Mittel der Streitbeilegung nach Absatz 2 wird die Streitigkeit auf Ersuchen einer der Streitparteien einem Vergleichsverfahren unterworfen, wenn nach Ablauf von zwölf Monaten, nachdem eine Vertragspartei einer anderen notifiziert hat, daß eine Streitigkeit zwischen ihnen besteht, die betreffenden Vertragsparteien ihre Streitigkeit nicht durch die in Absatz 1 genannten Mittel beilegen konnten. Subject to the agreement of the parties to the dispute on the means of dispute settlement referred to in paragraph 2, the dispute shall, at the request of either of the parties to the dispute, be subject to conciliation if, at the end of 12 months after one Party has notified another that a dispute exists between them, the Parties concerned were unable to settle their dispute through the means referred to in paragraph 1 of this Article.
( 6) Für die Zwecke des Absatzes 5 wird eine Vergleichskommission gebildet. For the purposes of paragraph 5, a Comparative Commission shall be established.
The Commission shall be composed of an equal number of members appointed by the parties concerned or, in the case of several parties to the conciliation procedure, by the entirety of those parties, and a chairman elected jointly by the members so appointed.
The Commission shall render a recommendative award which the Parties shall examine in good faith.
in the form of an exchange of letters between the European Community and the Argentine Republic under Article XXVIII of the General Agreement on Tariffs and Trade (GATT) 1994 amending the concessions concerning garlic provided for in the CXL list annexed to GATT
Convention for the Unification of Certain Rules relating to International Carriage by Air
RECOGNIZING the important contribution made by the Agreement on the Unification of Rules for International Carriage (hereinafter referred to as the <unk> Warsaw Agreement <unk>) signed in Warsaw on 12 October 1929 and other related agreements for the harmonisation of private international air transport law;
RECOGNISING the need to modernise and bring together the Warsaw Convention and related instruments,
ACKNOWLEDGING the importance of the protection of consumer interests in respect of international air transport and of reasonable levels of compensation <unk> (1) in accordance with the principle of full compensation;
AFFIRMING the desire for the orderly development of international air traffic and the smooth carriage of passengers, luggage and goods in accordance with the principles and objectives of the Agreement on International Civil Aviation concluded at Chicago on 7 December 1944,
CONVINCED that joint action by States to further harmonize and codify certain rules relating to international carriage by air by means of a new Agreement is the best means of achieving a fair balance of interests,
( 1) Dieses Übereinkommen gilt für jede internationale Beförderung von Personen, ReisegeLuck oder Gütern, die durch Luftfahrzeuge gegen Entgelt erfolgt. This Convention shall apply to any international carriage of persons, luggage or goods carried by aircraft against payment.
It shall also apply to carriage free of charge by aircraft carried out by an air carrier.
( 2) Als <unk> internationale Beförderung <unk> im Sinne dieses Übereinkommens ist jede Beförderung anzusehen, bei der nach den Vereinbarungen der Parteien der Abgangsort und der Bestimmungsort, gleichviel ob eine Unterbrechung der Beförderung oder ein Fahrzeugwechsel stattfinden oder nicht, in den Hoheitsgebieten von zwei Vertragsstaaten liegen oder, wenn diese Orte zwar im Hoheitsgebiet nur eines Vertragsstaats liegen, aber eine Zwischenlandung in dem Hoheitsgebiet eines anderen Staates vorgesehen ist, selbst wenn dieser Staat kein Vertragsstaat ist. <unk> international transport
Carriage between two locations within the territory of only one State Party without a stopover in the territory of another State shall not be considered as international carriage within the meaning of this Agreement.
( 3) Ist eine Beförderung von mehreren consecufolgenden Luftfrachtführern auszuführen, so gilt sie, gleichviel ob der Beförderungsvertrag in der Form eines einzigen Vertrags oder einer Reihe von Verträgen geschlossen worden ist, bei der Anwendung dieses Übereinkommens als eine einzige Beförderung, sofern sie von den Parteien als eintliche Leistung vereinbart worden ist; eine solche Beförderung verlieren ihre Eigenschaft als internationale Beförderung nicht dadurch, daß ein Vertrag oder eine Reihe von Verträgen ausschließlich im Hoheitsgebiet desselben Staates zu erfuellen ist. If carriage is to be carried out by several successive carriers, it shall be considered, irrespective of whether the contract of carriage has been concluded in the form of a single contract or a series of treaties, as a single carriage in the application of this Agreement, provided that it has been agreed by the Parties as a single service; such carriage shall not lose its status as international carriage by
( 4) Dieses Übereinkommen gilt auch für Beförderungen nach Kapitel V vorbehaltlich<unk> 2) der darin enthaltenen Bedingungen. This Agreement shall also apply to promotions provided for in Chapter V (2) of the conditions contained therein.
State transport and carriage of mail
( 1) Dieses Übereinkommen gilt auch für die Beförderungen, die der Staat oder eine andere juristische Person des öffentlichen Rechts ausführt, wenn die Voraussetzungen des Artikels 1 vorliegen. This Convention shall also apply to promotions carried out by the State or any other legal entity governed by public law, if the conditions laid down in Article 1 are met.
( 2) Bei der Befuhr von Postsendungen haftet der Luftfrachtführer nur gegenüber der zuständigen Postverwaltung nach Maßgabe der auf die Beziehungen zwischen Luftfrachtführern und Postverwaltungen anwendbaren Vorschriften. In the case of the carriage of postal consignments, the air carrier shall be liable only to the competent postal administration in accordance with the rules applicable to relations between air carriers and postal administrations.
( 3) Mit Ausnahme des Absatzes 2 gilt dieses Übereinkommen nicht für die Beförderung von Postsendungen. With the exception of paragraph 2 of this Article, the provisions of this Convention shall not apply to the carriage of mail.
PRODUCTS AND PROVIDERS OF THE PARTIES REFERRED THE PRODUCTION OF TRAVELLING, JOURNEY PACKAGES AND GOODS
( 1) Bei der Beförderung von Reisenden ist ein Einzel- oder Sammelbeförderungsschein auszuhändigen; er muss enthalten: In the case of passenger transport, a single or collective transport document shall be issued and shall contain:
( a) indication of the place of departure and destination;
( b) if the place of departure and destination is in the territory of the same State Party but one or more stopovers are provided in the territory of another State, the indication of at least one of these stopovers.
( 2) Jede andere Aufzeichnung, welche die in Absatz 1 genannten Angaben enthält, kann anstelle des in jenem Absatz genannten Beförderungsscheins verwendet werden. Any other record containing the information referred to in paragraph 1 of this Article may be used instead of the transport document referred to in that paragraph.
Where such other records are used, the carrier shall offer to provide the passenger with a written declaration of the information contained therein.
( 3) Der Luftfrachtführer hat dem Reisenden für jedes aufgegebene Baggage stück einen Beleg zur Baggage identifizierung auszuhändigen. The air carrier shall hand over to the passenger a voucher for luggage identification for each item of checked baggage.
( 4) Der Wanderer ist schriftlich darauf Hinweisen, daß dieses Übereinkommen, soweit es Anwendung findet, die Haftung des Luftfrachtführers für Tod oder Körperverletzung, für Zerstörung, Verlust oder Beschädigung von Baggage sowie für verzötung regelt und beschränken kann. The Traveller shall be notified in writing that this Convention, to the extent applicable, governs and may limit the air carrier <unk> s liability for death or bodily injury, for the destruction, loss or damage of luggage, and for delay.
( 5) Die Nichtsehtung der Absätze 1 bis 4 berührt weder den Bestand noch die Wirksamkeit des Beförderungsvertrags; dieser unterliegt gleichwohl den Vorschriften dieses Übereinkommens einschließlich derjenigen über die Haftungsbeschränkung. Failure to comply with paragraphs 1 to 4 of this Article shall not affect the existence or effectiveness of the Contract of Carriage, which shall nonetheless be subject to the provisions of this Convention, including those relating to the limitation of liability.
( 1) Bei der Beförderung von Gütern ist ein Luftwachtbrief auszuhändigen. A consignment note shall be issued for the carriage of goods.
( 2) Anstelle eines Luftwachtbriefs kann jede andere Aufzeichnung verwendet werden, welche die Angaben über die auszuführende Beförderung enthält. In lieu of an air waybill, any other record containing the information on the transport to be carried may be used.
Where such other records are used, the air carrier shall, at the sender <unk> s request, provide the sender with an acknowledgement of receipt of the goods, which shall enable the consignment to be identified and the information contained in such other records to be used.
The bill of lading and the acknowledgement of receipt of goods shall contain:
( a) indication of the place of departure and destination;
( b) if the place of departure and destination is in the territory of the same State Party but one or more stopovers are provided in the territory of another State, the indication of at least one of these stopovers;
( c) indication of the weight of the consignment.
Where necessary, the sender may be required to issue a document indicating the nature of the goods in order to comply with the requirements of customs, police or other authorities.
This provision shall not give rise to any obligation, liability or liability on the part of the carrier.
( 1) Der Luftwachtbrief wird vom Absender in drei Ausfertigungen ausgestellt. The consignment note shall be issued by the sender in three copies.
( 2) Die erste Ausfertigung trägt den Vermerk <unk> für den Luftfrachtführer <unk>; sie wird vom Absender unterzeichnet. The first copy shall bear the mark <unk> for the carrier <unk> and shall be signed by the sender.
The second copy shall bear the <unk> note for the consignee <unk> and shall be signed by the sender and the carrier.
The third copy shall be signed by the carrier and, upon receipt of the goods, handed over to the sender.
( 3) Die Unterschrift des Luftfrachtführer und diejenige des Absenders können gedruckt oder durch einen Stempel ersetzt werden. The signature of the carrier and that of the sender may be printed or stamped.
( 4) Wird der Luftfrachtbrief auf Verlangen des Absenders vom Luftfrachtführer ausgestellt, so wird bis zum Beweis des Gegenteils suspects, daß der Luftfrachtführer im Namen des Absenders gehandelt hat. If the air bill of lading is issued by the air carrier on the sender <unk> s request, it shall be assumed, pending evidence of the contrary, that the air carrier has acted on the sender <unk> s behalf.
( a) the carrier may require the sender to issue individual air waybills;
( b) the sender may require the carrier to hand over individual acknowledgements of receipt if other records are used within the meaning of Article 4 (2).
Failure to comply with Articles 4 to 8 shall not prejudice the existence or effectiveness of the Contract of Carriage, which is nevertheless subject to the provisions of this Convention, including those relating to the limitation of liability.
( 1) Der Absender haftet für die Richtigkeit der Angaben und Erklärungen über die Güter, die von ihm oder in seinem Namen in den Luftfrachtbrief eingetragen werden, sowie der von ihm oder in seinem Namen dem Luftfrachtführer gegemacht Angaben oder Erklärungen zur Aufnahme in die Empfangsbescheintigung über die Güter oder in die anderen Aufzeichnungen im Sinne des Artikels 4 Absatz 2. Dies gilt auch, wenn die für den Absender handelnde Person gleichzeitig der Beauftragte des Luftfrachtführers ist. The sender shall be liable for the correctness of the information and declarations concerning the goods entered by him or in his name in the air carriage letter, and of the information or declarations made by him or in his name to the air cargo carrier for inclusion in the receipt of the goods or other records referred to in Article 4 (2).
( 2) Der Absender hat dem Luftfrachtführer den Schaden zu ersetzen, den dieser oder ein Dritte, dem der Luftfrachtführer haftet, dadurch erleiden, daß die von dem Absender oder in seiner Namen gegemacht Angaben und Erklärungen unrichtig, ungenau oder invollständig sind. The sender shall compensate the air carrier for any damage incurred by the latter or any third party to which the air carrier is liable as a result of incorrect, inaccurate or incomplete information and declarations provided by the sender or on his behalf.
( 3) Vorbehaltlich<unk> 3) der Absätze 1 und 2 hat der Luftfrachtführer dem Absender den Schaden zu ersetzen, den dieser oder ein Dritte, dem der Absender haftet, dadurch erleiden, daß die Angaben und Erklärungen, die vom Luftfrachtführer oder in seinem Namen in die Empfangsbescheintigung über die Güter oder in die anderen Aufzeichnungen im Sinne des Artikels 4 Absatz 2 aufgenommen wurden, unrichtig, ingenau oder invollständig sind. Subject to the provisions of paragraphs 1 and 2 of this Article, the air carrier shall compensate the sender for the damage incurred by the sender or by a third party to whom the sender is liable by the information and declarations entered by the air carrier or on its behalf in the receipt of the goods or other records referred to in Article 4 (2) being incorrect, inaccurate or incomplete.
( 1) Der Luftfrachtbrief und die Empfangsbescheintigung über die Güter begründen die widerlegbare Vermutung für den Abschluss des Vertrags, die Annahme der Güter und die Beförderungsbedingungen, die darin niedergelegt sind. The air bill of lading and the receipt of the goods shall give rise to the refutable presumption of the conclusion of the contract, the acceptance of the goods and the conditions of carriage laid down therein.
( 2) Die Angaben in dem Luftfrachtbrief und der Empfangsbescheintigung über die Güter zu gewicht, Maßen und Verpackung sowie zu der Anzahl der Frachtstücke begründen die widerlegbare Vermutung ihrer Richtigkeit; die Angaben über Menge, Rauminhalt und Zustand der Güter begründen diese Vermutung gegenüber dem Luftfrachtführer nur insoweit, als er diese Angaben in Gegenwart des Absenders nachgeprüft hat und dies auf dem Luftfrachtbrief oder der Empfangsbescheintigung vermerkt ist, oder wenn es sich um Angaben handelt, die sich auf den äußerlich erkennbaren Zustand der Güter beziehen. The particulars in the air bill and the acknowledgement of receipt of the weight, dimensions and packaging of the goods and the number of the pieces of freight shall give rise to the disproving presumption of their correctness; the quantity, volume and condition of the goods shall
( 1) Der Absender ist unter der Eindingung, daß er alle Verpflichtungen aus dem Frachtvertrag erfuellt, berechtigt, über die Güter in der Weise zu verfügen, daß er sie am Abgangs- oder Bestimmungsflughafen sich zurückgeben, unterwegs während einer Landhalt, am Bestimmungsort oder unterwegs an eine andere Person als den ursprünglich bezeichneten Empfänger abliefern oder zum Abgangsflughafen zurückbringen lässt. The sender shall be entitled to dispose of the goods in such a way as to return them at the airport of departure or destination, to stop on the way during a landing, to deliver them to a person other than the original designated consignee or to return them to the airport of departure, provided that he fulfils all the obligations under the freight contract.
This right may be exercised only to the extent that it does not prejudice the air carrier or the other senders, and the sender is obliged to reimburse the costs incurred in exercising that right.
( 2) Ist die Ausführung der Weisungen des Absenders impossible, so hat der Luftfrachtführer ihn unverzüglich zu verständigen. If it is impossible to carry out the instructions of the sender, the air carrier shall notify him immediately.
( 3) Kommt der Luftfrachtführer den Weisungen des Absenders nach, ohne die Vorlage der diesem übergebenen Ausfertigung des Luftfrachtbriefs oder der Empfangsbescheintigung über die Güter zu verlangen, so haftet er unbeschadet seines Rückgriffsanspruchs gegen den Absender dem rechtmäßigen Besitz des Luftfrachtbriefs oder der Empfangsbescheintigung über die Güter für den daraus entstehenden Schaden. If the air carrier complies with the sender <unk> s instructions without requesting the presentation of the copy of the air bill of lading or the acknowledgement of receipt of the goods, it shall, without prejudice to its claim of recourse against the sender, be liable to the rightful owner of the air bill of lading or the acknowledgement of receipt of the goods for the resulting damage.
( 4) Das Recht des Absenders erlischt mit dem Zeitpunkt, in dem das Recht des Empfängers nach Artikel 13 entstehen. The right of the sender shall cease when the right of the recipient arises in accordance with Article 13.
However, it revives when the consignee refuses to accept the goods or when it cannot be reached.
( 1) Sofern der Absender nicht von seinem Recht nach Artikel 12 Gebrauch gemacht hat, ist der Empfänger berechtigt, nach Eintreffen der Güter am Destmungsort vom Luftfrachtführer die Ablieferung der Güter gegen Zahlung der geschuldeten Beträge und gegen Erfuellung der Beförderungsbedingungen zu verlangen. Unless the sender has exercised his right under Article 12, the consignee shall be entitled, upon the arrival of the goods at the destination, to request from the air carrier the delivery of the goods against payment of the sums due and against fulfilment of the conditions of carriage.
( 2) Sofern nichts anderes vereinbart ist, hat der Luftfrachtführer dem Empfänger das Eintreffen der Güter unverzüglich anzuanzeigen. Unless otherwise agreed, the carrier shall notify the consignee immediately of the arrival of the goods.
( 3) Hat der Luftfrachtführer den Verlust der Güter anerkannt oder sind die Güter nach Ablauf von sieben Tagen seit dem Tag, an dem sie should eintreffen, nicht eingetroffen, so kann der Empfänger die Rechte aus dem Frachtvertrag gegen den Luftfrachtführer geltend machen. If the air carrier has acknowledged the loss of the goods or if the goods have not arrived after seven days from the date on which they should have arrived, the consignee may claim the rights under the freight contract against the air carrier.
The sender and the consignee may, whether acting on their own account or on behalf of others, assert on their own behalf the rights to which they are entitled under Articles 12 and 13, provided that they fulfil their obligations under the freight contract.
Relationships between sender and consignee or third parties
( 1) Die RechtsBeziehungen zwischen dem Absender und dem Empfänger sowie die RechtsBeziehungen Dritter, die ihre Rechte vom Absender oder vom Empfänger herleiten, werden durch die Artikel 12, 13 und 14 nicht berührt. The legal relations between the sender and the recipient and the legal relations of third parties deriving their rights from the sender or the recipient shall not be affected by Articles 12, 13 and 14.
( 2) Jede von den Artikeln 12, 13 und 14 abweichende Vereinbarung muss auf dem Luftwachtbrief oder auf der Empfangsbescheintigung über die Güter vermerkt werden. Any arrangement deviating from Articles 12, 13 and 14 shall be noted on the air waybill or on the acknowledgement of receipt of the goods.
Rules of customs, police and other authorities
( 1) Der Absender ist verpflichtet, alle Auskünfte zu erteilen und alle Urkunden zur Verfügung zu stellen, die vor Aushändigung der Güter an den Empfänger zur Erfuellung der Vorschriften der Zoll-, der Polizei- und anderer Behörden erforderlich sind. The sender shall be obliged to provide all information and documents required before the goods are handed over to the consignee to satisfy the requirements of customs, police and other authorities.
The sender shall be liable to the air carrier for any damage caused by the absence, incompleteness or inaccuracy of such information and documents, unless the air carrier or its persons are at fault.
( 2) Der Luftfrachtführer ist nicht verpflichtet, diese Auskünfte und Urkunden auf ihre Richtigkeit und Vollständigkeit zu prüfen. The air carrier shall not be obliged to verify the correctness and completeness of such information and documents.
LIABILITY OF THE AIR LANGUAGE AND THE ENVIRONMENT OF THE REPLACEMENT OF DAMAGE (4)
Death and bodily injury of travellers - damage to luggage
( 1) Der Luftfrachtführer hat den Schaden zu ersetzen, der dadurch entstehen, daß ein Reisender getötet oder bodily hurt wird, jedoch nur, wenn sich der Unfall, durch den der Tod oder die Körperverletzung verursacht wurde, an Bord des Luftfahrzeugs oder beim Ein- oder Aussteigen ereignet hat. The air carrier shall replace the damage caused by the death or bodily injury of a passenger, but only if the accident causing death or bodily injury occurred on board the aircraft or when boarding or disembarking.
( 2) Der Luftfrachtführer hat den Schaden zu ersetzen, der durch Zerstörung, Verlust oder Beschädigung von aufgegebenem Reisegeluggck entstehen, jedoch nur, wenn das Event, durch das die die Zerstörung, der Verlust oder die Beschädigung verursacht wurde, an Bord des Luftfahrzeugs oder während eines Zeitraums eingetreten ist, in dem sich das aufgegebene Reisegepäck in der Obhut des Luftfrachtführers befindet. The air carrier shall replace any damage caused by the destruction, loss or damage of checked luggage, but only if the event causing the destruction, loss or damage occurred on board the aircraft or during a period in which the checked luggage was in the care of the air carrier.
However, the carrier shall not be liable if and to the extent that the damage is due to the nature of the baggage or to an inherent defect.
In the case of unchecked luggage, including personal belongings, the carrier shall be liable if the damage is due to its own fault or the fault of its people.
( 3) Hat der Luftfrachtführer den Verlust des aufgegebenen Reisegeluggcks anerkannt oder ist das aufgegebene Reisegeluggck nach Ablauf von undzwanzig Tage seit dem Tag, an dem es should have eintreffen, nicht eingetroffen, so kann der Wanderer die Rechte aus dem Beförderungsvertrag gegen den Luftfrachtführer geltend machen. If the air carrier has acknowledged the loss of the checked baggage or if the checked baggage has not arrived after twenty one days from the date on which it should have arrived, the passenger may claim the rights under the Contract of Carriage against the air carrier.
( 4) Vorbehaltlich<unk> 5) gegenstehender Bestimmungen bedeutet in diesem Übereinkommen der Begriff <unk> Reisegepäck <unk> sowohl aufgegebenes sowie nicht aufgegebenes Reisegepäck. 5) contrary provisions in this Agreement, the term <unk> luggage
( 1) Der Luftfrachtführer hat den Schaden zu ersetzen, der durch Zerstörung, Verlust oder Beschädigung von Gütern entstehen, jedoch nur, wenn das Event, durch das der Schaden verursacht wurde, während der Luftbeförderung eingetreten ist. The air carrier shall replace any damage caused by the destruction, loss or damage to goods, but only if the event causing the damage occurred during the air carriage.
( 2) Der Luftfrachtführer haftet jedoch nicht, wenn und soweit er nachweist, daß die Zerstörung, der Verlust oder die Beschädigung der Güter durch einen oder mehrere der folgenden Umstände verursacht wurde: However, the air carrier shall not be liable if and to the extent that it can prove that the destruction, loss or damage to the goods was caused by one or more of the following circumstances:
( a) the nature of the goods or any defect inherent in them;
( b) faulty packaging of the goods by a person other than the carrier or his staff;
( c) an act of war or armed conflict;
( d) sovereign action in connection with the import, export or transit of the goods.
( 3) Die Luftbeförderung im Sinne des Absatzes 1 umfasst den Zeitraum, während dessen die Güter sich in der Obhut des Luftfrachtführer befinden. Air carriage as defined in paragraph 1 shall cover the period during which the goods are in the care of the air carrier.
( 4) Der Zeitraum der Luftbeförderung umfasst nicht die Beförderung zu Land, zur See oder auf Binnengewässern außerhalb eines Flughafen. The period of air transport shall not include land, sea or inland transport outside an airport.
However, where such carriage is carried out for the purpose of loading, delivery or transhipment in the course of the performance of the contract of carriage by air, it shall be presumed, pending evidence to the contrary, that the damage was caused by an event occurring during the carriage by air.
If, without the consent of the sender, an air carrier replaces, in whole or in part, the air carriage agreed by the Parties by another type of carriage, this shall be considered to have been carried out within the period of carriage.
The carrier shall compensate for any damage caused by a delay in the carriage by air of passengers, luggage or goods.
However, he shall not be liable for the damage caused by the delay if he can prove that he and his people have taken all reasonable measures to avoid the damage or that he or she has not been able to take such measures.
If the air carrier proves that the person claiming the claim for damages (6), or its predecessor in law, caused or contributed to the damage by an unlawful act or omission, whether or not it was negligent, the air carrier shall be fully or partly exempt from its liability to that person to the extent that that act or omission caused or contributed to the damage.
7), the air carrier shall be fully or partially exempt from its liability to the extent that it can prove that the damage was caused or contributed to by an unlawful act or omission on the part of the passenger, whether or not it was negligent.
This Article shall apply to all liability provisions of this Convention, including paragraph 1 of Article 21.
8) In the event of death or bodily injury of a passenger
( 1) Für Schäden nach Artikel 17 Absatz 1, die 100000 Sonderziehungsrechte je Reisenden nicht übersteigen, kann die Haftung des Luftfrachtführers nicht ausgeschlossen oder beschränkt werden. For damage not exceeding 100000 Special Drawing Rights per passenger in accordance with Article 17 (1), the liability of the air carrier shall not be excluded or restricted.
( 2) Der Luftfrachtführer haftet nicht für Schäden nach Artikel 17 Absatz 1, soweit sie 100000 Sonderziehungsrechte je Reisenden übersteigen, wenn er nachweist, daß The air carrier shall not be liable for any damage in accordance with Article 17 (1) to the extent that it exceeds 100000 Special Drawing Rights per passenger if it can prove that:
( a) such damage is not the result of an unlawful act or omission on the part of the air carrier or its persons, whether or not it was caused by negligence; or
( b) such damage is solely the result of an unlawful act or omission by a third party, whether or not it was committed through negligence.
Maximum liability in the event of delay and for baggage and goods
( 1) Für DeltungsSchäden im Sinne des Artikels 19 haftet der Luftfrachtführer bei der Befuhr von Personen nur bis einem Betrag von 4150 Sonderziehungsrechte je Reisenden. The air carrier shall be liable for any delay in the carriage of persons within the meaning of Article 19 only up to an amount of 4150 Special Drawing Rights per passenger.
( 2) Bei der Befuhr von Reisegeluggck haftet der Luftfrachtführer für Zerstörung, Verlust, Beschädigung oder delay nur bis einem Betrag von 1000 Sonderziehungsrechte je Reisenden; diese Beschränkung gilt nicht, wenn der Wanderer bei der Handgabe des aufgegebenen Reisegeluggcks an den Luftfrachtführer das Interesse an der Ablieferung am Destmungsort betragsmäßig angegeben und den verlangten Zuschlag entrichtet hat. In the case of the carriage of luggage, the air carrier shall be liable for destruction, loss, damage or delay not exceeding 1000 Special Drawing Rights per passenger, except where the passenger has indicated, on a fixed date, and paid the requested supplement, the interest in the delivery to the destination of the checked luggage to the air carrier.
In this case, the air carrier shall provide compensation up to the amount of the specified amount, unless it can prove that it is in excess of the passenger <unk> s actual interest in the delivery at the destination.
( 3) Bei der Befuhr von Gütern haftet der Luftfrachtführer für Zerstörung, Verlust, Beschädigung oder delay nur bis einem Betrag von 17 Sonderziehungsrechte für das Kilograms; diese Beschränkung gilt nicht, wenn der Absender bei der Handgabe des Frachtstücks an den Luftfrachtführer das Interesse an der Ablieferung am Destmungsort betragsmäßig angegeben und den verlangten Zuschlag entrichtet hat. In the case of the carriage of goods, the air carrier shall be liable for destruction, loss, damage or delay only up to an amount of 17 Special Drawing Rights for the kilogram; this limitation shall not apply if the sender, at the time of handover of the piece of cargo to the air carrier, has indicated betragsmäßig interest in the delivery to the destination and has paid the requested supplement.
In this case, the air carrier shall provide compensation up to the amount of the specified amount, unless it can prove that it is in excess of the sender <unk> s actual interest in the place of destination.
( 4) Im Fall der Zerstörung, des Verlust, der Beschädigung oder der spätung eines Teiles der Güter oder irgendeines darin enthaltenen gegenstands ist für die Feststellung, bis zu welcher Betrag der Luftfrachtführer haftet, nur das Gesamtgewicht der betroffenen Freichtstücke berechgebend. In the event of the destruction, loss, damage or delay of any part of the goods or of any item contained therein, only the total weight of the pieces of freight concerned shall be relevant for the determination of the amount to which the carrier is liable.
However, where the destruction, loss, damage or delay of any part of the goods or of any item contained therein adversely affects the value of other pieces of freight listed in the same air waybill or acknowledgement of receipt or, if not issued, in the other records referred to in Article 4 (2), the total weight of such pieces of freight shall be decisive in determining the amount to which the carrier is liable.
( 5) Die Absätze 1 und 2 finden keine Anwendung, wenn proved wird, daß der Schaden durch eine Handlung oder Unterlassung des Luftfrachtführers oder seiner Menschen verursacht worden ist, die entweder in der Absicht, Schaden herbeizuführen, oder frichtfertig und in dem Bewusstsein begangen wurde, daß probably ein Schaden eintreten wird; im Fall einer Handlung oder Unterlassung der Menschen ist Außerdem nachweisen, daß diese in Ausführung ihrer Verrichtungen gehandelt haben. The provisions of paragraphs 1 and 2 of this Article shall not apply where it is established that the damage has been caused by an act or omission by the air carrier or its people, either with the intention of causing harm, or recklessly and with the awareness that it is likely to cause harm; in the case of an act or omission by the people concerned, it shall also be demonstrated that they have acted in accordance with their instructions.
( 6) Die in Artikel 21 und in diesem Artikel festgesetzten Haftungsbeschränkungen nicht hindern das Gericht, zusätzlich nach seinem Recht einen Betrag zuzusprechen, der ganz oder teilweise den vom Kläger aufgewendeten Gerichtskosten und sonstigen Ausgaben für den Rechtsstreit, einschließlich Zinsen, entspricht. The limitations on liability set out in Article 21 and in this Article shall not prevent the Court from making, in addition, under its own laws, an additional contribution equivalent in whole or in part to the court costs and other expenses incurred by the plaintiff in the dispute, including interest.
This shall not apply if the amount of the damages awarded (9) does not exceed the amount offered by the carrier to the plaintiff in writing, within a period of six months from the date of the event causing the damage, or, if the action has been brought after that period has expired, before its collection, without taking into account the court costs and other expenses of the dispute.
( 1) Die in diesem Übereinkommen angegebenen Beträge von Sonderziehungsrechte beziehen sich auf das vom Internationalen Währung festgelegte Sonderziehungsrecht. The amounts of Special Drawing Rights specified in this Agreement relate to the Special Drawing Right established by the International Monetary Fund.
Such amounts shall be converted into local currencies in the event of judicial proceedings based on the value of such currencies in the Special Drawing Rights at the time of the decision.
The value, expressed in Special Drawing Rights, of the national currency of a Contracting State that is a member of the International Monetary Fund shall be calculated in accordance with the assessment method applied by the International Monetary Fund, which shall apply to its operations and transactions at the time of the decision.
The value, expressed in Special Drawing Rights, of the national currency of a Contracting State which is not a member of the International Monetary Fund shall be calculated in a manner determined by that State.
( 2) Dessen ungeachtet können Staaten, die nicht Mitglieder des Internationalen Währung sind und deren Recht die Anwendung des Absatzes 1 nicht zulst, bei der Ratifikation oder dem Beitritt oder jederzeit danach erklären, daß die Haftung des Luftfrachtführer in gerichtlichen Verfahren in ihrem Hoheitsgebiet im Fall des Artikels 21 auf 1500000 Rechnungseinheiten je Reisenden Limited ist, im Fall des Artikels 22 Absatz 1 auf 62500 Rechnungseinheiten je Reisenden, im Fall des Artikels 22 Absatz 2 auf 15000 Rechnungseinheiten je Reisenden und im Fall des Artikels 22 Absatz 3 auf 250 Rechnungseinheiten für das Kilogramm. Notwithstanding this, States which are not members of the International Monetary Fund and whose laws do not permit the application of paragraph 1 may, at ratification or accession, or at any time thereafter, declare that the air carrier <unk> s liability in judicial proceedings in their territory
One unit of account corresponds to 65 1 / 2 milligrams of gold of 900 / 1000 purity.
These amounts may be converted into a rounded amount of the local currency.
Amounts shall be converted into the local currency in accordance with the laws of the State concerned.
( 3) Die Berechnung nach Absatz 1 Satz 4 und die Umrechnung nach Absatz 2 ist so vorzunehmen, daß soweit wie möglich die Beträge in den Artikeln 21 und 22 dem selben Realwert in der LandesWährung des Vertragsstaats entsprechen, wie er sich aus der Anwendung des Absatzes 1 Satz 1 bis 3 ergeben würde. The calculation in accordance with paragraph 1, sentence 4, and the conversion in accordance with paragraph 2 shall be carried out in such a way as to ensure that, as far as possible, the amounts referred to in Articles 21 and 22 of this Article correspond to the same real value in the national currency of the Contracting State as would result from the application of paragraph 1, sentences 1 to 3.
The Contracting States shall, at the time of deposit of the instrument of ratification, acceptance, approval or accession, inform the depositary of the method of calculation referred to in paragraph 1 of this Article or the result of the conversion referred to in paragraph 2 of this Article and of any amendment thereto.
( 1) Unbeschadet des Artikels 25 und vorbehaltlich<unk> 11) des Absatzes 2 werden die Hafungshöchstbeträge nach den Artikeln 21, 22 und 23 vom Depositar<unk> 12) nach jeweils fünf Jahren überprüft; die erste Überprüfung ist am Ende des 5. Jahres vorzunehmen, das nach das Inkrafttreten dieses Übereinkommens folgt, oder, wenn das Übereinkommen nicht innerhalb von fünf Jahren ab dem Tag, an es ersten zur Unterlag aufliegt, in Kraft tritt, innerhalb des ersten Jahres nach Inkrafttreten; der Überprüfung ist ein Inflationsfaktor zugrunde zu legen, der der der der kumulierten Inflationsrate seit der früheren Überprüfung oder, beim ersten Mal, seit Inkrafttreten des Übereinkommens entspricht. Notwithstanding the provisions of Article 25 and 11) of paragraph 2, the maximum amounts of liability referred to in Articles 21, 22 and 23
The inflation rate to be used in determining the inflation factor shall be the weighted average of the annual growth or decline rates of the consumer price indices of the States whose currencies constitute the Special Drawing Right referred to in Article 23 (1).
( 2) Ergibt die in Absatz 1 genannte Überprüfung, daß der Inflationsfaktor 10 Prozent<unk> 13) übersteigt, so notifiziert der Depositar<unk> 14) den Vertragsstaaten die angeebenen Hafungshöchstbeträge. Where the verification referred to in paragraph 1 of this Article indicates that the inflationary factor exceeds 10% (13), the depositary shall notify the States Parties of the adjusted maximum amounts of liability.
Each adaptation shall enter into force six months after its notification to the States Parties.
If, within three months of notification to States Parties, a majority of States Parties notifies them of their rejection, the adjustment shall not enter into force, in which case the depositary shall submit the matter to a meeting of States Parties.
The depositary (16) shall immediately notify all States Parties of the entry into force of any adjustment.
( 3) Unbeschadet des Absatzes 1 ist das in Absatz 2 genannte Verfahren auf Verlangen eines Drittels der Vertragsstaaten jederzeit anzuwenden, wenn der in Absatz 1 genannte Inflationsfaktor seit der vorherige Überprüfung oder, wenn eine solche nicht erfolgt ist, seit Inkrafttreten des Übereinkommens, 30 Prozent<unk> 17) überstieg hat. Without prejudice to paragraph 1, the procedure referred to in paragraph 2 shall be applied at any time at the request of one third of the States Parties if the inflation factor referred to in paragraph 1 has exceeded the previous review or, if such review has not taken place, since the entry into force of the Convention, 30%.
Further reviews in accordance with the procedure described in paragraph 1 of this Article shall be carried out after five years, for the first time at the end of the fifth year following a review under this paragraph.
An air carrier may, under the Contract of Carriage, submit to liability ceilings greater than those provided for in this Convention or waive liability ceilings.
Any provision of the Contract of Carriage intended to exclude the liability of the carrier or to reduce the maximum liability laid down in this Agreement shall be null and void and shall not invalidate the whole of the Agreement, which shall nonetheless be subject to this Agreement.
Nothing in this Agreement shall preclude the air carrier from refusing to enter into a contract of carriage, from waiving any objection at its disposal under this Agreement, or from laying down contractual conditions which do not conflict with this Agreement.
If air accidents result in the death or bodily injury of a passenger, the air carrier, if required to do so under national law, shall promptly make advance payments to persons entitled to compensation for damages (18) for the satisfaction of their immediate economic needs.
Such advance payments shall not constitute an acknowledgement of liability and may be offset against any subsequent performance of damages <unk> 19) by the carrier.
For the carriage of passengers, luggage and goods, any claim for damages <unk> 20), on whatever legal ground it may be based, be it this Agreement, a contract, an unlawful act or any other legal ground, may be asserted only under the conditions and subject to the restrictions provided for in this Agreement, without prejudice to the question of which persons are entitled to sue and the rights to which they are entitled.
Any such action shall preclude any form of punitive, aggravated or other non-compensatory damages.
( 1) Wird einer der Leute des Luftfrachtführers wegen eines Schadens in Anspruch genommen, der unter dieses Übereinkommen fällt, so kann er sich auf die Haftungsbedingsetzungen und -beschränkungen berufen, die nach diesem Übereinkommen für den Luftfrachtführer gelten, sofern er nachweist, daß er in Ausführung seiner Verrichtungen gehandelt hat. If any of the persons in the Air Carrier is claimed for damage covered by this Agreement, he may invoke the liability requirements and limitations applicable to the Air Carrier under this Agreement, provided that he demonstrates that he has acted in accordance with the provisions of this Agreement.
( 2) Der Betrag, der in diesem Fall von dem Luftfrachtführer und seinen Menschen als Ersatz insgesamt zu leisten ist, darf die genannten Haftungsgrenzen nicht übersteigen. The sum to be paid in total in this case by the air carrier and its persons as a substitute shall not exceed the limits of liability referred to above.
( 3) Die Absätze 1 und 2 finden, außer bei der Befuhr von Gütern, keine Anwendung, wenn festgestellt wird, daß der Schaden durch eine Handlung oder Unterlassung der Menschen des Luftfrachtführers verursacht worden ist, die entweder in der Absicht, Schaden herbeizuführen, oder frichtfertig und in dem Bewusstsein begangen wurde, daß wahrscheinlich ein Schaden eintreten wird. The provisions of paragraphs 1 and 2 of this Article shall not apply, except in the case of the carriage of goods, where it is established that the damage has been caused by an act or omission by the persons of the air carrier, either with the intention of causing harm or recklessly and in the knowledge that such damage is likely to occur.
( 1) Nimmt der Empfänger aufgegebenes Reisegeluggck oder Güter vorbehaltlos an, so begründet dies die widerlegbare Vermutung, daß sie unbeschädigt und entsprechend dem Beförderungsschein oder den anderen Aufzeichnungen im Sinne des Artikels 3 Absatz 2 und Artikels 4 Absatz 2 abgegeliefert worden sind. If the consignee accepts checked baggage or goods without reservation, this shall give rise to the refutable presumption that they have been delivered undamaged and in accordance with the terms of Article 3 (2) and Article 4 (2).
( 2) Im Fall einer Beschädigung muss der Empfänger unverzüglich nach Entdeckung des Schadens, bei aufgegebenem ReisegeLuck Anyway binnen sieben und bei Gütern binnen vierzehn Tage nach der Annahme, dem Luftfrachtführer Anzeige erstatten. In the event of damage, the consignee shall notify the carrier immediately after the damage has been discovered, within seven days in the case of checked luggage and fourteen days in the case of goods after acceptance.
In the event of a delay, notification shall be made within twenty one days after the baggage or goods have been placed at the disposal of the addressee.
( 3) Jede Beanstandung Must be declared in writing and delivered or sent within the time limit provided for.
( 4) Wird die Anzeigefrist versäumt, so ist jede Klage gegen den Luftfrachtführer ausgeschlossen, es sei sei, daß dieser fraustig gehandelt hat. If the period of notice is missed, any claim against the air carrier shall be excluded unless the latter has acted fraudulently.
If the person liable for such damages dies (23), the claim for such damages (24) under this Agreement may be made against his successors in title.
( 1) Die Klage auf Schadensatz<unk> 25) muss im Hoheitsgebiet eines der Vertragsstaaten erhoben werden, und zwar nach Wahl des Klägers entweder bei dem Gericht des Ort, an dem sich der Wohnsitz des Luftfrachtführers, seine Hauptniederlassung oder seine Geschäftsstelle befindet, durch die der Vertrag geschlossen worden ist, oder bei dem Gericht des Bestimmungsorts. The claim for damages (25) must be brought in the territory of one of the States Parties, at the plaintiff <unk> s discretion, either before the court of the place of residence of the air carrier, its headquarters or its office through which the contract has been concluded, or before the court of destination.
( 2) Die Klage auf Ersatz des Schadens, der durch Tod oder Körperverletzung eines Reisenden entstanden ist, kann bei einem der in Absatz 1 genannten Gerichte oder im Hoheitsgebiet eines Vertragsstaats erhoben werden, in dem der Traveller im Zeitpunkt des Unfalls seinen ständigen Wohnsitz hatten und in das oder aus dem der Luftfrachtführer Reisende im Luftverkehr gewerbsmäßig befördert, und zwar entweder mit seinen eigenen Luftfahrzeugen oder aufgrund einer Geschäftsftlichen Vereinbarung mit Luftfahrzeugen eines anderen Luftfrachtführers, und in dem der Luftfrachtführer sein Gewerbe von Geschäftsräumen aus betreibt, deren tenant oder Besitz er selbst oder ein anderer Luftfrachtführer ist, mit dem er eine Geschäftsftliche Vereinbarung geschlossen hat. The claim for compensation of damage caused by the death or bodily injury of a passenger may be brought before one of the courts referred to in paragraph 1 of this Article or in the territory of a Contracting
( 3) Im Sinne des Absatzes 2 bedeutet Within the meaning of paragraph 2:
( a) a commercial arrangement establishing a contract between carriers for the provision of joint air transport services to passengers other than commercial agents <unk> 26);
( b) permanent residence and habitual residence of the Traveller at the time of the accident.
The nationality of the traveller is not decisive in this respect.
( 4) Das Verfahren richten sich nach dem Recht des angerufenen Gerichts. The procedure shall be governed by the law of the court being called.
( 1) Die Parteien des Vertrags über die Befuhr von Gütern können nach Maßgabe dieses Artikels vereinbaren, daß Streitigkeiten über die Haftung des Luftfrachtführers nach diesem Übereinkommen in einem Schiedsverfahren beigelegt werden. The Parties to the Treaty on the carriage of goods may agree, in accordance with the provisions of this Article, that disputes concerning the air carrier <unk> s liability under this Agreement shall be settled in arbitration.
( 2) Das Schiedsverfahren wird nach Wahl des Anspruchstellers an einem der in Artikel 33 genannten Gerichtsstände durchgeführt. Arbitration shall be conducted at the discretion of the claimant at one of the courts referred to in Article 33.
( 3) Der Schiedsrichter oder das Schiedsgericht hat dieses Übereinkommen anzuwenden. The arbitrator or tribunal shall apply this Convention.
( 4) Die Absätze 2 und 3 gelten als Bestandteil jeder Schiedsklausel oder -vereinbarung; abweichende Bestimmungen sind nichtig. Paragraphs 2 and 3 of this Article shall form an integral part of any arbitration clause or agreement and any deviating provisions shall be null and void.
( 1) Die Klage auf Schadensatz<unk> 27) kann nur binnen einer Ausschlußfrist von zwei Jahren erhoben werden; die Frist beginnt mit dem Tag, an dem das Luftfahrzeug am Bestimmungsort gekommen ist oder an dem es Should have ankommen oder an dem die Beförderung abgebrochen worden ist. The claim for damages (27) may only be brought within a period of exclusion of two years commencing on the date on which the aircraft arrived at its destination or on which it should have arrived or on which the carriage has been cancelled.
( 2) Die Berechnung der Frist richten sich nach dem Recht des angerufenen Gerichts. The time limit shall be calculated in accordance with the law of the court being called.
( 1) Jeder Luftfrachtführer, der Reisende, Reisegeluggck oder Güter annimmt, ist bei Beförderungen im Sinne des Artikels 1 Absatz 3, die nacheinander durch mehrere Luftfrachtführer ausgeführt werden, den Vorschriften dieses Übereinkommens unterworfen; er gilt für den Teil der Beförderung, der unter seiner Leitung ausführt wird, als Partei des Beförderungsvertrags. Any air carrier that accepts passengers, luggage or goods shall be subject to the provisions of this Agreement for carriage within the meaning of Article 1 (3), carried out in succession by several air carriers, and shall be considered as a Party to the contract of carriage.
( 2) Bei einer solchen Beförderung kann der Wanderer oder die sonst anspruchsberechtigt Person nur den Luftfrachtführer in Anspruch nehmen, der die Beförderung ausgeführt hat, in deren Verlauf der Unfall oder die Deltung eingetreten ist, es sei sei, daß der erste Luftfrachtführer durch ausdrückliche Vereinbarung die Haftung für die ganze Reise übernommen hat. In the event of such carriage, the passenger or the person otherwise entitled to claim may only claim the air carrier which carried out the carriage in which the accident or delay occurred, unless the first air carrier has assumed liability for the whole journey by express agreement.
( 3) Bei ReisegeLuck oder Gütern kann der Wanderer oder der Absender den ersten, der Wanderer oder der Empfänger, der die Auslieferung verlangen kann, den letzten, und jeder von ihnen denjenigen Luftfrachtführer in Anspruch nehmen, der die Beförderung ausführt hat, in deren Verlauf die Zerstörung, der Verlust oder die Beschädigung erfolgt oder die Delayed eingetreten ist. In the case of luggage or goods, the traveller or the sender may claim the first, the traveller or the consignee who may request the delivery, the last and any of them may claim the air carrier which carried out the carriage during which the destruction, loss or damage or delay has occurred.
Such carriers shall be jointly and severally liable to the traveller, sender or consignee.
This Agreement shall not affect the question of whether the person liable for damages under its provisions (<unk> 28) may have recourse against another person.
( 1) Bei gemischter Beförderung, die Teil durch Luftfahrzeuge, Teil durch andere Verkehrsmittel ausführt wird, gilt dieses Übereinkommen vorbehaltlich<unk> 29) des Artikels 18 Absatz 4 nur für die Luftbeförderung im Sinne des Artikels 1. In the case of mixed transport carried out in part by aircraft and in part by other means of transport, this Agreement shall apply, subject to the conditions laid down in Article 18 (4), only to air transport as defined in Article 1.
( 2) Bei gemischter Beförderung sind die Parteien durch dieses Übereinkommen nicht gehindert, Bedingungen für die Beförderung durch andere Verkehrsmittel in den Luftbeförderungsvertrag aufzunehmen, sofern hinsichtlich der Luftbeförderung dieses Übereinkommen beachtet wird. In the case of mixed transport, the Parties shall not be prevented by this Agreement from including conditions for transport by other means of transport in the Agreement, provided that this Agreement is observed with respect to air transport.
AIR PROVISION BY ANY OTHER THAN THE CONTRACTED AIR PROVIDER
This Chapter shall apply when a person (hereinafter referred to as <unk> the Contractual Air Carrier <unk>) has concluded a Contract of Carriage subject to this Agreement with a traveller or sender or a person acting on behalf of the traveller or sender and another person (hereinafter referred to as <unk> the executing Air Carrier <unk>) is entitled, pursuant to an agreement with the Contractual Air Carrier, to perform the carriage in whole or in part, without, in respect of this Part, being a successive carriage within the meaning of this Agreement.
The entitlement shall be assumed until such time as evidence to the contrary is provided.
If an exporting air carrier carries out in whole or in part a carriage governed by the Contract of Carriage referred to in Article 39 of this Agreement, both the contractual air carrier and the exporting air carrier shall be subject, unless otherwise provided in this Chapter, to the provisions of this Agreement, the former for all carriage provided for in the Treaty, the latter only for the carriage which it carries out.
( 1) Die Handlungen und Unterlassungen des ausführenden Luftfrachtführers und seiner Menschen, soweit diese in Ausführung ihrer Verrichtungen handeln, gelten bezüglich der von dem ausführenden Luftfrachtführer ausgeführten Beförderung auch als solche des Vertragsglichen Luftfrachtführers. The acts and omissions of the exporting air carrier and its persons, to the extent that they are acting in the execution of their directions, shall also be considered as such of the contractual air carrier with respect to the carriage carried out by the exporting air carrier.
( 2) Die Handlungen und Unterlassungen des vertraglichen Luftfrachtführers und seiner Menschen, soweit diese in Ausführung ihrer Verrichtungen handeln, gelten bezüglich der von dem ausführenden Luftfrachtführer ausgeführten Beförderung auch als solche des ausführenden Luftfrachtführers. The actions and omissions of the contractual air carrier and its persons, to the extent that they are acting in the execution of their directions, shall also be considered as such of the exporting air carrier with respect to the carriage carried out by the exporting air carrier.
However, such acts or omissions shall not make the actual carrier liable beyond the amounts referred to in Articles 21, 22, 23 and 24.
A special arrangement whereby the contractual air carrier shall enter into obligations not imposed by this Agreement, or waiver of rights or objections under this Agreement, or a declaration of interest in the delivery in accordance with Article 22, shall be effective in respect of the exporting air carrier only with the latter <unk> s consent.
Complaints or instructions to be made to the carrier pursuant to this Agreement shall take effect, whether addressed to the contractual carrier or to the exporting carrier.
However, the instructions under Article 12 shall only take effect if they are addressed to the contractual carrier.
In so far as the exporting air carrier has carried out the carriage, both his and the persons of the contractual air carrier, provided that they demonstrate that they have acted in accordance with their obligations, may invoke the conditions and limitations of liability applicable under this Agreement to the air carrier to which they belong, except where evidence is furnished that they have acted in a manner which precludes recourse to the limitations of liability under this Agreement.
In so far as the exporting air carrier has carried out the carriage, the amount to be paid by that air carrier, the contractual air carrier and their agents, provided that they have acted in accordance with their obligations, as compensation for damages (31), shall not exceed the maximum amount which may be claimed under this Agreement by the contractual air carrier or the exporting air carrier as compensation (32); however, none of the abovementioned persons shall be liable beyond the maximum amount applicable to them.
In so far as the executing air carrier has carried out the carriage, action for damages (33) may be brought, at the applicant <unk> s discretion, against that air carrier, the contractual air carrier or both, jointly or separately.
Where the action is brought only against one of those carriers, the latter shall have the right to require the other carrier to participate in the dispute and the effects and proceedings shall be governed by the law of the court before it.
An action for damages (34) under Article 45 may be brought only in the territory of one of the Contracting States, at the discretion of the plaintiff, either before one of the courts before which an action may be brought against the contractual carrier in accordance with Article 33, or before the court of the place of residence or principal place of business of the exporting carrier.
Any contractual provision which shall exclude the liability of the contractual or exporting carrier under this Chapter, or which shall reduce the maximum authoritative amount of liability, shall be null and void and shall not result in the annulment of the entire Agreement, which shall continue to be governed by the provisions of this Chapter.
This Chapter, with the exception of Article 45, shall not affect the rights and obligations of carriers among themselves, including rights of recourse or damages (35).
All provisions of the Contract of Carriage and any special arrangements made prior to the occurrence of the damage with which the Parties derogate from this Convention by determining the law to be applied or by amending the rules on jurisdiction shall be null and void.
States Parties shall oblige their air carriers to insure themselves adequately to meet their liability under this Convention.
The Contracting State to which the carriage is carried out by an air carrier may require proof of adequate insurance coverage to cover liability under this Convention.
The provisions of Articles 3 to 5, 7 and 8 on instruments of carriage shall not apply to carriage carried out in exceptional circumstances and not within the framework of ordinary air transport.
The term <unk> days <unk> for the purposes of this Convention means calendar days, not working days.
( 1) Dieses Übereinkommen liegt am 28. Mai 1999 in Montreal für die Staaten zur Unterzeichnung auf, die an der Internationalen Konferenz über Luftrecht vom 10. bis zum 28. Mai 1999 in Montreal teilgenommen haben. This Convention shall be open for signature in Montreal on 28 May 1999 by those States which have participated in the International Conference on Air Treaty held in Montreal from 10 to 28 May 1999.
After 28 May 1999, the Convention shall be open for signature by all States at the headquarters of the International Civil Aviation Organisation in Montreal until it enters into force in accordance with paragraph 6 of this Article.
( 2) Dieses Übereinkommen liegt ebenfalls für Organisationen der regionalen Wirtschaftsintegration zur Unterzeichnung auf. This Agreement shall also be open for signature by regional economic integration organisations.
For the purposes of this Agreement, a <unk> regional economic integration organisation <unk> means an organisation constituted by sovereign States of a particular region which is competent for certain items governed by this Agreement and has the due authority to sign and ratify, accept, approve or accede to this Agreement.
A reference to a <unk> State Party <unk> or <unk> Contracting States <unk> in this Agreement, with the exception of Article 1 (2), Article 3 (1) (b), Article 5 (b), Articles 23, 33 and 46 and Article 57 (b), shall apply equally to a regional economic integration organisation.
The references in Article 24 to <unk> a majority of States Parties <unk> and <unk> a third of States Parties <unk> shall not apply to any regional economic integration organisation.
( 3) Dieses Übereinkommen bedarf der Ratifikation durch die Staaten und Organisationen der regionalen Wirtschaftsintegration, die es unterzeichnet haben. This Agreement shall be subject to ratification by the States and regional economic integration organisations which have signed it.
( 4) Staaten oder Organisationen der regionalen Wirtschaftsintegration, die dieses Übereinkommen nicht unterzeichnen, können es jederzeit annehmen oder genehmigen oder ihm beitreten. States or regional economic integration organisations which do not sign this Agreement may at any time accept or approve it or accede to it.
( 5) Die Ratifikations-, Annahme-, Genehmigungs- oder Beitrittsurkunden werden bei der Internationalen Zivilluftfahrt-Organisation hinterlegt; diese wird hiermit zum Depositar<unk> 36) bestimmt. Instruments of ratification, acceptance, approval or accession shall be deposited with the International Civil Aviation Organization, which shall hereby become depositary (36).
( 6) Dieses Übereinkommen tritt am sechzigsten Tag nach Hinterlegung der dreißigsten Ratifikations-, Annahme-, Genehmigungs- oder Beitrittsurkunde beim Depositar<unk> 37) zwischen den Staaten in Kraft, die eine solche Urkunde hinterlegt haben. This Convention shall enter into force on the sixtieth day following the deposit of the thirtieth instrument of ratification, acceptance, approval or accession with the depositary (37) between the States which have deposited such an instrument.
An instrument deposited by a regional economic integration organization shall not be counted to that extent.
( 7) Für andere Staaten und für andere Organisationen der regionalen Wirtschaftsintegration tritt dieses Übereinkommen sechzig Tage nach Hinterlegung der Ratifikations-, Annahme-, Genehmigungs- oder Beitrittsurkunde in Kraft. For other States and for other regional economic integration organisations, this Agreement shall enter into force sixty days after the date of deposit of the instrument of ratification, acceptance, approval or accession.
( 8) Der Depositar<unk> 38) notifiziert allen Unterzeichnern und Vertragsstaaten umgehend
( a) any signature of this Convention and the date thereof;
( b) any deposit of an instrument of ratification, acceptance, approval or accession and the date of such deposit;
( c) the date of entry into force of this Agreement;
( d) the date on which an adjustment of the maximum liability amounts made under this Convention enters into force;
( e) Any denunciation under Article 54.
( 1) Jeder Vertragsstaat kann dieses Übereinkommen durch eine an den Depositar<unk> 39) gerichtete schriftliche Notifikation kündigen. Any State Party may terminate this Agreement by notifying the depositary in writing.
( 2) Die Kündigung wird einhundertachtzig Tage nach Eingang der Notifikation beim Depositar<unk> 40) wirksam. Termination shall become effective one hundred and eighty days after the date of receipt of the notification by the depositary.
Relationship with other agreements related to the Warsaw Agreement
This Agreement shall take precedence over all the provisions applicable to international carriage by air.
1. between States Parties to this Agreement on the basis of the fact that these States are jointly Parties to the following Agreements:
( a) Agreement for the Unification of Rules relating to International Carriage by Air, signed in Warsaw on 12 October 1929 (hereinafter referred to as the <unk> Warsaw Agreement <unk>);
( b) the Protocol amending the Agreement on the Unification of Rules for International Carriage by Air, signed at Warsaw on 12 October 1929 and adopted at The Hague on 28 September 1955 (hereinafter referred to as the <unk> Hague Protocol <unk>);
( c) Additional Agreement to the Warsaw Convention for the Unification of Rules relating to International Carriage by Air carried out by a Carrier other than the Contracting Carrier, signed in Guadalajara on 18 September 1961 (hereinafter referred to as the <unk> Guadalajara Agreement <unk>);
( d) Protocol amending the Agreement on the Unification of Rules for International Carriage by Air, signed in Warsaw on 12 October 1929, as amended by the Hague Protocol of 28 September 1955, signed in Guatemala City on 8 March 1971 (hereinafter referred to as the <unk> Protocol of Guatemala City <unk>);
( e) Additional Protocols 1 to 3 and the Montreal Protocol 4 amending the Warsaw Convention as amended by the Hague Protocol or the Warsaw Convention as amended by the Hague Protocol and the Guatemalan City Protocol, signed in Montreal on 25 September 1975 (hereinafter referred to as the <unk> Montreal Protocols <unk>), or
2. within the territory of an individual State Party to this Agreement by virtue of the fact that that State is party to one or more of the agreements referred to in subparagraphs (a) to (e) of paragraph 1.
( 1) Umfasst ein Staat zwei oder mehr Gebietseinheiten, in denen auf die durch dieses Übereinkommen geregelten Gegenstände unterschiedliche Rechtsordnungen angewendet werden, so kann er bei der Unterzeichnung, der Ratifikation, der Annahme, der Genehmigung oder dem Beitritt erklären, daß dieses Übereinkommen sich auf alle seine Gebietseinheiten oder nur auf eine oder mehrere der selben erstreckt; er kann seine Erklärung jederzeit durch eine neue Erklärung ersetzt. A State comprising two or more territorial units in which different legal systems are applied to items governed by this Agreement may, at the time of signature, ratification, acceptance, approval or accession, declare that this Agreement extends to all its territorial units or to only one or more of them; it may, at any time, replace its declaration by a new declaration.
( 2) Die Erklärungen werden dem Depositar<unk> 42) notifiziert und müssen ausdrücklich angeben, auf welche Gebietseinheiten sich das Übereinkommen erstreckt. Statements shall be notified to the depositary (42) and shall explicitly specify to which territorial units the Convention extends.
( 3) Hinsichtlich eines Vertragsstaats, der eine solche Erklärung abgegeben hat, With respect to any State Party which has made such a declaration:
( a) any reference to the <unk> national currency <unk> in Article 23 shall be construed as referring to the currency of the relevant territorial unit of that State; and
( b) the reference to <unk> national law <unk> in Article 28 shall be understood as referring to the law of the relevant territorial unit of that State.
No reservations may be made with respect to this Agreement, except that a State Party may at any time, by notification addressed to the depositary, declare that this Agreement does not apply to:
( a) international carriage by air, carried out and carried out directly by that State Party for non-commercial purposes with a view to its functions and obligations as a sovereign State;
( b) the carriage of persons, goods and luggage for its military services by aircraft registered or rented by it in that Contracting State, reserved exclusively for such services.
between the European Union and the former Yugoslav Republic of Macedonia on the activities of the European Union Monitoring Mission (EUMM) in the former Yugoslav Republic of Macedonia
On the other hand,
hereinafter referred to as <unk> Participating Parties
- the European Community and its Member States have offered to establish a European Community Monitoring Mission (ECMM) in the former Yugoslav Republic of Macedonia, and that the host Party accepted this offer on a provisional basis on 24 March 1998,
- have been observers of the European Community / European Union in the former Yugoslav Republic of Macedonia since 1998,
- the Council of the European Union, on 22 December 2000, adopted Joint Action 2000 / 811 / CFSP on the European Union Monitoring Mission converting the ECMM into the EUMM, as an instrument of the European Union <unk> s Common Foreign and Security Policy (CFSP) which, building on previous initiatives, should contribute to formulating an effective European Union policy for the Western Balkans,
- a Stabilisation and Association Agreement between the former Yugoslav Republic of Macedonia and the European Communities and their Member States was concluded in Luxembourg on 9 April 2001,
- recognising the independence, sovereignty and territorial integrity of the former Yugoslav Republic of Macedonia and the strong desire of the European Union to contribute to further strengthening of peace and stability in the region,
( 1) Die Überwachungsmission der Europäischen Union, nachstehend <unk> EUMM <unk> genannt, die ursprünglich in der Region als Überwachungsmission der Europäischen Gemeinschaft (ECMM) errichtet wurde, hat ihr Hauptquartier derzeit in Sarajevo und wird ein Missionsbüro in Skopje sowie auf Entscheidung des Missionsleiters nach Hearing und Zustimmung der Aufnahmepartei gegebenenfalls weitere Büro in der ehemaligen jugoslawischen Republik Mazedonien einrichten, um dazu zutzutzutragen, eine wirksame Politik der Europäischen Union für den Westlichen Balkan zu formulieren. The European Union Monitoring Mission, hereinafter referred to as the EUMM, which was originally established in the region as a European Community Monitoring Mission (ECMM), shall have its headquarters in Sarajevo and shall establish a mission office in Skopje and, by decision of the Head of Mission after consultation and agreement of the host party, further offices in the former
( a) monitor political developments and developments in the security situation within their competence;
( b) pay particular attention to border control, issues affecting different ethnic groups and the return of refugees;
( c) submit analytical reports in accordance with the tasks assigned to it;
( d) contribute to the early warning of the Council and to confidence building within the framework of the stabilisation policies pursued by the European Union in the region.
( e) keep the host Party regularly informed of the activities of the EUMM, including, where the assigned tasks so provide, humanitarian matters.
( 2) Die Aufnahmepartei erteilt der EUMM alle Informationen und leistet jede Art von Zusammenarbeit, die zur Erreichung der Ziele der EUMM erforderlich sind. The host Party shall provide the EUMM with all information and shall cooperate in any manner necessary to achieve the objectives of the EUMM.
The host party may appoint a liaison officer from the respective ministries to the EUMM.
( 1) Die Aufnahmepartei ergreift alle erforderlichen Maßnahmen für den Schutz und die Sicherheit der EUMM und ihrer Mitglieder. The host Party shall take all necessary measures for the protection and security of the EUMM and its members.
All relevant arrangements proposed by the host Party shall be agreed with the Head of Mission before they are implemented.
( 2) Zur Durchführung ihrer Tätigkeit genießen die EUMM und ihr Personal unter Einbeziehung ihrer Transportmittel und Ausrüstungen die Freiheit, die zur Erfuellung des Auftrags der Mission erforderlich ist. In order to carry out their activities, the EUMM and its staff shall enjoy the freedom of movement required for the purpose of carrying out the mission <unk> s mission, including their means of transport and equipment.
( 3) Das Personal der EUMM kann bei seiner Tätigkeit von einem Dolmetscher und, auf Anforderung der EUMM, von einem von der Aufnahmespartei benannten Begleitoffizier begleitoffizier escort werden. The staff of the EUMM may be accompanied in their activities by an interpreter and, at the request of the EUMM, by an escort officer designated by the host party.
( 4) Die EUMM kann auf ihrem Missionsbüro in Skopje sowie an anderen Orten, über die der Missionsleiter befindet, die Flagge der Europäischen Union hoist. The EUMM may fly the flag of the European Union at its mission office in Skopje and at other locations over which the Head of Mission is located.
( 5) Fahrzeuge und andere Transportmittel der EUMM tragen ein Erkennungszeichen der Mission, über das die zuständigen Behörden unterrichtet werden. EUMM vehicles and other means of transport shall bear a mission identification badge which shall be communicated to the competent authorities.
( 1) Der Missionsleiter der EUMM wurde vom Rat der Europäischen Union ernannt. The head of mission of the EUMM shall be appointed by the Council of the European Union.
Future Heads of Mission shall also be so appointed.
( 2) Sonstiges EUMM -Personal shall be seconded by the Member States of the European Union.
Personnel shall be allocated to specific uses by the Head of Mission under the supervision of the Secretary-General / High Representative.
Norway and Slovakia, which participate in the EUMM at the time of this Agreement, may also designate EUMM staff, who shall then be seconding parties, as shall the European Union and its Member States.
( 3) Das auswärtige Personal der EUMM trägt die Bezeichnung <unk> Beobachter <unk>. The foreign staff of the EUMM shall bear the designation <unk> Observer <unk>.
( 4) Die Regierungen der Versandendeparteien benennen Beobachter für die EUMM. The governments of the sending parties shall designate observers for the EUMM.
( 5) Der Missionsleiter bestimmt nach Hearing und Zustimmung der Aufnahmespartei die Anzahl der Beobachter im Rahmen dieses Abkommens. The Head of Mission shall, after consultation and approval by the host party, determine the number of observers under this Agreement.
( 6) Die Beobachter unterlassen alle Handlungen oder Tätigkeiten, die mit der Unparteilichkeit ihrer Aufgaben unvereinbar sind; unbeschadet der Bestimmungen des Artikels VIII beachten sie die Rechtsvorschriften des Aufnahmeestaats. The observers shall refrain from any action or activity which is incompatible with the impartiality of their duties, without prejudice to the provisions of Article VIII, and shall observe the laws of the host State.
( 7) Die EUMM kann auf die Unterstützung durch Verwaltungs- und technisches Personal der Entsendeparteien fallgreifen. The EUMM may call upon the assistance of the administrative and technical staff of the posting parties.
The members of the administrative or technical staff of the EUMM shall enjoy, in accordance with the Vienna Convention on Diplomatic Relations, the same status as the administrative and technical staff of the posting parties in embassies.
( 8) Die EUMM kann vor Ort das erfordertigte Hilfspersonal eingestellt. The EUMM may appoint on site the auxiliary staff required.
At the request of the Head of Mission, the host Party shall facilitate the recruitment by the EUMM of qualified local staff.
The auxiliary staff of the EUMM shall enjoy the same status as the local staff in embassies, in accordance with the Vienna Convention on Diplomatic Relations.
( 1) Die Beobachter dürfen keine Waffen tragen. The observers shall not carry weapons.
( 2) Die Beobachter tragen weiß Zivilkleidung mit einem EUMM-Erkennungszeichen. The observers shall wear white civilian clothing bearing an EUMM identification mark.
( 1) Die EUMM in der ehemaligen jugoslawischen Republik Mazedonien führt ihre Tätigkeit unter der Verantwortung des Missionsleiter aus. The EUMM in the former Yugoslav Republic of Macedonia shall carry out its activities under the responsibility of the Head of Mission.
( 2) Der Missionsleiter bericht dem Rat der Europäischen Union durch den Generalsekretär/ Hohen Vertreter regelmäßig über die Tätigkeit und die Erkenntnisse der EUMM. The Head of Mission shall report regularly to the Council of the European Union, through the Secretary-General / High Representative, on the activities and findings of the EUMM.
( 3) Im Rahmen des Mandats gemäß Artikel I Absatz 1 werden die Aufgaben der EUMM vom Generalsekretär/ Hohen Vertreter in enger Zusammenarbeit mit dem Vorsitz und in Einklang mit der vom Rat verabschiedeten Politik für den Westlichen Balkan festgelegt. The functions of the EUMM shall be determined by the Secretary-General / High Representative in close cooperation with the Presidency and in accordance with the policy for the Western Balkans adopted by the Council.
( 4) Der Missionsleiter unterrichtet die Aufnahmepartei regelmäßig über die Tätigkeit der EUMM. The Head of Mission shall regularly inform the host party of the activities of the EUMM.
( 1) Fahrzeuge und andere Transportmittel der EUMM unterliegen keine Zwangszulassung oder -genehmigung; alle Fahrzeuge sind bei Dritten versicherung. Vehicles and other means of transport of the EUMM shall not be subject to compulsory registration or approval; all vehicles shall be insured with third parties.
( 2) Die EUMM kann Straßen, Flugplätze und andere Einrichtungen ohne Zahlung von Gebühren, Maut oder anderen Abgaben benutzt. EUMM may use roads, airports and other facilities without the payment of fees, tolls or other charges.
( 3) Die Aufnahmepartei erleichtert der EUMM den Betrieb ihrer eigenen Fahrzeuge und anderen Transportmittel. The host Party shall facilitate the operation of its own vehicles and other means of transport for the EUMM.
( 1) Das EUMM-Personal hat zum Zwecke der Ausübung seiner Tätigkeit zu den üblichen Kosten Zugang zu angemessenen Telekommunikationseinrichtungen der Aufnahmepartei, auch zum Zwecke der Kommunikation mit diplomatischen oder konsularischen Vertretern der Entsendeparteien. For the purpose of carrying out its activities, the EUMM staff shall have, at the usual cost, access to appropriate telecommunications facilities of the host Party, including for the purpose of communicating with diplomatic or consular representatives of the posting parties.
( 2) Die EUMM hat das Recht auf uneingeschränkte Kommunikation mit eigenen Funkgeräten (einschließlich Satelliten-, Mobil- und Handfunk geräte), Telefonen, Telegrafen, Faxgeräten oder anderen Mitteln. EUMM shall have the right to communicate without restriction by means of its own radios (including satellite, mobile and hand-held radios), telephones, telegraphs, fax machines or other means.
The host Party shall provide, after signature of this Agreement, the frequencies on which radios may be operated.
( 1) Die EUMM erhält den Status einer diplomatischen Mission. The EUMM shall have the status of a diplomatic mission.
( 2) Die Beobachter genießen während ihrer Mission in Einklang mit dem Wiener Übereinkommen über diplomatische Beziehungen die Vorrechte und Immunitäten diplomatischer Bediensteter. The observers shall enjoy, during their mission in accordance with the Vienna Convention on Diplomatic Relations, the privileges and immunities of diplomatic officials.
( 3) Das Missionsbüro in Skopje, andere Büro und alle Transportmittel der EUMM sind unverletzlich. The mission office in Skopje, other offices and all means of transport of the EUMM shall be inviolable.
( 4) Die Vorrechte und Immunitäten nach diesem Artikel stehen den Beobachter während ihrer Mission zu und danach in Bezug auf Handlungen, die sie zuvor im Rahmen ihrer Mission ausgeführt haben. The privileges and immunities provided for in this Article shall apply to the observers during their mission and thereafter in respect of actions previously performed by them under their mission.
( 5) Die Aufnahmepartei erleichtert alle Bewegungsdes Missionsleiter und des Personals der EUMM. The host Party shall facilitate the movements of the Head of Mission and the staff of the EUMM.
The EUMM shall provide the host party with a list of the members of the EUMM and shall inform the host party in advance of the arrival or departure of EUMM staff.
The EUMM staff shall carry the national passport and an identity card of the EUMM.
( 6) Die Aufnahmepartei erkennt das Recht der Entsendeparteien und der EUMM an, zollfrei und ohne sonstige Beschränkungen die von der EUMM benötigten und zu ihrer ausschließlichen und offizielle Verwendung bestimmten Ausrüstungen, Vorräte, Lieferungen und anderen Güter einzuführen. The host Party shall recognise the right of the posting parties and of the EUMM to introduce, duty free and without other restrictions, the equipment, supplies and other goods required by the EUMM and intended for their exclusive and official use.
The receiving Party shall also recognise its right to buy such items in the territory of the receiving Party and to export or otherwise dispose of such imported or purchased equipment, stocks, supplies and other goods.
The host Party shall also recognise the right of the observers to buy and / or import items for personal use duty free and to export such items.
The Government of the former Yugoslav Republic of Macedonia declares its readiness to assist the EUMM, upon request, in the search for suitable office space and accommodation.
The participating Parties shall decide on other provisions concerning privileges and immunities, on practical arrangements, including emergency medical assistance and evacuation, and on requirements for travel documents.
This Agreement shall enter into force upon signature.
Its provisions shall be applied provisionally by the receiving Party of the EUMM from the date of initialling until its entry into force by signature.
The Agreement shall remain in force until one of the participating Parties notifies the other Party, within a period of two months, of its intention to request the cessation of such activities.
Approval of the administrative budget and fixing of contributions
Convention of 2001 on the Statutes of the International Jute Study Group
Recognizing the importance of jute and jute products to the economies of a number of countries,
Considering that close international cooperation in solving problems related to this commodity will promote the economic development of exporting countries and strengthen cooperation between exporting and importing countries,
Considering also that the International Agreements on Jute and Jute Products of 1982 and 1989 have contributed to cooperation between exporting and importing countries and that it is desirable to enhance the effectiveness of such cooperation in the future,
Recalling the need to promote and implement projects and activities that increase the revenue of jute producing developing countries based on jute and thereby contribute to the alleviation of poverty in those countries,
1. Die Internationale Jute-Studiengruppe, hereinafter referred to as <unk> Gruppe <unk>, wird hermit errichtet, um die Bestimmungen dieser Satzung auszuführen und ihre Anwendung zu überwachen. The International Jute Study Group, hereinafter referred to as <unk> Group
As soon as these Statutes enter into force, the Group shall be considered as the successor, legally, administratively, financially and practically, to the International Jute Organization, which was initially established under the International Agreement on Jute and Jute Products of 1982 and continued to exist under the International Agreement on Jute and Jute Products of 1989.
2. Für die Zwecke dieser Statzung For the purposes of this Statute
( a) <unk> jute <unk> means raw jute, kenaf and other related fibres including urea lobata, abutilon avicennae and cephalonema polyandrum;
( b) <unk> jute product
( c) <unk> member
( d) <unk> associated member
( e) <unk> special vote
( f) <unk> simple majority voting
( g) <unk> financial year <unk> means the period from 1 July to 30 June inclusive;
( h) <unk> jute year
( i) <unk> Statute
3. the objectives of the Group shall be to:
( a) to provide Members with an effective framework for international cooperation, consultation and the development of their policies in respect of all aspects relating to the world jute economy;
( b) promote the expansion of international trade in jute and jute products through the conservation of existing and the opening up of new markets, including the introduction of new jute products and the development of new end uses;
( c) to establish a forum for the active participation of the private sector in the development of the jute sector;
( d) address in the jute sector issues of poverty alleviation, employment and human resource development, with particular emphasis on women;
( e) facilitate the improvement of the structural characteristics of the jute sector by enhancing productivity and quality and encouraging the use of new techniques and technologies;
( f) Raise awareness of the benefits of using jute as an environmentally friendly, renewable and biodegradable natural fibre;
( g) improve market information in cooperation with other organizations, including the Food and Agriculture Organization of the United Nations (FAO), with a view to ensuring greater transparency of the international jute market.
4. In pursuit of its objectives, the Group shall perform the following functions:
( a) developing an appropriate strategy for improving the world jute economy, with particular emphasis on the promotion of jute and jute products in general;
( b) consultations and exchanges of information on the international jute economy;
( c) stimulate, encourage, supervise, control and accelerate projects and similar projects aimed at improving the structural conditions of the world jute economy and the overall economic well-being of its employees.
In exceptional cases, the participation of the Group in the implementation of projects shall be approved by the Council on condition that such participation does not impose an additional burden on the Group <unk> s administrative budget;
( d) provide and improve statistical information and market information on jute and jute dependent products in consultation with the Food and Agriculture Organization of the United Nations and other appropriate fora;
( e) conducting studies on various aspects of the world jute economy and related topics;
( f) addressing any problems or difficulties which may arise in the international jute economy.
In carrying out these functions, the Group shall take into account the activities of other relevant international organizations, including the Food and Agriculture Organization of the United Nations (FAO).
5. Mitglieder der Gruppe können alle Staaten sowie die Europäische Gemeinschaft werden, die an der Produktion, am Verbrauch oder am internationalen Handel mit Jute und Jute-Erzeugnissen interessiert sind und, mit Zustimmung des Rates, alle zwischenstaatlichen Organisationen, die für das Aushandeln, den Abschluss und die Anwendung internationaler Übereinkommen, insbesondere von Rohstoffübereinkommen, zuständig sind. Members of the Group may include any State or the European Community interested in the production, consumption or international trade in jute and jute products and, with the consent of the Council, any intergovernmental organisation responsible for the negotiation, conclusion and application of international agreements, in particular those relating to raw materials.
6. assoziierte Mitglieder der Gruppe können mit Zustimmung des Rates solche Organisationen und Rechtsträger werden, die nach Absatz 5 nicht berechtigt sind, Vollmitglieder zu werden. Associated members of the Group may, with the consent of the Council, become such organisations and entities as are not entitled to become full members under paragraph 5 of this Article.
The Council shall lay down rules concerning the circle of associated members and their rights and obligations.
7. a) The highest decision-making body of the group established in accordance with this Statute shall be the Council, in which all members are represented.
The Council shall meet at least once a year.
( b) The Council shall exercise all its powers and shall take all measures or shall take all measures necessary to implement and ensure the application of the provisions of this Statute.
( c) The Council shall, by special vote, adopt rules which are necessary for the performance of the Group <unk> s functions and which are subject to, and may not be incompatible with, these statutes.
These rules shall include (i) the rules of procedure, (ii) the financial rules and regulations relating to projects, (iii) the rules of service and (iv) the rules relating to the staff support fund.
( d) The Council shall not be empowered, and shall not be deemed to be empowered by its members, to assume obligations beyond the scope of this Statute or the provisions referred to in subparagraph (c) of this Article.
( e) In order to achieve the objectives set out in paragraph 3, the Council shall approve a work programme which shall be reviewed regularly.
8. Der Sitz der Gruppe befindet sich in Dhaka, Bangladesh, sofern der Rat nicht im Wege der besonderen Abstimmung etwas anderes beschließt. The headquarters of the Group shall be in Dhaka, Bangladesh, unless the Council, by special vote, decides otherwise.
The Council shall conclude a Headquarters Agreement with the host government as soon as practicable after the entry into force of this Statute.
9. a) Unless otherwise specified, and subject to subparagraph (d), the Council, the project committee referred to in paragraph 10, and any committees or subordinate bodies which may be set up, shall, as far as possible, take decisions by consensus.
If consensus cannot be reached, any member may request that such a decision be taken by a simple majority, unless a special vote is required.
( b) Each Member shall be entitled to the number of votes allotted to it in accordance with subparagraph (c) of this Article.
When voting, the European Community and members which are intergovernmental organisations shall cast the number of votes equal to the total number of votes accorded to their Member States.
( c) All members shall have a total of 2000 votes.
50% of the votes of all members shall be distributed evenly among all members, subject to subparagraph (b).
The remaining 50% of the total number of votes shall be divided among each member pro rata on the basis of a factor related to its importance in the jute economy (COJI) as specified in subparagraph (d).
The total number of basic votes and votes related to COJI of each member shall be rounded in an appropriate manner so as not to give rise to partial votes and so as not to exceed the total number of votes of members in 2000, subject, however, to subparagraph (e) of this Article.
( d) Für die Zwecke dieser Statzung gilt als <unk> Faktor bezogen auf die Bedeutung in der Jutewirtschaft <unk> (COJI) eines Mitglieds sein Anteil am Gesamtwert, der alle Mitgliedländer zugerechnet nach den folgenden Formuleln zugerechnet wird: For the purposes of this Statute, the <unk> factor relating to the importance in the jute economy <unk> (COJI) of a member shall be its share of the total value attributed to all member countries in accordance with the following formulas:
( i) for jute producers, the weighted average production volume of 40% and the average net trade volume of 60% of jute and jute products during the last three year period for which relevant statistics are available;
( ii) for non-jute producers and net jute importing countries, the average volume of net imports of jute and jute products during the last three year period for which relevant statistics are available.
( e) No member representing a single country shall receive more than 450 votes.
Votes exceeding this number by the method of calculation prescribed in subparagraphs (c) and (d) and in accordance with subparagraph (i) of this Article shall be distributed among all Members on the same basis as is provided for therein.
( f) Should, for any reason, difficulties arise in the calculation of votes in accordance with the method prescribed in subparagraphs (c), (d) and (e) of this Article, the Group may, by special vote, adopt another method for the distribution of votes.
( g) A Council meeting may commence only in the presence of members representing a total of 1000 votes.
A decision by the Council shall require the presence of members with a total of 1200 votes.
( h) The Council shall distribute the votes for each financial year at the beginning of the last session of the preceding year in accordance with this paragraph.
The distribution shall remain effective for the entire jute year, unless otherwise provided in subparagraph (i).
( i) The Council shall redistribute the votes of all members in accordance with this paragraph as soon as membership of the Group changes, or as soon as a member <unk> s right to vote is suspended or restricted by virtue of a provision of the rules of procedure.
The Council shall determine the date on which the redistribution of votes shall take effect.
( j) A member authorised by another member to cast the votes accorded to the authorising member in accordance with this paragraph shall cast such votes in accordance with the instructions of the authorising member.
10. a) The Council shall establish a project committee (COP) open to all members.
The Committee may invite associated members and other interested parties to participate in its work.
( b) The Project Committee shall advise the Council on all matters relating to projects and similar activities in accordance with the rules laid down by the Council.
( c) The Council may, under certain circumstances, delegate its powers with respect to the approval of projects and similar activities to the Project Committee.
The Council shall lay down rules for the delegation of powers to the Project Committee.
11. a) Um das Zusammenwirken mit der Privatwirtschaft zu erleichtern, errichtet der Rat einen Beirat der Privatwirtschaft (hereinafter referred to as <unk> Advisory Board <unk>). In order to facilitate cooperation with the private sector, the Council shall establish a Private Sector Advisory Board (hereinafter referred to as <unk> Advisory Board <unk>).
The Advisory Board shall be an advisory body which may make recommendations to the Council in matters relating to this Statute.
( b) The Advisory Board shall consist of associated members.
Other private sector entities expressing an interest may participate upon invitation.
( c) The Advisory Board shall submit periodic reports to the Council.
( d) The Advisory Board shall adopt its own rules of procedure in accordance with these statutes.
12. Besides the Project Committee and the Advisory Board of the Private Sector, the Council may establish further committees or other subordinate bodies under conditions to be determined by it.
13. a) Die Gruppe hat ein Sekretariat, das aus dem Generalsekretär und dem erforderlichen Personal besteht. The Group shall have a secretariat composed of the Secretary-General and the necessary staff.
( b) The Council shall appoint the Secretary-General by special vote.
With the exception of the appointment of the first Secretary-General, the procedure for the appointment of the Secretary-General shall be in accordance with the rules of procedure for the appointment.
( c) The Secretary-General shall be the chief administrative officer of the Group and shall be responsible to it for the application and implementation of these Statutes in accordance with the decisions of the Council.
( d) The Secretary-General shall appoint the staff in accordance with the rules laid down by the Council.
The staff shall be responsible to the Secretary-General.
14. a) The Group may, as necessary, arrange for consultations or cooperation with the United Nations, its organs or specialized agencies and other intergovernmental agencies.
( b) The Group may also make the arrangements it considers appropriate for maintaining contacts with interested governments of non-Member States, with national and international non-governmental institutions, and with non-associated private sector organizations and research entities.
( c) Observers may be invited to meetings of the Council or of its subordinate bodies on conditions to be determined by the Council or the bodies concerned.
15. Die Gruppe kann Antrag, nach Artikel 7 Absatz 9 des Übereinkommens zur Gründung des Gemeinsamen Fonds für Rohstoffe zum internationalen Rohstoffgremium (ICB) bestimmt zu werden, um im Einklang mit dieser Satzung Projekte für Jute und Jute-Erzeugnisse zu fördern, die der Fonds finanziert. The Group may request to be designated to the International Commodity Board (ICB) pursuant to Article 7 (9) of the Convention establishing the Common Fund for Commodities in order to promote, in accordance with this Statute, projects for jute and jute products financed by the Fund.
Decisions concerning the funding of such projects shall as a rule be taken by consensus.
If consensus is not reached, decisions shall be taken by special vote.
No member shall be liable, on the basis of its membership of the Council, for any liabilities arising from the borrowing or granting of loans in connection with projects by another member or entity.
The Secretary-General shall be empowered to conclude agreements with the Fund on approved projects.
16. a) The Group shall have international legal personality.
In particular, but subject to paragraph 7 (b) of this Article, it shall have the capacity to conclude contracts, to acquire and dispose of movable and immovable property, and to initiate judicial proceedings in the territory of each Member, subject to domestic law.
( b) The position of the Group in the territory of the host country shall be governed by the Headquarters Agreement between the host government and the Council referred to in paragraph 8 of this Article.
( c) As the legal successor of the International Jute Organization, all assets and liabilities of the Organization shall be transferred to the Group.
17. a) For the purposes of this Statute, the Group shall establish the following accounts:
( b) Each member shall, in accordance with the rules of procedure, contribute to the administrative account within the framework of an annual administrative budget approved by the Council.
The amount of the contribution of the members shall be directly proportional to the votes allotted to them in accordance with paragraph 9.
Payment of each member <unk> s contribution shall be made in accordance with the respective constitutional procedures.
( c) In addition to contributions to the administrative account under the annual administrative budget, the Group may accept contributions to the special account.
The special account shall be set up to finance projects, project planning and other activities.
Potential sources of financing for the Special Account may include:
( i) voluntary contributions from members, associated members and other sources; and
( ii) regional and international financial institutions, including the Common Fund for Commodities, the United Nations Development Programme, the World Bank, the Asian Development Bank, the International Fund for Agricultural Development, the Inter-American Development Bank and the African Development Bank.
18. a) Die Gruppe Analyse und verarbeitet Informationen und Statistiken zum Jute-Handel, die sie von der Ernährungs- und Landwirtschaftsorganisation der Vereinten Nationen (FAO), anderen internationalen und nationalen Einrichtungen und der Privatwirtschaft erhalten. The Group shall analyse and process information and statistics on jute trade received from the Food and Agriculture Organisation of the United Nations (FAO), other international and national institutions and the private sector.
The Group shall provide market forecasts and information on the market, including information on stocks and consumption by specific markets and industrial end users, to Members, associated Members and other interested parties.
The Group also invites national bodies in producing countries to improve data collection in the jute sector and to share the results with all interested parties.
Wherever possible, every effort shall be made to minimise duplication.
( b) The Group shall, in so far as the Council agrees, carry out studies on the international jute economy.
( c) The Group shall endeavour to ensure that the information it provides does not prejudice the confidentiality of the operations of governments, persons or undertakings producing, processing, marketing or consuming jute.
19. a) Die Gruppe übernimmt aufgrund der von den Mitgliedern übermittelten Informationen, augmented by information from all other relevant sources and including regular evaluation reports from donors, an annual assessment of the situation of the world jute economy and related affairs.
The annual assessment shall include an overview of the prospective production capacity of jute in the coming years and the outlook for jute production, consumption and trade in the following calendar year for the purpose of assisting members in their own assessment of the further development of the international jute economy.
( b) prepare a report on the results of the annual evaluation and circulate it to the members.
Where the Group considers it appropriate, this report and other reports and studies distributed to Members may be made available to other interested parties in accordance with the Rules of Procedure.
( c) The Group shall make periodic evaluations of its activities at least every two years and shall compare their consistency with the objectives and tasks of the Group in accordance with paragraphs 3 and 4 of this Article.
20. The Group shall, in consultation with members, associated members and other interested parties, identify obstacles and opportunities in the world market for jute and jute products with a view to taking appropriate action, in particular with a view to increasing demand and developing the market for jute and jute products and the diffusion and economic use of new technologies.
21. Die Mitglieder bemühen sich nach besten Kräften, zusammenarbeiten und sich für die Erreichung der Ziele der Gruppe eingesetzt, vor allem durch Übermittlung der in Absatz 19 Buchstabe a) bezeichneten Angaben. Members shall make every effort to cooperate and to contribute to the attainment of the Group <unk> s objectives, in particular by transmitting the information referred to in paragraph 19 (a).
22. Reservations to this Statute shall not be permitted.
23. a) Diese Satzung tritt in Kraft, wenn Staaten, die Europäische Gemeinschaft oder zwischenstaatliche Organisationen nach Absatz 5, auf die nach Anlage A dieser Satzung 60 v. H. des Handels (Einfuhr und Ausfuhr) mit Jute und Jute-Erzeugnissen entfallen, dem Generalsekretär der Vereinten Nationen (hereinafter referred to as <unk> Verwahrer <unk>) nach Buchstabe b) notifiziert haben, daß sie diese Satzung vorläufig anwenden oder endgültig annehmen. This Statute shall enter into force if States, the European Community or intergovernmental organizations referred to in paragraph 5 of this Article have notified the Secretary-General of the United Nations (hereinafter referred to as <unk> Depositary <unk>) in accordance with subparagraph (b) of Annex A to this Statute that they provisionally apply or definitively accept this Statute.
( b) A State, the European Community or intergovernmental organizations pursuant to paragraph 5 of this Article which wish to become members of the Group shall notify the Depositary that they have definitively accepted this Statute or are applying it provisionally pending the completion of their internal procedures.
States, the European Community or intergovernmental organisations which have notified that they are applying the Statute provisionally shall endeavour to complete their internal procedures as soon as possible and shall notify the depositary of the final adoption of the Statute.
( c) If the conditions for the entry into force of this Statute have not been fulfilled by 31 December 2001, the Secretary-General of the United Nations Conference on Trade and Development shall invite the States, the European Community and the intergovernmental organizations which have notified that they have accepted or are provisionally applying this Statute to decide whether they wish to implement this Statute among themselves.
( d) When these Statutes enter into force, the Secretary-General of the United Nations Conference on Trade and Development shall convene, as soon as possible, a founding session of the Council.
This shall, where possible, be notified to Members at least one month before the meeting.
24. Diese Statute kann vom Rat nur durch Konsens geändert werden. This Statute may be amended by the Council only by consensus.
The Secretary-General shall notify the depositary of any amendment adopted in accordance with this paragraph.
An amendment shall enter into force 90 days after the date on which notifications of acceptance by members representing at least 60% of the votes have been received by the depositary.
25. a) Die Gruppe bleibt für einen Zeitraum von acht Jahren bestehen, sofern der Rat nicht durch besondere Abstimmung beschließt, die Veltungsdauer dieser Satzung nach den Buchstaben b) und c) zu verlängern oder sie neu zu Verhandlungen oder sie nach Absatz 27 außer Kraft zu setzen. The Group shall remain in force for a period of eight years, unless the Council, by special vote, decides to extend or renegotiate the validity of this Statute in accordance with subparagraphs (b) and (c) of this Article or to suspend it in accordance with paragraph 27 of this Article.
( b) The Council may, by special vote, decide to extend the period of validity of this Statute not more than twice for two years each.
( c) The Council may, by special vote, decide to renegotiate these Statutes.
26. a) Ein Mitglied kann jederzeit durch eine an den Verwahrer und den Generalsekretär der Gruppe gerichtete schriftliche Rücktsanzeige aus der Gruppe ausstreten. A member may withdraw from the group at any time by giving written notice of withdrawal to the depositary and the Secretary-General of the group.
( b) Withdrawal shall not prejudice the financial obligations of the withdrawing member and shall not entitle the withdrawing member to a reduction in its contribution for the year in which the withdrawal is made.
( c) Withdrawal shall take effect 12 months after notification is received by the Depositary.
( d) The Secretary-General of the Group shall promptly notify each Member of the notifications received in accordance with this paragraph.
27. The Council may at any time, by special vote, decide to suspend these Statutes.
Such abrogation shall take effect on the date on which the Council decides.
The Secretary-General shall notify the Depositary of the decision taken in accordance with this paragraph.
28. Notwithstanding the lapse or withdrawal of this Statute, the Council shall remain in force for as long as is necessary for the dissolution of the Group, including the final settlement, but not more than 12 months.
between the European Community and Romania on the control of the carriage of goods by road and the promotion of combined transport
THE EUROPEAN COMMUNITY, hereinafter referred to as the <unk> Community <unk>, and
ROMANIA, hereinafter referred to as <unk> Romania
HAVING REGARD to the Europe Agreement establishing an association between the European Communities and their Member States, of the one part, and Romania, of the other part, of 1 February 1993, and in particular to Article 57 (3) thereof,
CONSIDERING that, with a view to the completion of the internal market and the implementation of the common transport policy, it is essential for the Community that the transit of goods through Romania can be completed as quickly and efficiently as possible and without obstacles or discrimination,
CONSIDERING that Romania has an interest in developing existing reciprocal rights and obligations with respect to access to the transport market and transit traffic as a first step towards a land transport agreement, as provided for in the Europe Agreement establishing an association between the European Communities and their Member States, of the one part, and Romania, of the other part, of 1 February 1993,
CONSIDERING that it is also necessary to ensure the coordinated development of transport between and through the territories of the Parties, in particular by introducing and developing a series of coordinated measures for road and combined transport which are competitive, promote environmentally friendly vehicles and are designed for sustainable mobility,
The objective of this Agreement is to strengthen cooperation between the Contracting Parties in the field of freight transport, and in particular road transit, and to ensure the coordinated development of traffic between and through the territories of the Contracting Parties.
( 1) Die Zusammenarbeit betrifft den Güterverkehr auf der Straße sowie den kombinierten Verkehr. Cooperation concerns road transport of goods and combined transport.
( 2) Dieses Abkommen regelt insbesondere folgende Punkte: This Agreement shall in particular govern the following points:
- access to the road freight transit market;
- accompanying legislative, regulatory and administrative measures, including economic, fiscal, social and technical provisions;
- cooperation in developing a transport system which also takes account of environmental protection requirements,
- the regular exchange of information on the development of the transport policies of the Parties.
For the purposes of this Agreement, the following definitions shall apply:
( a) <unk> transit traffic
( b) <unk> combined transport
- Hereby, the incoming or outgoing route shall include the route from the point at which the goods are loaded to the nearest loading bay for the incoming route and from the nearest suitable loading bay to the point at which the goods are unloaded, for the outgoing route, or
- a radius not exceeding 150 km as the crow flies around the inland or seaport of the transhipment;
( c) <unk> road vehicle
( d) <unk> user charges <unk> are special sums payable on a non-discriminatory basis for the use of an infrastructure by a motor vehicle for a fixed period of time;
( e) <unk> tolls
( f) <unk> Territory of Party
- as regards the European Community, the territory in which the Treaty establishing the European Economic Community is applied under the conditions laid down in that Treaty, and
- as regards Romania, the territory of Romania.
The Contracting Parties shall adopt by mutual agreement the measures necessary for the development and promotion of combined transport to ensure that a large part of transboundary transport is carried out under more environmentally friendly conditions.
The Parties shall take all necessary measures to improve the competitiveness of combined transport (CT), in particular:
( a) encourage transport users and consignors to use combined transport by:
- improving the competitiveness of all types of combined transport in relation to road transport by providing financial support to new CT projects in the Community or Romania,
- the promotion of unaccompanied combined transport, particularly over long distances, and in particular the use of swap bodies, containers and semitrailers;
- the abolition, within the appropriate framework, of quota and licence systems for the inflow and / or outflow routes which form an integral part of the CV service;
- the consideration of a tax reduction for road vehicles used in combined transport,
- reducing journey times and improving the reliability of combined transport, in particular by:
( i) measures are taken to increase the frequency of the transport of CV services in accordance with the needs of the senders and users;
( ii) measures are taken to reduce waiting times at terminals and increase their productivity;
( iii) simplification of frontier checks in the case of combined transport, with checks on all goods, except in cases requiring veterinary and phytosanitary inspection, being carried out as soon as possible in the CV terminals themselves;
( iv) improve the safety of the goods, the transport unit and the loading unit in the combined transport chain.
- ensuring non-discriminatory access to terminals financed or supported by public funds,
- to the extent possible, the priority award of road transit licences issued pursuant to Article 6 (2) by the competent authorities of the Contracting Parties to road haulage undertakings which make high use of combined transport in accordance with the statistical data available to each Contracting Party;
- where necessary for the uniformity of rail dimensions, for the control of the weight, dimensions and technical characteristics of specific CV equipment and for the consideration of the coordinated ordering and commissioning of such equipment where the volume of traffic so requires;
( b) provide, on request, information on new CV actions, including technology research projects, which are co-financed by the Contracting Party (s), in the form of a summary report listing the content, results and impact of the action or technology project;
- in accordance with the relevant provisions of the European Agreement on Important Transboundary Compounds and Equipment (AGTC) of 1 February 1991;
- by eliminating bottlenecks on the feeder routes to the CV terminals in order to encourage the use of combined transport,
- examination of the possibility of approving 44 tonne hexagonal vehicles on the routes used in combined transport;
- derogations from the prohibition on driving on weekends and public holidays on routes used in and out of combined transport;
- reciprocal approval of CT operators for rail transport under a new Agreement.
( 1) Die Vertragsparteien kommen hinsichtlich des beiderseitigen Zugangs zum Verkehrsmarkt überein, unbeschadet des Absatzes 2 zunächst die aufgrund bilateraler Abkommen oder sonstiger zwischen Mitgliedstaaten der Gemeinschaft und Romania geschlossener bilateraler Vereinbarungen bestehenden Regelungen beizubehalten. The Contracting Parties agree, without prejudice to paragraph 2 of this Article, to maintain in the first instance the existing arrangements based on bilateral agreements or other arrangements concluded between Member States of the Community and Romania.
However, pending the conclusion of an Agreement between the Contracting Parties on market access in the road haulage sector in accordance with Article 7, Romania shall, together with the Member States of the Community, make any necessary amendments to those bilateral agreements and / or arrangements with a view to bringing them into conformity with this Agreement.
( 2) Die Vertragsparteien kommen überein, mit Inkrafttreten dieses Abkommens zusätzlich zu den Lizenzen gemäß der in Absatz 1 genannten Regelung für jedes Kalenderjahr folgende Lizenzen für den Transitverkehr von Lastkraftfahrzeugen durch die Gebiete der Mitgliedstaaten der Gemeinschaft und Romania zu gewähren: The Contracting Parties agree, upon the entry into force of this Agreement, to grant, in addition to the licences referred to in paragraph 1 of this Article, for each calendar year the following licences for the transit of heavy goods vehicles through the territories of the Member States of the Community and Romania:
7000 licences valid in the Member States of the Community whose trademarks are glued into the licence.
3000 trademarks for each Member State of the Community.
( d) For the licences referred to in subparagraphs (a) and (b) above, the models in Annex 1a and 1b respectively shall be used.
( e) For the marks referred to in subparagraph (c), the model in Annex 1c shall be used.
( f) The certificates referred to in subparagraphs (a) and (b) shall be issued by the competent authorities of Romania and the competent authorities of the Member States of the Community, respectively, from the services of the Commission.
The competent authorities shall fill out the licence with the exception of the points <unk> number plate of the motor vehicle <unk>, <unk> outbound <unk> and <unk> return <unk> and send it to the transport undertakings for a fee which shall cover only reasonable administrative expenses.
( g) The trademarks referred to in subparagraph (c) shall be provided to the competent authorities of Romania by the services of the Commission.
The marks shall be affixed to them before the use of the licence, indicating which Member States of the Community the licence is valid for.
( h) The Contracting Parties agree that no tax or similar charge shall be levied on the use of the licences referred to in subparagraphs (a) and (b).
( i) The licences and trademarks shall be valid for one calendar year from 1 January to 31 January of the following year and may be used only for one return journey.
( 3) Die in Absatz 2 genannten Lizenzen können nur für Fahrzeuge verwendet werden, die mindestens die EURO-1 -Normen oder die in Anhang 4 aufgenommenen Bedingungen für die Bescheinigung <unk> umweltfreundlicher Lastkraftwagen <unk> erfuellen. The licences referred to in paragraph 2 of this Article may only be used for vehicles meeting at least the EURO1 standards or the conditions for certification of environmentally friendly lorries listed in Annex 4.
Evidence of compliance with these conditions shall always be carried in the vehicle.
( 4) Ist das Datum des Inkrafttretens dieses Abkommens gemäß Artikel 19 nicht der 1. Januar, so wird die Zahl der Lizenzen und Marken nach Absatz 2 in dem Kalenderjahr des Inkrafttretens des Abkommens entsprechend verringert. If the date of entry into force of this Agreement pursuant to Article 19 is not 1 January, the number of licences and trademarks in accordance with paragraph 2 of this Article shall be reduced accordingly in the calendar year in which the entry into force of this Agreement takes place.
( 5) Die zuständigen Behörden der Vertragsparteien erteilen gemäß diesem Abkommen nur solchen Verkehrsunternehmen Lzenzen für die Güterbeförderung, die im Land dieser Vertragspartei berechtigt sind, grenzüberschreitende Beförderungen auf der Straße vorzunehmen. The competent authorities of the Contracting Parties shall, in accordance with this Agreement, issue only to such transport undertakings licences for the carriage of goods authorised in the country of that Contracting Party to carry out frontier operations by road.
The licence shall be carried in the vehicle.
In the case of vehicle combinations, it shall be carried in the vehicle.
The licence shall apply to the whole combination of vehicles, even if the trailer or semitrailer is not registered in the name of the licence holder or if it is registered in another State.
( 6) Die Vertragsparteien unterlassen jegliche einseitigen Maßnahmen, die zur Diskriminierung von Verkehrsunternehmen oder fahrzeuge aus der Gemeinschaft bzw. Rumniens führen könnten. The Contracting Parties shall refrain from any unilateral measures that could lead to discrimination against transport undertakings or vehicles from the Community or Romania.
Each Contracting Party shall take the necessary measures to facilitate the road traffic covered by this Agreement in or through its territory.
The Contracting Parties undertake to develop, as a matter of priority and taking into account the fact that Romania will adopt the fiscal, social and technical provisions of the Community, a common system of the Contracting Parties for future access to the road transport market.
For carriage under this Agreement:
1. Die Vertragsparteien stellen sicher, daß bei der Kraftfahrzeugbesteuererung, bei der Steuerload, Maut und sonstigen Formen von Benutzungsgebühren nicht nach Nationgehörigkeit oder Niederlassungsort diskriminiert wird. The Contracting Parties shall ensure that no discrimination is made on the basis of nationality or place of establishment in respect of vehicle taxation, taxation, toll and other forms of user charges.
2. Straßenfahrzeuge, die bei einer Vertragspartei gemeldet sind, werden von sämtlichen Fahrzeugsteuer und Gebühren, die auf die Benutzung oder den Besitz von fahrzeuge erhoben werden, sowie von sämtlichen Sondersteuer und -abgaben, die auf Beförderungen auf dem Gebiet der anderen Vertragspartei erhoben werden. Road vehicles registered with either Party shall be exempt from all vehicle taxes and charges levied on the use or possession of vehicles and from any special taxes and charges levied on the other Party <unk> s territory.
Road vehicles shall not be exempt from the payment of taxes and charges on fuel, tolls and other user charges.
3. Die Vertragsparteien stellen sicher, daß für die Benutzung eines Straßenabschnitts nicht Simultaneously Mautgebühren und sonstige Benutzungsgebühren erhoben werden. The Contracting Parties shall ensure that tolls and other charges are not levied at the same time for the use of a road section.
However, the Contracting Parties may charge a toll for the use of bridges, tunnels and passes in transport networks where user charges are already levied.
4. folgende Stoffe und Gegenstände sind von Zollgebühren und sämtlichen Steuern und Gebühren frei: The following substances and items shall be exempt from customs duties and all taxes and fees:
( a) fuel in the tanks of road vehicles entering the territory of the other Contracting Party, when the tanks concerned are those provided by the manufacturer for the type of vehicle concerned;
( b) fuel in the tanks of trailers and semitrailers used for cooling systems of refrigeration systems;
( c) lubricants for use during the journey in appropriate quantities;
( d) spare parts and tools for the repair of a vehicle in the event of a breakdown during an international road transport operation; the parts to be replaced should be re-exported or destroyed under the supervision of the competent customs authority of the other Contracting Party.
5. Unbeschadet von Absatz 2 Unterabsatz 2 müssen für ein Fahrzeug, dessen Gewicht, Abmessungen oder Achslast die im Gebiet Romniens gültigen Grenzwerte überten, das jedoch den Bestimmungen der Richtlinie 96 / 53 / EG des Rates<unk> 1) über Gewicht und Abmessungen entspricht, keine Sonderabgaben gezahlt werden, sofern es den in Anhang 5 festgelegten Vorschriften entspricht. Notwithstanding the provisions of paragraph 2 (2) of this Article, no special charge shall be paid for a vehicle whose weight, dimensions or axle load exceeds the limits in force in the territory of Romania which complies with the provisions of Council Directive 96 / 53 / EC (1) on weights and dimensions, provided that it complies with the provisions laid down in Annex 5.
The Contracting Parties to this Agreement shall implement, or apply provisions consistent with Council Regulations (EEC) No 3820 / 85 (2) and (3) as amended, the European Agreement on the Work of Manpower Employed in International Road Traffic (AETR) of 1 July 1970, as amended at the time of the entry into force of this Agreement.
( 1) Romania verabschiedet bei Inkrafttreten dieses Abkommens Maßnahmen, die den in Anhang 2 genannten Rechtsvorschriften gleichwertig sind, und innerhalb von zwei Jahren nach Inkrafttreten dieses Abkommens Maßnahmen, die den in Anhang 3 genannten Rechtsvorschriften gleichwertig sind. Romania shall adopt measures equivalent to those referred to in Annex 2 and, within two years of the entry into force of this Agreement, measures equivalent to those referred to in Annex 3.
( 2) Die Vertragsparteien dieses Abkommens setzen das Europäische Übereinkommen über die internationale Beförderung gefährlicher Güter auf der Straße (ADR) vom 30. September 1957 in der bei Inkrafttreten dieses Abkommens gültigen Fassung um. The Contracting Parties to this Agreement shall implement the European Agreement on the International Carriage of Hazardous Goods by Road (ADR) of 30 September 1957 as it stands at the time of the entry into force of this Agreement.
( 3) Rumänien bemüht sich um die Anpassung seiner Vorschriften über die Befuhr verderblicher Güter, lebender Tiere und gefährlichen Güter an die der Gemeinschaft. Romania shall endeavour to adapt its rules on the carriage of perishable goods, live animals and dangerous goods to those of the Community.
( 4) Die Vertragsparteien tauschen Erfahrungen und Informationen über ihre Vorschriften aus, um den Verkehrsfluss und die Verkehrssicherheit in Spitzenverkehrszeiten (Weekends, Feiertage, Ferienzeiten) zu verbessern. The Contracting Parties shall exchange experience and information on their regulations to improve traffic flow and safety at peak times (weekends, holidays, holidays).
( 5) Die Vertragsparteien setzen sich gemeinsam für die Einführung, Weiterentwicklung und Koordinierung interoperabler Verkehrsinformationssysteme ein. The Parties shall jointly implement, develop and coordinate interoperable transport information systems.
( 6) Die Vertragsparteien bemühen sich um die Harmonisierung der technischen Hilfe für fahrer, die Verbreitung wichtiger Informationen über den Verkehr und die Emergency dienste, darunter den Krankenentransport, sowie anderer für den fahrer wichtigen Aspekte. The Contracting Parties shall endeavour to harmonize technical assistance for drivers, to disseminate important information on transport and emergency services, including ambulance transport, and other driver relevant aspects.
( 1) Die Vertragsparteien kommen überein, die Formalitäten für die Befuhr von Gütern im Rahmen dieses Abkommens zu vereinfachen. The Contracting Parties agree to simplify the formalities for the carriage of goods under this Agreement.
( 2) Die Vertragsparteien kommen überein, Verhandlungen über ein Abkommen über die Vereinfachung der Kontrollen und Förmlichkeiten im Güterverkehr aufzunehmen. The Contracting Parties agree to enter into negotiations on an Agreement on the simplification of controls and formalities in the transport of goods.
( 3) Die Vertragsparteien kommen überein, soweit erforderlich, weitere Vereinfachungsmaßnahmen gemeinsam anzustreben und zu fördern. The Contracting Parties agree, as far as necessary, to jointly seek and promote further simplification measures.
If, on the basis of experience gained with the application of this Agreement, one of the Contracting Parties concludes that other measures not covered by this Agreement are in the interest of a coordinated European transport policy and could, in particular, contribute to the solution of the transit problems, it shall make proposals in this respect to the other Contracting Party.
The body responsible for cooperation shall be a Joint Committee called the <unk> Transport Committee Community / Romania <unk>.
- be composed of representatives designated by the Community and Romania,
- meet alternately in the Community and in Romania at the request of either Contracting Party,
- ensure the smooth implementation of this Agreement, in particular:
( a) explore possibilities for cooperation and the promotion of combined transport and review progress made in this respect at least every two years;
( b) review the Annexes to this Agreement at least every two years;
( c) arbitrate any disputes arising out of the application and interpretation of this Agreement; in the event of differences of opinion, the decision shall be postponed until a later meeting of the Joint Committee, which shall take place within two months of the date of the postponement, in accordance with the procedure laid down in the rules of procedure;
( d) coordinate monitoring, forecasting and other statistical work in the field of international road and combined transport, and in particular road transport;
( e) take, where appropriate, measures to make technical adjustments to the provisions of this Agreement;
( f) develop, where necessary, recommendations for a possible increase in the number of licences / trademarks;
( g) discuss, where appropriate, other issues relevant to the implementation of this Agreement.
( 1) Verstößt ein Fahrzeug oder ein Fahrzeugführer gegen die Bestimmungen dieses Abkommens, so kann die zuständigen Behörde der Vertragspartei, in dessen Gebiet es zu diesem Verstoß gekommen ist, den Unfall der zuständigen Behörde der anderen Vertragspartei melden, die die gesetzlich vorgesehenen Maßnahmen ergreifen kann. If a vehicle or driver violates the provisions of this Agreement, the competent authority of the Contracting Party in whose territory it has come to this violation may report the incident to the competent authority of the other Contracting Party, which may take the measures provided for by law.
( 2) Die zuständigen Behörde, bei der eine solche Mitteilung eingeht, unterrichtet die zuständigen Behörde der anderen Vertragspartei umgehend von der getroffenen Maßnahme. The competent authority receiving such notification shall promptly inform the competent authority of the other Contracting Party of the measure taken.
( 3) Die Bestimmungen dieses Artikels haben keinen Auswirkungen auf rechtmäßige Sanktionen, die je nachdem, wo es zu dem Verstoß gekommen ist, von den Gerichten oder Strafverfolgungsbehörden des Mitgliedstaats der Europäischen Gemeinschaft oder Rumniens verhängt werden können. The provisions of this Article shall have no effect on lawful sanctions which may be imposed by the courts or criminal prosecution authorities of the Member State of the European Community or of Romania, depending on where the violation has occurred.
This Agreement shall be concluded for a period of five years.
It shall be renewed automatically for a further period of three years, unless either Party denounces the Agreement within a period of 12 months to the end of its term.
Either Party may denounce this Agreement by giving the other Party 12 months <unk> notice.
between the European Community and the United Nations Relief and Works Agency for Palestine Refugees in the Near East (UNRWA) on Aid to Refugees in the Middle East (2000 -2005)
The European Community (hereinafter referred to as the <unk> Community <unk>) shall conclude this Agreement with the United Nations Relief and Works Agency for Palestine Refugees in the Near East (hereinafter referred to as <unk> UNRWA <unk>) in order to reaffirm its commitment to financial support to UNRWA.
This financial support, which shall be provided over a period of four years (2002 -2005), shall take the form of contributions to the general budget of UNRWA.
Commitment shall be made in accordance with the budgetary resources available and in accordance with the Community financial perspective up to the year 2006.
( 1) Die Gemeinschaft zahlt dem UNRWA jährlich einen Barbeitrag zum GesamthHaushalt. The Community shall pay UNRWA annually a contribution to the budget as a whole.
Notwithstanding Article 3, this contribution shall not exceed EUR 55 million for 2002, EUR 57.75 million for 2003, EUR 606 637 500 for 2004 and EUR 636 669 375 for 2005.
( 2) Der Beitrag zum GesamthBudget wird auf der Grundlage von Zuschussvereinbarungen geleistet, die zwischen der Kommission der Europäischen Gemeinschaften und dem UNRWA für die Jahre 2002-2005 zu schließen sind. The contribution to the total budget shall be made on the basis of grant agreements to be concluded between the Commission of the European Communities and UNRWA for the years 2002 to 2005.
The Grant Arrangements shall be concluded in accordance with the Agreement between the United Nations and the European Community of 9 August 1999 on the principles governing the financing and cofinancing by the Community of programmes and projects managed by the United Nations.
( 3) Für den Beitrag sind die internen und externen Rechnungspaufungsverfahren nach den einschlägigen Finanzvorschriften, Regeln und Richtlinien des UNRWA berechgebend; das Ergebnis der Prüfungen wird der Kommission mitgeteilt. The contribution shall be governed by internal and external audit procedures in accordance with the relevant financial regulations, rules and guidelines of UNRWA; the result of such audits shall be communicated to the Commission.
Taking into account the annual needs of the refugee population, further Community resources may be made available to UNRWA <unk> s food aid programme to meet the specific needs of disadvantaged groups.
The quantity, amount, scope and characteristics of the products, cash and services provided and any other conditions relating to the support to the food aid programme shall be agreed separately on the basis of annual requests from UNRWA.
During the period of validity of this Agreement, the Contracting Parties may, if necessary, increase or reduce by mutual agreement, on the basis of an exchange of letters between the Community and UNRWA, the parts of the contributions otherwise established under this Agreement.
By the end of 2003, the Parties shall review the political developments concerning refugees and evaluate any plans drawn up and, where appropriate, implemented by UNRWA for the transfer of its functions to the Palestinian Authority and / or any other agency.
If, during the period of validity of this Agreement, the functions of UNRWA are transferred in whole or in part to the Palestinian Authority or any other body, the necessary adjustments to the corresponding parts of the Community contribution received by UNRWA under this Agreement shall be made on the basis of an exchange of letters between the Community and UNRWA.
( 1) Bei Streitigkeiten, Meinungsverschieheiten und Forderungen, die sich aus der Auslegung, Anwendung oder Erfuellung dieses Abkommens ergeben oder damit in Zusammenhang stehen, einschließlich Fragen in Bezug auf sein bestehen, seine Gültigkeit oder seine Beendigung, die von den Vertragsparteien nicht einvernehmlich geregelt werden können, wird ein Schiedsverfahren nach der Freiwilligen Schiedsgerichtsordnung des Ständigen Schiedshofs für internationale Organisationen und Staaten in der Zeitpunkt der Unterzeichnung dieses Abkommens geltenden Fassung eingeleitet. In the event of any dispute, disagreement or claim arising out of or relating to the interpretation, application or fulfilment of this Agreement, including any question relating to its existence, validity or termination which may not be mutually resolved by the Contracting Parties, arbitration shall be instituted in accordance with the volunteer rules of arbitration of the Permanent Court of Arbitration for International Organisations
( 2) Es wird ein Schiedsrichter ernannt. An arbitrator shall be appointed.
( 3) Verfahrenssprache ist Englisch. The language of the proceedings shall be English.
( 4) Kann sich die beiden Vertragsparteien nicht auf einen Schiedsrichter einigen, so wird dieser auf schriftliches Ersuchen einer Vertragspartei vom Präsident des Internationalen Gerichtshofs ernannt. If the two Contracting Parties are unable to agree on an arbitrator, the latter shall be appointed by the President of the International Court of Justice at the written request of either Contracting Party.
( 5) Der Schiedsrichter trifft seine Entscheidung unter Berücksichtigung der von den Staaten anerkannten allgemeinen Rechtsgrundsätze im Einklang mit den Bestimmungen dieses Abkommens. The arbitrator shall make his decision in accordance with the provisions of this Agreement, taking into account the general legal principles recognised by the States.
When the United Nations and the Commission have agreed in their discussions on a general arrangement for voluntary contributions, the relevant provisions of the Arrangement and this Agreement shall be reviewed without delay and the necessary amendments to the provisions of this Agreement agreed by UNRWA and the Commission shall be made.
This Agreement shall apply for a period of four calendar years (2002, 2003, 2004 and 2005).
This Agreement shall be approved by the Contracting Parties in accordance with their own procedures.
It shall enter into force on the first day of the month following the date on which the Contracting Parties have notified each other of the completion of the procedures referred to in paragraph 1.
This Agreement is drawn up in duplicate in the Danish, Dutch, English, Finnish, French, German, Greek, Italian, Portuguese, Spanish and Swedish languages, each text being equally authentic.
( UNRWA)
between the European Union and Bosnia and Herzegovina on the activities of the European Union Police Mission (EUPM) in Bosnia and Herzegovina
hereinafter referred to as the <unk> Admission Party
hereinafter referred to as <unk> Participating Parties
- the United Nations International Police Intervention Force (IPTF) has been present in Bosnia and Herzegovina since 1996 and the European Union has offered to provide the follow-up mission to the IPTF mission in Bosnia and Herzegovina as from 1 January 2003,
- Bosnia and Herzegovina has accepted this offer,
- the Council of the European Union, on 11 March 2002, adopted Joint Action 2002 / 210 / CFSP on the European Union Police Mission (EUPM), according to which EUPM should ensure that Bosnia and Herzegovina maintains its own sustainable policing arrangements in accordance with best European and international practice and thus raises the current policing standard in Bosnia and Herzegovina,
( 1) Die Polizeimission der Europäischen Union, nachstehend <unk> EUPM <unk> genannt, richten ihr Hauptquartier in Sarajewo ein. The Police Mission of the European Union, hereinafter referred to as <unk> EUPM <unk>, shall establish its headquarters in Sarajevo.
( 2) Die EUPM richten auf Entscheidung des Leiters der Mission/ Polizeizeichefs in Absprache mit der Aufnahmepartei darüber gegebenenfalls weitere Büro in Bosnia und Herzegovina ein. EUPM shall, by decision of the Head of the Mission / Police Chiefs, in consultation with the host Party, furthermore, as appropriate, establish further offices in Bosnia and Herzegovina.
To this end, EUPM shall establish an initial number of 24 observer teams, which shall be based in the various police structures of Bosnia and Herzegovina at the intermediate and higher levels, including the territorial units, public security centres, cantons, the State Intelligence Protection Agency, the State Border Services and the Brcko District.
( 3) Die mit den erforderlichen Beobachtungs-, Beratungs- und Überprüfungsbefugnissen ausgestattete EUPM sollte ihre Ziele bis Ende 2005 erreichen. The EUPM, equipped with the necessary powers of observation, consultation and verification, should achieve its objectives by the end of 2005.
( 4) Die EUPM handelt gemäß ihrem in Artikel 1 Absatz 2 der Gemeinsamen Aktion 2002/ 210 / CFSP festgelegten Auftrag. The EUPM shall act in accordance with its mandate set out in Article 1 (2) of the 2002 / 210 / CFSP Joint Action.
( 5) Die EUPM nimmt ihre Aufgaben im Rahmen dieses Abkommens unabhängig wahr. The EUPM shall independently perform its functions under this Agreement.
( 6) Die Aufnahmepartei erteilt der EUPM alle Informationen und leistet jede Art von Zusammenarbeit, die zur Erreichung der Ziele der EUPM erforderlich sind. The host Party shall provide the EUPM with all information and shall cooperate in any manner necessary to achieve the objectives of the EUPM.
The host Party may designate one of its police officers as a liaison officer with the EUPM.
( 1) Die EUPM setzt sich aus dem Leiter der Mission/ Polizeizeichef und den sonstigen Angehörigen der EUPM zusammen. The EUPM shall consist of the head of the mission / police force and other members of the EUPM.
( 2) Der Leiter der Mission/ Polizeizeichef der EUPM wird vom Rat der Europäischen Union ernannt. The head of the mission / police force of the EUPM shall be appointed by the Council of the European Union.
The other members of the EUPM shall be assigned by the Head of Mission to specific uses.
( 3) Die sonstigen Angehörigen der EUPM setzen sich zusammen aus Other members of the EUPM shall consist of:
( a) Police forces seconded by the Member States of the European Union.
Non-Member States of the EU may also designate EUPM police forces and shall then be seconding parties, as shall the European Union and its Member States;
( b) international civilian staff seconded by the sending parties or recruited by the EUPM, if necessary, on a contract basis;
( c) local staff who may be recruited by EUPM as necessary.
At the request of the Head of Mission / Police Chiefs, the host Party shall facilitate the recruitment by EUPM of qualified local staff.
( 4) Die Gesamtzahl der EUPM-Angehörigen wird vom Leiter der Mission/ Polizeizeichef festgelegt. The total number of members of the EUPM shall be determined by the Chief of Mission / Police.
( 1) Die EUPM in Bosnia und Herzegovina führt ihre Tätigkeit unter der Verantwortung des Leiters der Mission/ Polizeizeichefs aus, der die EUPM leitet und die laufenden Geschäfte führt. The EUPM in Bosnia and Herzegovina shall carry out its activities under the responsibility of the Head of Mission / Police Chiefs, who shall direct the EUPM and shall conduct its current operations.
( 2) Der Leiter der Mission/ Polizeizeichef erstattet dem Generalsekretär/ Hohen Vertreter für die Gemeinsame Außen- und Sicherheitspolitik über den Sonderbeauftragten der Europäischen Union in Bosnia und Herzegovina (EUSR) Bericht. The Head of Mission / Police shall report to the Secretary-General / High Representative for the Common Foreign and Security Policy through the Special Representative of the European Union in Bosnia and Herzegovina (EUSR).
( 3) Der Leiter der Mission/ Polizeizeichef unterrichtet die Aufnahmepartei regelmäßig über die Tätigkeit der EUPM. The head of the mission / police chief shall regularly inform the host party of the activities of the EUPM.
( 1) Die EUPM erhält einen Status, der dem einer diplomatischen Mission entspricht. The EUPM shall have a status equivalent to that of a diplomatic mission.
( 2) Das Hauptquartier in Sarajewo, andere Büro und alle Transportmittel der EUPM sind inverletzlich. The headquarters in Sarajevo, other offices and all means of transport of EUPM shall be inviolable.
( 3) Das EUPM-Personal genießen sämtliche Vorrechte und Immunitäten, wie sie diplomatischen Bediensteten gemäß dem Wiener Übereinkommen vom 18. April 1961 über diplomatische Beziehungen gewährt werden, nach dessen Maßgabe die vorrangige gerichtliche Zuständigkeit bei den EU-Mitgliedstaaten und sonstigen Entsendeparteien liegt. The EUPM-staff shall enjoy all privileges and immunities accorded to diplomatic officials in accordance with the Vienna Convention on Diplomatic Relations of 18 April 1961, under whose conditions priority jurisdiction shall lie with the Member States of the EU and other sending parties.
Such privileges and immunities shall be accorded to EUPM staff during and after their mission in respect of acts previously performed within the framework of their mission.
( 4) Das Verwaltungs- und technische Personal der EUPM genießt in Einklang mit dem Wiener Übereinkommen über diplomatische Beziehungen den gleichen Status wie das Verwaltungs- und technische Personal der Entsendeparteien in Embassies. The administrative and technical staff of EUPM shall enjoy the same status in accordance with the Vienna Convention on Diplomatic Relations as the administrative and technical staff of the sending parties to embassies.
Such privileges and immunities shall be accorded to the administrative and technical staff of EUPM during and after their mission in respect of acts previously performed within the framework of their mission.
( 5) Das vor Ort eingestellte Hilfspersonal der EUPM genießen im Einklang mit dem Wiener Übereinkommen über diplomatische Beziehungen den gleichen Status wie das örtliche Personal in Embassies. The on-site staff of the EUPM shall enjoy the same status as the local staff in embassies in accordance with the provisions of the Vienna Convention on Diplomatic Relations.
( 6) Die Aufnahmepartei erleichtert alle Ein- und Ausreisen des Leiters der Mission/ Polizeizeichefs und der EUPM-Angehörigen in das bzw. aus dem Hoheitsgebiet von Bosnia und Herzegovina. The host Party shall facilitate all entry and exit of the Head of the Mission / Police Chiefs and of the EUPM personnel to and from the territory of Bosnia and Herzegovina.
The EUPM shall provide the host party with a list of the nationals of the EUPM and shall inform the host party in advance of the first arrival and final departure of EUPM staff.
( 7) Die Aufnahmepartei erkennt das Recht der Entsendeparteien und der EUPM an, zollfrei und ohne sonstige Beschränkungen die von der EUPM benötigten und zu ihrer ausschließlichen und offizielle Verwendung bestimmten Ausrüstungen, Vorräte, Lieferungen und anderen Güter einzuführen. The host Party shall recognise the right of the posting parties and of the EUPM to introduce, duty free and without other restrictions, the equipment, supplies, supplies and other goods required by the EUPM and intended for their exclusive and official use.
The receiving Party shall also recognise its right to buy such items in the territory of the receiving Party and to export or otherwise dispose of such imported or purchased equipment, stocks, supplies and other goods.
( 8) Die Aufnahmepartei erkennt ferner das Recht des EUPM-Personals sowie des Verwaltungs- und technischen Personals der EUPM an, Gegenstände für den Personal Bedarf zu kaufen und/ oder zollfrei und ohne sonstige Beschränkungen einzuführen und diese Gegenstände auszuführen. The host Party shall also recognise the right of EUPM staff and EUPM administrative and technical staff to purchase and / or import, duty free and without any other restrictions, items for personal use and to execute such items.
( 1) Die Mitglieder der EUPM tragen keine Waffen. The members of the EUPM shall not carry weapons.
( 2) Die Mitglieder der EUPM können ihre nationale Uniform oder Zivilkleidung mit einem EUPM-Erkennungszeichen tragen. The members of the EUPM may wear their national uniform or civilian clothing bearing a EUPM badge.
They shall carry the national passport and an identity card of the EUPM.
( 1) Die Aufnahmepartei ergreift alle erforderlichen Maßnahmen für den Schutz und die Sicherheit der EUPM und ihrer Mitglieder. The host Party shall take all necessary measures for the protection and security of EUPM and its members.
All relevant arrangements proposed by the host party shall be agreed with the head of mission / police before they are implemented.
( 2) Die EUPM-Angehörigen unterlassen alle Handlungen oder Tätigkeiten, die mit der Unparteilichkeit ihrer Aufgaben unvereinbar sind. The members of the EUPMshall refrain from any action or activity incompatible with the impartiality of their duties.
( 3) Die EUPM und ihre Angehörigen genießen unter Einbeziehung ihrer Transportmittel und Ausrüstungen die Freiheit, die zur Erfuellung des Auftrags der Mission erforderlich ist. The EUPM and its nationals shall enjoy, including their means of transport and equipment, the freedom of movement required to fulfil the mission <unk> s mandate.
( 4) Die EUPM-Angehörigen können bei ihrer Tätigkeit von einem Dolmetscher und, auf Anforderung der EUPM, von einer von der Aufnahmepartei benannten offizielle Begleitperson begleitperson begleiten werden. EUPM nationals may be accompanied in their activities by an interpreter and, at the request of the EUPM, by an official escort designated by the host party.
( 5) Die EUPM kann an ihrem Hauptquartier in Sarajewo sowie an anderen Orten, über die Leiter der Mission/ Polizeizeichef befindet, die Flagge der Europäischen Union hoist. The EUPM may fly the flag of the European Union at its headquarters in Sarajevo and at any other location where the Head of Mission / Police is located.
( 6) Fahrzeuge und andere Transportmittel der EUPM tragen ein Erkennungszeichen der Mission, über das die zuständigen Behörden unterrichtet werden. EUPM vehicles and other means of transport shall bear a mission identification badge which shall be communicated to the competent authorities.
( 1) Fahrzeuge und andere Transportmittel der EUPM unterliegen keine Zwangszulassung oder -genehmigung; alle Fahrzeuge sind bei Dritten versicherung. EUPM vehicles and other means of transport shall not be subject to compulsory registration or approval; all vehicles shall be insured with third parties.
( 2) Die EUPM kann Streets, Bridges, Canals und andere Wasserstraße, Hafenanlagen und Flugplätze ohne Zahlung von Gebühren, Maut oder anderen Abgaben benutzt. EUPM may use roads, bridges, canals and other waterways, port facilities and airports without payment of fees, tolls or other charges.
( 3) Die Aufnahmespartei erleichtert der EUPM den Betrieb ihrer eigenen Fahrzeuge und anderen Transportmittel. The host Party shall facilitate for EUPM the operation of its own vehicles and other means of transport.
( 1) Die EUPM und ihre Angehörigen haben zum Zweck der Ausübung ihrer Tätigkeit zu geringsten Kosten Zugang zu angemessenen Telekommunikationseinrichtungen, die der Aufnahmepartei gehören oder von ihr kontrolliwerden, auch zum Zweck der Kommunikation mit diplomatischen oder konsularischen Vertretern der Entsendeparteien. For the purpose of exercising their activities, the EUPM and its affiliates shall, at the lowest cost, have access to appropriate telecommunications facilities belonging to or controlled by the host party, including for the purpose of communicating with diplomatic or consular representatives of the posting parties.
( 2) Die EUPM und ihre Angehörigen haben das Recht auf unbeschränkte Kommunikation mit eigenen Funkgeräten (einschließlich Satelliten-, Mobil- und Handfunk geräte), Telefonen, Telegrafen, Faxgeräten oder anderen Mitteln. EUPM and its members shall have the right to communicate without restriction by means of their own radios (including satellite, mobile and hand-held radios), telephones, telegraphs, fax machines or other means.
The host Party shall provide, after signature of this Agreement, the frequencies on which radios may be operated.
( 1) Die Regierung von Bosnia und Herzegovina erklärt sich bereit, der EUPM auf Antrag bei der Suche nach geeigneten Bürorräumen und Unterkünfte behilflich zu sein. The Government of Bosnia and Herzegovina declares its readiness to assist EUPM, upon request, in the search for suitable offices and accommodation.
( 2) Soweit erforderlich, vereinbaren die teilnehmenden Parteien weitere Bestimmungen betreffend Vorrechte und Immunitäten sowie praktische Vorkehrungen, einschließlich notfallmedizinischer Versorgung und Emerfallevakuierung, der Benennung officieller Vertreter als Kontaktpartner sowie Anforderungen für Reisedokumente. Where necessary, the participating Parties shall agree on further provisions concerning privileges and immunities and practical arrangements, including emergency medical care and evacuation, the designation of official representatives as contact persons and requirements for travel documents.
This Agreement shall enter into force upon its signature.
It shall apply for the duration of the mandate of EUPM.
concerning the occasional international carriage of passengers by bus and coach
Aiming to promote the development of transboundary traffic in Europe and, in particular, to facilitate its organisation and implementation,
Seeking to facilitate tourism and cultural exchanges between the Parties,
The Convention on the International Occasional Carriage of Passengers by Bus and Coach (ASOR), signed in Dublin on 26 May 1982, does not contain any provisions for the accession of further Parties.
The experience gained with the abovementioned Agreement and the liberalization achieved should be preserved.
It is desirable to ensure harmonised liberalisation of certain occasional cross-border services by bus and coach and the associated transit services.
It is desirable to provide for certain harmonized procedural rules for non-liberalized occasional cross-border trade, which will continue to be subject to authorisation.
In the interests of road safety and environmental protection, it is necessary to provide for far-reaching harmonisation of the technical requirements imposed on vehicles engaged in occasional cross-border bus and coach traffic between the Contracting Parties.
It is necessary for the Contracting Parties to apply uniform rules with respect to the work of international road transport drivers of buses and coaches.
It is desirable to harmonize the conditions of access to the craft of passenger transport by road,
The principle of non-discrimination on the basis of nationality or place of business of the haulier and the country of origin or destination of the bus and coach shall be regarded as a basic requirement for the provision of transboundary services.
In order to facilitate and simplify control procedures it is necessary to provide for uniform models for accompanying documents such as the liberalised occasional trade control document and the authorisation and application form for non-liberalised trade.
Certain harmonized measures shall be provided for in order to enforce this Agreement, in particular as regards control procedures, penal provisions and mutual assistance.
In order to ensure the proper implementation of this Agreement and to permit some technical adjustment of the Annexes, it is appropriate to establish certain procedures for the management of the Agreement.
Accession to this Agreement should be open to all future Member States of the European Conference of Ministers of Transport and certain other European countries,
HAVE DECIDED to establish uniform rules for the occasional international carriage of passengers by bus and coach, and
( 1) Dieses Übereinkommen gilt für This Convention shall apply to:
( a) the international carriage by road of passengers of any nationality, on an occasional basis;
- between the territories of two Contracting Parties or to and from the territory of the same Contracting Party and, where necessary in the course of such operations, in transit through the territory of another Contracting Party or the territory of a State not party to this Agreement;
- transport operators operating on a rental or remuneration basis established in one of the Contracting Parties under its laws and authorised to carry occasional international coach and coach passengers;
- buses and coaches registered in the Contracting Party on whose territory the haulier is established;
( b) empty journeys of the buses and coaches used for such operations.
( 2) Keine der Bestimmungen dieses Übereinkommens darf dahin auszugelegt werden, daß sie den im Gebiet einer der Vertragsparteien niedergelassenen Transportunternehmern die Möglichkeit gewähren würde, nationale Casegenheitsverkehre im Hoheitsgebiet einer anderen Vertragspartei durchzuführen. None of the provisions of this Agreement may be interpreted as meaning that it would provide hauliers established in the territory of one of the Parties with the opportunity to conduct national occasional operations in the territory of another Party.
( 3) Die Verwendung von nach ihrer Bauart für den Pasentransport bestimmten Omnibussen für die Befuhr von Gütern für gewerbliche Zwecke ist vom Geltungsbereich dieses Übereinkommens ausgeschlossen. The use of buses designed for passenger transport for the transport of goods for commercial purposes is excluded from the scope of this Convention.
( 4) Dieses Übereinkommen betrifft nicht auf eigene Rechnung durchgeführte Casegenheitsverkehre. This Agreement does not relate to occasional traffic carried out for one <unk> s own account.
The Contracting Parties shall be obliged to ensure compliance with the principle of prohibition of any discrimination based on the nationality or place of business of the haulier or the country of origin or destination of the bus, in particular with respect to the fiscal provisions of Section VI and the control and penal provisions of Section IX.
For the purposes of this Agreement the following definitions shall apply:
1. <unk> buses <unk> shall mean motor vehicles suitable for their design and equipment and intended to carry more than nine persons including the driver.
2. <unk> Intra-frontier occasional services
The journeys made in the course of such traffic may be carried out with a certain frequency, without thereby losing the character of occasional traffic.
3. <unk> Liner Verkehr <unk> means the regular transport of persons on a particular transport connection, in which passengers may be picked up or dropped off at previously fixed stops.
Regular services may be subject to the obligation to follow timetables and fares fixed in advance.
4. als <unk> Sonderform des Linienverkehrs <unk> gilt - unabhängig davon, wer den Ablauf der Fahrt bestimmt - die Beförderung bestimmter Kategorien von Personen unter Ausschluss anderer Passagiere, soweit die in Nummer 3 genannten Merkmale gegeben sind. <unk> special form of regular services
- the transport of workers between home and place of work;
- the transport of pupils and students between their homes and educational establishments.
The regularity of such journeys and their classification as regular services shall not be affected by the adaptation of the itinerary to the needs of the users.
<unk> Shuttle transport <unk> means transport of persons previously grouped together on a number of return journeys between the same departure point and the same destination.
Each group of travellers, i.e. the persons who have made the outbound journey together, shall, on a later journey, be returned to their point of departure by the same haulier.
<unk> Place of departure <unk> and <unk> destination <unk> shall mean the places where the journey begins or ends, including their surroundings, within a radius of 50 km.
2. In the case of commuting, passengers shall not be accepted or dropped off en route.
3. Die erste Rückfahrt und die letzte Hinfahrt einer Reihe von Pendelfahrten sind Empty trips. The first return journey and the last outward journey of a series of shuttle journeys shall be empty journeys.
4. Die Einordnung eines Verkehrs als Pendelverkehr wird jedoch nicht berührt, daß mit Zustimmung der zuständigen Behörden in der betreffenden Vertragspartei oder in den betreffenden Vertragsparteien The classification of a traffic as a shuttle service shall not, however, be affected by the fact that, with the consent of the competent authorities in the Contracting Party concerned or in the Contracting Parties concerned,
- by way of derogation from paragraph 1, to make the return journey with another group of travellers or with another haulier;
- be taken in or dropped off en route in derogation from paragraph 2;
- by way of derogation from paragraph 3, the first return journey of a series of shuttle journeys shall be empty journeys.
<unk> Contracting Parties
This Agreement shall apply to the territories in which the Treaty establishing the European Community is applied and under the conditions laid down in that Treaty, and also to BOSNIA, HERZEGOVINA, BULGARIA, ESTONIA, CROATIA, LATVIA, LITHUANIA, the REPUBLIC OF MOLDAU, POLAND, ROMANIA, SLOVAKIA, SLOVENIA, the CZECH REPUBLIC, TURKEY and HUNGARY, to the extent that these countries have concluded this Agreement.
7. <unk> Competent authorities
8. <unk> Transit
( 1) Soweit noch nicht geschehen, erlassen die Vertragsparteien Vorschriften, die den Bestimmungen der im Anhang 1 genannten Richtlinie der Europäischen Gemeinschaft entsprechen. As far as is not already the case, the Contracting Parties shall adopt rules which comply with the provisions of the Directive of the European Community referred to in Annex 1.
( 2) Hinsichtlich der in Artikel 3 Absatz 3 jener Richtlinie genannten Anforderungen an die finanzielle Leistungsfähigkeit können die Vertragsparteien bis zum 1. Januar 2003 als nachprovsendes Minimkapital (einschließlich Reserven) einen geringeren als den in dem genannten Absatz 3 Buchstabe c) festgelegten Betrag vorsehen; unbeschadet der Bestimmungen des jeweiligen Europa-Abkommens zur Gründung einer Assoziation zwischen den Europäischen Gemeinschaften und ihren Mitgliedstaaten und bestimmten Vertragsparteien dieses Übereinkommens verlängert sich die genannte Frist bis zum 1. Januar 2005, wenn bei der Ratifizierung dieses Übereinkommens eine entsprechende Erklärung abgegeben wird. With respect to the financial capacity requirements referred to in Article 3 (3) of that Directive, the Contracting Parties may, by 1 January 2003, provide for a lesser amount than the amount specified in that paragraph (3) (c) of that Directive as a minimum capital requirement (including reserves) to be verified;
The buses and coaches used in occasional international traffic under this Agreement shall comply with the technical standards set out in Annex 2.
The following occasional operations carried out in the territory of a Contracting Party other than that in which the operator is established shall be exempt from the requirement of authorisation:
1. Rundfahrten <unk> mit geschlossenen Türen <unk>, d. h. Fahrt, die mit dem gleichen Omnibus ausführt werden, der die gleiche Reisegruppe über die gesamten Fahrtstrecke befördert und auf dem Ausgangsort zurückbringt. <unk> round trips
The place of departure shall be the territory of the Contracting Party in which the haulier is established.
2. transport of passengers on the outward journey with an empty return journey.
The place of departure shall be the territory of the Contracting Party in which the haulier is established.
3. Voyages with an empty outward journey, in which all passengers are accepted at the same place, provided that one of the following conditions is fulfilled:
( a) Passengers, in the territory of a non-Contracting Party or a Contracting Party which is not the home of the transport operator or the home of the passengers, shall constitute groups composed by contracts of carriage concluded before their arrival in the latter Contracting Party.
Passengers shall be brought to the territory of the Contracting Party in which the operator is established.
( b) Passengers have previously been brought to the territory of the Contracting Party by the same transport operator under the circumstances set out in paragraph 2 of this Article, in order to be transported to the territory of the Contracting Party in which the transport operator is established.
( c) Passengers have been invited to travel to the territory of another Contracting Party, the cost of the journey being borne by the inviting person.
Passengers shall be a homogeneous group, not constituted solely for the purpose of this journey and brought to the territory of the Contracting Party in which the operator is established.
The following journeys shall also be exempt from the requirement for authorisation:
4. Transitfahrten durch das Gebiet von Vertragsparteien im Zusammenhang mit genehmigungsfreie Casegenheitsverkehren. Transit journeys through the territory of Contracting Parties in connection with unauthorised occasional traffic.
5. Empty runs of buses and coaches intended solely to replace buses and coaches damaged or lost in a transboundary operation covered by this Agreement.
For journeys carried out by hauliers established in the European Community, the origin and / or destination of the journeys may be in any Member State of the European Community, irrespective of the Member State in which the coach is licensed or the haulier is established.
( 1) Für Casegenheitsverkehre, die nicht den in Artikel 6 genannten Bedingungen entsprechen, ist eine Genehmigung gemäß Artikel 15 erforderlich. An authorisation pursuant to Article 15 is required for occasional traffic which does not meet the conditions set out in Article 6.
( 2) Bei Verkehren, die von in der Europäischen Gemeinschaft niedergelassenen Verkehrsunternehmern ausgeführt werden, kann der Ausgangs- und/ oder Zielort des Verkehrs in jedem Mitgliedstaat der Europäischen Gemeinschaft liegen, unabhängig davon, in welcher Mitgliedstaat der Omnibus zugelassen oder der Verkehrsunternehmer niedergelassen ist. In the case of transport operations carried out by operators established in the European Community, the point of departure and / or destination of transport may be in any Member State of the European Community, irrespective of which Member State the bus is licensed or the operator is established.
The Contracting Parties to this Agreement shall accede, where not yet done, to the revised European Agreement on the Work of Mobile Personnel engaged in International Road Traffic (AETR) of 1 July 1970, or shall apply the version of Community Regulations (EEC) No 3820 / 85 and (EEC) No 3821 / 85 in force at the time of the entry into force of this Agreement.
( 1) Omnibusse used for journeys carried out in accordance with this Agreement shall be exempt from all vehicle taxes and taxes levied on the operation or ownership of vehicles and from all taxes and charges levied specifically on transport services in the territory of the other Contracting Parties.
This exemption for buses and coaches shall not apply to taxes and charges on fuels, VAT levied on transport services, road user charges and other charges levied by transport users for the use of infrastructure.
( 2) Die Vertragsparteien stellen sicher, daß Straßenusungsgebühren und andere von den Verkehrsnutzern zu zahlende Abgaben nicht gleichzeitig für das Befahren eines bestimmten Straßenabschnitts erhoben werden können. The Contracting Parties shall ensure that road use charges and other charges payable by road users cannot be levied simultaneously for driving on a particular section of road.
However, the Contracting Parties may levy charges on road networks on which user charges are payable for bridges, tunnels and mountain passes.
( 3) Der von den Omnibussen in den hierfür herstellerseitig vorgesehenen Behältern mitgeführte Kraftstoff bis zur Hoechstmenge von 600 l sowie die in den Fahrzeuge ausschließlich für Betriebszwecke befindlichen Schmierstoffe sind von allen in den anderen Vertragsparteien erhobenen Einfuhrzöllen und sonstigen Steuern und Abgaben befreit. The fuel carried by the buses in the containers provided for by the manufacturers for this purpose, up to the maximum volume of 600 litres, and the lubricants used in the vehicles exclusively for operating purposes, shall be exempt from all customs duties on imports and other taxes and charges levied in the other Contracting Parties.
( 4) Der nach Artikel 23 gebildete Gemeinsame Ausschuss erstellt eine Liste der in den einzelnen Vertragsparteien auf den Straßenpersonenverkehr mit Omnibussen erhobenen Steuern. The Joint Committee established pursuant to Article 23 shall draw up a list of taxes levied in each of the Contracting Parties on road passenger transport by bus and coach.
This list shall specify which taxes are covered by the provisions of the first subparagraph of paragraph 1 of this Article and can therefore only be levied in the Contracting Party in which the vehicle is registered.
In addition, the list shall specify which taxes are covered by the provisions of the second subparagraph of paragraph 1 of this Article and may therefore also be levied in Contracting Parties other than the Contracting Party in which the vehicle is registered.
Contracting Parties which replace one of the taxes on these lists with another equivalent or different tax shall inform the Joint Committee so that it may update the lists accordingly.
( 5) Die Ersatzteile und Werkzeuge für die Instandsetzung eines bei einer internationalen Verkehrsleistung Damdeten Omnibusses sind bei ihrer Einfuhr in das Gebiet der anderen Vertragspartei zu den in deren Bestimmungen für die vorübergehende Einfuhr solcher Gegenstände festgelegten Bedingungen von Einfuhrzöllen und allen Steuern und Abgaben befreit. Spare parts and tools for the repair of an omnibus damaged in an international traffic accident shall be exempt from customs duties on imports and all taxes and charges upon their entry into the territory of the other Contracting Party under the conditions laid down in the other Contracting Party <unk> s provisions for the temporary importation of such items.
The replaced parts shall be exported again or destroyed under the supervision of the competent customs authority of the other Contracting Party.
The operations referred to in Article 6 shall be carried out under a control document issued by the competent authorities or by another authorised authority of the Contracting Party in which the transport operator is established.
( 1) Das Kontrolldokument besteht aus severbaren Fahrtenblättern in doppelter Ausfertigung, die in Fahrtenheften zu je 25 Fahrtenblättern enthalten sind. The control document shall consist of detachable, duplicate sheets, each of which shall be contained in 25 sheets.
The control document shall conform to the model set out in Annex 3 to this Agreement.
( 2) Jedes Fahrtenheft und die in ihm enthaltenen Fahrtenblätter werden mit einer Kennnummer versehen. Each notebook and the sheets contained therein shall be provided with an identification number.
The individual sheets shall be additionally numbered from 1 to 25.
( 3) Der Text auf dem Deckblatt des Fahrtenheftes und auf den Fahrtenblättern wird in der Amtssprache oder in mehreren Amtssprachen der Vertragspartei gedruckt, in der der der Verkehrsunternehmer niedergelassen ist. The text on the cover of the booklet and on the travel sheets shall be printed in the official language or in several official languages of the Contracting Party in which the transport operator is established.
( 1) Das in Artikel 11 vorgesehene Fahrtenheft wird auf den Namen des Verkehrsunternehmers ausgestellt; es ist nicht übertragbar. The booklet provided for in Article 11 shall be issued in the name of the transport undertaking and shall not be transferable.
( 2) Das Original des Fahrtenblatt ist während der ganze Fahrt, für die es ausgestellt wurde, im Omnibus mitzführen. The original of the travel sheet shall be carried in the omnibus throughout the journey for which it has been issued.
( 3) Der Verkehrsunternehmer ist für die ordnungsgemäße Führung der Fahrtenblätter verantwortlich. The transport operator shall be responsible for the proper operation of the sheets.
( 1) Das Fahrtenblatt ist vom Verkehrsunternehmer für jede Fahrt vor deren Antritt in doppelter Ausfertigung auszufuellen. The travel sheet shall be duplicated by the haulier for each journey prior to its commencement.
( 2) Zur Angabe der Namen der Passagiere kann der Verkehrsunternehmer eine im Voraus auf einem gesonderten Blatt erstellte Liste verwenden, die dem Fahrtenblatt beizufügen ist. In order to specify the names of the passengers, the transport operator may use a list prepared in advance on a separate sheet, which shall be attached to the travel sheet.
The postmark of the transport operator and, where appropriate, the signatures of the transport operator and the coach driver shall be affixed both to this list and to the travel sheet.
( 3) Wenn die Hinfahrt gemäß Artikel 6 Absatz 3 als Emperfahrt erfolgt, kann die Liste der Passagiere zu den in Absatz 2 genannten Bedingungen zum Zeitpunkt der Aufnahme der Passagiere erstellt werden. If the outbound journey is an idle journey in accordance with Article 6 (3), the list of passengers may be drawn up on the terms and conditions set out in paragraph 2 of this Article at the time the passengers are admitted.
The competent authorities in two or more Contracting Parties may agree that the establishment of the passenger list is not necessary.
In this case, the number of passengers shall be specified in the control document.
The Joint Committee established in accordance with Article 23 shall be notified of such arrangements.
( 1) Genehmigungen für Casegenheitsverkehre, die nicht nach Artikel 6 liberalisiert sind, werden in gegenseitigem Einvernehmen zwischen den zuständigen Behörden der Vertragsparteien, in deren Gebiet Passagiere aufgenommen oder abgesetzt werden sollen, und den zuständigen Behörden der im Transit zu durchfahrenden Vertragsparteien erteilt. Approvals for occasional traffic not liberalized under Article 6 shall be issued by mutual agreement between the competent authorities of the Contracting Parties in whose territory passengers shall be admitted or disembarked and the competent authorities of the Contracting Parties to be transited.
If both the point of departure and the point of destination of the journey are in a Member State of the European Community, transit through other Member States of the Community is not subject to authorisation.
( 2) Die Genehmigung entspricht dem in Anhang 5 wiedergegebenen Muster. The approval shall be in accordance with the model set out in Annex 5.
( 1) Der Antrag auf Genehmigung ist vom Verkehrsunternehmer an die zuständigen Behörden der Vertragspartei zu richten, in deren Gebiet der Ausgangsort liegt. The request for authorisation shall be made by the transport operator to the competent authorities of the Contracting Party in whose territory the place of departure is.
The application form shall comply with the model set out in Annex 4.
( 2) Dem vom Verkehrsunternehmer auszufuellenden Antrag ist der Nachweis beizufügen, daß der Antragsteller die in Artikel 1 Absatz 1 Buchstabe a) zweiten Gedankenstrich genannte Erlaubnis zur Befuhr von Fahrgästen im grenzüberschreitenden Gelegenheitsverkehr mit Omnibussen besitzt. The request to be completed by the transport operator shall be accompanied by evidence that the applicant possesses the permit referred to in Article 1 (1) (a), second indent, for the carriage of passengers in occasional cross-border coach and coach services.
( 3) Die zuständigen Behörden der Vertragspartei, in deren Gebiet der Ausgangsort liegt, prüfen den Antrag auf Genehmigung des betreffenden Verkehrsdienst und leiten ihn im Genehmigungsfall weiter an die zuständigen Behörden der Vertragsparteien <unk> en), in deren Gebiet<unk> en) der oder die Zielort<unk> e) liegt, liegen, sowie an die zuständigen Behörden der im Transit zu durchfahrenden Vertragsparteien. The competent authorities of the Contracting Party in whose territory the place of departure is, shall examine the request for the approval of the transport service concerned and, in the case of approval, forward the request to the competent authorities of the Contracting Parties in whose territories (s) the place of departure is, or are, and to the competent authorities of the Contracting Parties in transit.
( 4) Abweichend von Artikel 15 Absatz 1 können Vertragsparteien, deren Gebiete im Transit durchfahren werden, beschließen, daß ihre Zustimmung zu den in diesem Abschnitt behandelten Verkehren nicht mehr erforderlich ist. In derogation from Article 15 (1), Contracting Parties whose areas are to be transited may decide that their consent to the operations referred to in this paragraph is no longer required.
Such a decision shall be notified to the Joint Committee established in accordance with Article 23.
( 5) Die zuständigen Behörden der Vertragsparteien <unk> en), deren Zustimmung Antrag wurde, erteilen die Genehmigung innerhalb eines Monats, und zwar ohne Diskriminierung aufgrund der Nationgehörigkeit oder des Geschäftssitz der Verkehrsunternehmers. The competent authorities of the Contracting Parties whose consent has been requested shall grant the authorisation within one month, without discrimination on the basis of nationality or place of business of the transport undertakings.
If such authorities do not agree to the conditions of the authorisation, they shall inform the competent authorities of the Contracting Parties concerned, stating the relevant reasons.
The competent authorities of two or more Contracting Parties may agree to simplify the authorisation procedure, the model of the application for authorisation and the model of authorisation for occasional traffic between them.
Such an arrangement shall be notified to the Joint Committee established in accordance with Article 23.
The control document provided for in Article 10 and the authorisations provided for in Article 15 shall be carried in an omnibus and presented to the inspecting officials on request.
The competent authorities in the Contracting Parties shall take the necessary measures to ensure that operators comply with the provisions of this Agreement.
An officially certified copy of the authorisation referred to in Article 1 (1) (a), second indent, for the carriage of occasional international bus and coach passengers shall be carried on the bus and provided upon request to the controlling officials.
The Joint Committee established in accordance with Article 23 shall be provided with samples of such documents issued by the competent authorities of the Contracting Parties.
The competent authorities of the Contracting Parties shall establish a system of penalties for violations of this Convention.
The penalties provided therein shall be effective, proportionate and dissuasive.
( 1) Wenn ein nicht ansässiger Verkehrsunternehmer schweren oder repeated Verstöße gegen die Straßenverkehrsvorschriften, insbesondere gegen die Bestimmungen über Fahr- und Ruhhezeiten und die Sicherheit im Straßenverkehr begangen hat, die zum Entzug der Erlaubnis zur Ausübung des Berufs eines Personenverkehrsunternehmers führen könnten, übermitteln die zuständigen Behörden der betreffenden Vertragspartei den zuständigen Behörden der Vertragspartei, in der der der Verkehrsunternehmer niedergelassen ist, alle in ihrem Besitz befindlichen Informationen über diese Verstöße und über die gegen ihn verhängten Strafen. If a non-resident haulage operator has committed serious or repeated violations of the road transport legislation, in particular of the provisions relating to driving and rest times and road safety which could result in the withdrawal of a passenger transport operator <unk> s occupation permit, the competent authorities of the Contracting Party concerned shall communicate to the competent authorities of the Contracting Party in which the haulage
( 2) Die zuständigen Behörden der Vertragspartei, in deren Gebiet die schweren oder wiederholte Verstöße gegen die Straßenverkehrsvorschriften, insbesondere gegen die Bestimmungen über Fahr- und Ruhhezeiten und die Sicherheit im Straßenverkehr begangen wurden, können dem betreffenden Verkehrsunternehmer vorübergehend den Zugang zum Gebiet dieser Vertragspartei verweigern. The competent authorities of the Contracting Party in whose territory the serious or repeated violations of the Road Traffic Regulations, in particular of the provisions relating to driving and rest periods and road safety, have been committed may, on a temporary basis, refuse access to the territory of that Contracting Party to the transport operator concerned.
Within the European Community, the competent authorities of a Member State may refuse access to that Member State only on a temporary basis.
Such measures shall be notified to the competent authorities of the Contracting Party in which the haulier is established and to the Joint Committee established in accordance with Article 23.
( 3) Wenn ein Verkehrsunternehmer schweren oder wiederholte Verstöße gegen die Straßenverkehrsvorschriften, insbesondere gegen die Bestimmungen über Fahr- und Ruhhezeiten und die Sicherheit im Straßenverkehr begangen hat, treffen die zuständigen Behörden der Vertragsparteien, in der der Verkehrsunternehmer niedergelassen ist, geeignete Maßnahmen, um eine Wiederholung derartiger Verstöße zu vermeiden; diese Maßnahmen können in der Aussetzung oder dem Entzug der Erlaubnis zur Ausübung des Berufs eines Personenverkehrsunternehmers bestehen. If a transport operator has committed serious or repeated violations of the road transport regulations, in particular of the provisions relating to driving and rest periods and road safety, the competent authorities of the Contracting Parties, in which the transport operator is established, shall take appropriate measures to avoid a repeat of such violations; such measures may include suspension or withdrawal of a passenger transport operator <unk> s licence.
Such action shall be notified to the Joint Committee established in accordance with Article 23.
( 4) Die Vertragsparteien garantieren den Verkehrsunternehmern das Recht, gegen die verhängten Strafmaßnahmen Rechtsmittel einzulegen. The Contracting Parties shall guarantee the right of carriers to bring legal proceedings against the penalties imposed.
( 1) Zur Erleichterung der Durchführung dieses Übereinkommens wird hermit ein Gemeinsamer Ausschuss gebildet. To facilitate the implementation of this Agreement, a Joint Committee shall be formed hereby.
This Committee shall be composed of representatives of the Contracting Parties.
( 2) Der Gemeinsame Ausschuss hält innerhalb von sechs Monaten nach Inkrafttreten dieses Übereinkommens eine erste Sitzung ab. The Joint Committee shall hold its first meeting within six months of the entry into force of this Agreement.
( 3) Der Gemeinsame Ausschuss gibt sich eine Geschäftsordnung. The Joint Committee shall adopt its own rules of procedure.
( 4) Der Gemeinsame Ausschuss tritt auf Verlangen mindestens einer Vertragspartei zusammen. The Joint Committee shall meet on the request of at least one Contracting Party.
( 5) Der Gemeinsame Ausschuss fasst Beschlüsse nur, wenn zwei Drittel der Vertragsparteien, darunter die Europäische Gemeinschaft, in den Sitzungen des Gemeinsamen Ausschusses vertreten sind. The Joint Committee shall take decisions only if two thirds of the Contracting Parties, including the European Community, are represented in the meetings of the Joint Committee.
( 6) Für die von dem Gemeinsamen Ausschuss zu fassenden Beschlüsse ist die Einstimmigkeit der vertretenen Vertragsparteien erforderlich. Decisions to be taken by the Joint Committee shall require the unanimity of the Parties represented.
If this unanimity cannot be reached, the competent authorities shall meet for consultations within six weeks at the request of one or more of the Contracting Parties concerned.
( 1) Der Gemeinsame Ausschuss sorgt für die ordnungsgemäße Durchführung dieses Übereinkommens. The Joint Committee shall ensure the proper implementation of this Agreement.
The Committee shall be informed of any measures taken or intended to be taken to implement the provisions of this Agreement.
( 2) Der Gemeinsame Ausschuss soll insbesondere The Joint Committee shall, in particular:
( a) draw up, on the basis of information provided to it by the Contracting Parties, a list of the competent authorities of the Contracting Parties for the functions referred to in paragraphs V, VI, VII, VIII and IX;
( b) modify or adapt the control documents and other models reproduced in the Annexes to this Convention;
( c) amend or adapt the Annexes to the technical standards to be applied to buses and coaches and to Annex 1 to the requirements applicable to passenger transport operators in accordance with Article 4 in order to take into account future measures adopted within the European Community;
( d) draw up, on the basis of information provided by the Contracting Parties, a list of customs duties, taxes and charges referred to in Article 9 (4) and (5);
( e) modify or adapt the social requirements referred to in Article 8 in order to take into account future measures adopted within the European Community;
( f) resolve any disputes which may arise concerning the implementation and interpretation of this Convention;
( g) propose further steps to liberalize the occasional traffic which remains subject to authorisation.
( 3) Die Vertragsparteien treffen die notwendigen Maßnahmen, um die Beschlüsse des Gemeinsamen Ausschusses nötigenfalls entsprechend ihren jeweiligen internen Verfahrensweisen Umsetzung. The Contracting Parties shall take the necessary steps to implement the decisions of the Joint Committee in accordance with their respective internal procedures.
( 4) Wenn zu einer Streitfrage gemäß Absatz 2 Buchstabe f) dieses Artikels keine Einigkeit erzielt werden kann, können die betroffenen Vertragsparteien den Fall einem Schiedsgericht vorlegen. If no agreement can be reached on a dispute under paragraph 2 (f) of this Article, the Contracting Parties concerned may submit the case to an arbitral tribunal.
Each of the Contracting Parties concerned shall designate a member of the arbitral tribunal.
The Joint Committee itself shall also designate a member of that arbitral tribunal.
The arbitrators shall make a majority decision.
The Contracting Parties concerned by the dispute shall take the necessary measures to implement the decision of the arbitral tribunal.
( 1) Die Bestimmungen dieses Übereinkommens ersetzt die einschlägigen Bestimmungen der zwischen einzelnen Vertragsparteien geschlossenen Übereinkommen. The provisions of this Agreement shall replace the relevant provisions of the agreements concluded between the Parties.
In the case of the European Community, this also applies to agreements between individual Member States and other Contracting Parties.
( 2) Einzelne Vertragsparteien mit Ausnahme der Europäischen Gemeinschaft können vereinbaren, auf Omnibusse, die im Casegenheitsverkehr zwischen ihren Gebieten und bei Transitfahrten durch ihre Gebiete eingesetzt werden, anstelle von Artikel 5 und Anhang 2 dieses Übereinkommens andere technische Normen anzuwenden. Individual Contracting Parties, with the exception of the European Community, may agree to apply other technical standards in place of Article 5 and Annex 2 of this Agreement to buses and coaches used in occasional traffic between their territories and on transit journeys through their territories.
( 3) Unbeschadet der Bestimmungen von Anhang 2 Artikel 6 ersetzen die Bestimmungen dieses Übereinkommens die einschlägigen Bestimmungen der zwischen den Mitgliedstaaten der Europäischen Gemeinschaft und anderen Vertragsparteien abgeschlossenen Übereinkommen. Without prejudice to the provisions of Annex 2 to Article 6, the provisions of this Agreement shall replace the relevant provisions of the Agreements concluded between the Member States of the European Community and other Contracting Parties.
However, the provisions concerning exemptions from authorisation contained in existing bilateral agreements between Member States of the European Community and other Contracting Parties on occasional trade under Article 7 may be maintained and renewed.
In such a case, the Contracting Parties concerned shall promptly inform the Joint Committee established in accordance with Article 23.
This Agreement shall be opened for signature in Brussels from 14 April 2000 to 30 June 2001 at the General Secretariat of the Council of the European Union, which shall act as the depositary for this Agreement.
This Convention shall be approved or ratified by the signatory Parties in accordance with their respective rules of procedure.
Instruments of approval or ratification shall be deposited with the General Secretariat of the Council of the European Union, which shall notify all other signatories accordingly.
( 1) Dieses Übereinkommen tritt für diejenigen Vertragsparteien, die es genehmigt oder ratifiziert haben, in Kraft, nachdem es von insgesamt vier Vertragsparteien, darunter die Europäische Gemeinschaft, genehmigt oder ratifiziert wurde; das Inkrafttreten erfolgt am ersten Tag des dritten auf das Datum der Hinterlegung der 4. Genehmigungs- oder Ratifizierungsurkunde folgenden Monats oder, wenn zum Zeitpunkt der Ratifizierung des Übereinkommens eine entsprechende Erklärung abgegeben wurde, erst am ersten Tag des 6. Monats. This Convention shall enter into force for those Contracting Parties which have approved or ratified it after it has been approved or ratified by a total of four Contracting Parties, including the European Community, and shall enter into force on the first day of the third month following the date of deposit of the fourth instrument of approval or ratification, or, if, at the time of the ratification of the Convention a declaration has been made, on the first day
( 2) Für Vertragsparteien, die dieses Übereinkommen nach dessen Inkrafttreten gemäß Absatz 1 genehmigen oder ratifizieren, tritt es am ersten Tag des dritten Monats in Kraft, der auf den Tag folgt, an dem die betreffende Vertragspartei ihre Genehmigungs- oder Ratifizierungsurkunde hinterlegt. For Contracting Parties which approve or ratify this Agreement after its entry into force in accordance with paragraph 1 of this Article, it shall enter into force on the first day of the third month following the date on which that Contracting Party deposits its instrument of approval or ratification.
Duration of the Convention - Assessment of its effectiveness
( 1) Dieses Übereinkommen wird für einen Zeitraum von fünf Jahren geschlossen, der mit seinem Inkrafttreten beginnt. This Convention shall be concluded for a period of five years commencing with its entry into force.
( 2) Die Laufzeit dieses Übereinkommens wird für diejenigen Vertragsparteien, die sich nicht dagegen aussprechen, automatisch um weitere Zeiträume von jeweils fünf Jahren verlängert. The term of this Agreement shall be automatically extended by further periods of five years each for those Contracting Parties which do not object.
Contracting Parties which do not wish to renew the Agreement shall notify the depositary body in accordance with the procedure laid down in Article 31.
( 3) Vor Ablauf eines jeden Fünfjahreszeitraums erstellt der Gemeinsame Ausschuss eine Bewertung der Wirksamkeit dieses Übereinkommens. Before the end of each five year period, the Joint Committee shall prepare an assessment of the effectiveness of this Agreement.
( 1) Nach dem Inkrafttreten ist dieses Übereinkommen offen für den Beitritt von Ländern, die Vollmitglieder der Europäischen Konferenz der Verkehrsminister (CEMT) sind. Upon entry into force, this Agreement shall be open to the accession of countries that are full members of the European Conference of Ministers of Transport (CEMT).
In the event of the accession of countries which are members of the Agreement on the European Economic Area, this Agreement shall not apply to trade between the Contracting Parties to the Agreement on the European Economic Area.
( 2) Dieses Übereinkommen ist auch offen für den Beitritt der Republik San Marino, des Fürstentums Andorra und des Fürstentums Monaco. This Convention shall also be open to the accession of the Republic of San Marino, the Principality of Andorra and the Principality of Monaco.
( 3) Für jeden diesem Übereinkommen nach dessen Inkrafttreten gemäß Artikel 28 beitretenden Staat tritt es am ersten Tag des dritten Monats in Kraft, der auf die Hinterlegung der Beitrittsurkunde dieses Staates folgt. For each State acceding to this Agreement after its entry into force in accordance with Article 28 of this Agreement, it shall enter into force on the first day of the third month following the deposit of that State <unk> s instrument of accession.
( 4) Jedem diesem Übereinkommen nach dessen Inkrafttreten gemäß Artikel 28 beitretenden Staat kann für die Einführung von Bestimmungen, die der der (den) in Anhang 1 genannten Richtlinie<unk> n) entsprechen, ein Zeitraum von höchstens drei Jahren eingeräumt werden. Any State acceding to this Agreement after its entry into force in accordance with Article 28 may be granted a period of not more than three years for the introduction of provisions equivalent to those referred to in Annex 1.
The Joint Committee shall be informed of the measures taken.
Either Contracting Party may denounce this Agreement for itself by simultaneously notifying the other Contracting Parties through the depositary body of the Agreement, subject to one year <unk> s notice.
The Joint Committee shall also be informed of the reasons for the denunciation.
However, for the first four years after its entry into force in accordance with Article 28, denunciation of this Agreement shall not be possible.
If the Agreement has been denounced by one or more Contracting Parties and the number of Contracting Parties falls below the minimum agreed for its initial entry into force in accordance with Article 28, the Agreement shall remain in force, unless the Joint Committee comprising the remaining Contracting Parties decides otherwise.
A Contracting Party acceding to the European Union shall cease to be a Contracting Party as from the date of such accession.
