ROTTERDAMER AGREEMENT ON THE PROCEDURE OF PREVIOUS AGREEMENT FOR CERTAIN DANGEROUS CHEMICALS AND PESTICIAL INTERNATIONAL TRADE
Aware of the effects of certain hazardous chemicals and pesticides on human health and the environment,
Recalling the relevant provisions of the Rio Declaration on Environment and Development and of Chapter 19 of Agenda 21 <unk> Environmentally sound management of toxic chemicals, including measures to prevent illegal international trade in toxic and hazardous products <unk>,
Recognising the work carried out by the United Nations Environment Programme (UNEP) and the Food and Agriculture Organisation (FAO) of the United Nations in applying the Prior Informed Consent (PIC) voluntary procedure, as set out in UNEP <unk> s amended London Guidelines for the Exchange of Information on Chemicals in International Trade (hereinafter referred to as <unk> the London Guidelines <unk>) and in FAO <unk> s International Code of Conduct on the Marketing and Use of Pesticides (hereinafter referred to as <unk> the International Code of Conduct <unk>),
Bearing in mind the realities and specific needs of developing countries and countries with transition economies, and in particular the need to strengthen national competences and capacities for handling chemicals, including through technology transfer, provision of financial and technical assistance and promotion of cooperation between the Parties,
Considering the specific information needs of certain countries concerning transit traffic,
Recognising that good practice in the handling of chemicals should be promoted in all countries, taking into account, inter alia, the voluntary standards set out in the International Code of Conduct and in the UNEP Code of Ethics on International Trade in Chemicals,
Guided by the desire to ensure that hazardous chemicals exported from their territories are packaged and labelled in such a way as to ensure adequate protection of human health and the environment, in accordance with the principles of the revised London Guidelines and the International Code of Conduct,
Recognising that trade and environmental policies should complement each other with a view to sustainable development,
Emphasizing that this Agreement shall not be interpreted as implying in any way an amendment of the rights and obligations of a Contracting Party under applicable international conventions on chemicals in international trade or for the protection of the environment,
provided that the foregoing motivations are not intended to establish a hierarchy between this Convention and other international conventions,
Determined to protect health, including the health of consumers and workers, and the environment, from the potentially harmful effects of certain hazardous chemicals and pesticides in international trade,
The objective of this Agreement is to promote joint responsibility and joint efforts by the Contracting Parties in international trade in certain hazardous chemicals with a view to protecting health and the environment from potential harm and to contribute to their environmentally sound use by facilitating the exchange of information on the characteristics of such chemicals, by establishing a domestic decision making process for their import and export and by transmitting such decisions to the Contracting Parties.
( a) <unk> Chemicals
These categories include: pesticides (including particularly hazardous pesticide formulations) and industrial chemicals;
( b) <unk> prohibited chemicals
It includes chemicals for which authorisation has been refused for their initial use or which have been withdrawn from the market by industry either domestically or which have been excluded from further consideration in the national authorisation process, provided that it is clear that these measures have been taken for reasons of public health or environmental protection;
( c) <unk> chemicals subject to strict restrictions
It includes chemicals which have been refused authorisation for their use for virtually all purposes or which have been withdrawn from the market by industry either domestically or have been excluded from further consideration in the national authorisation process, provided that it is clear that these measures have been taken for reasons of public health or environmental protection;
( d) <unk> particularly hazardous pesticide formulations
( e) <unk> directly applicable legislation
( f) <unk> export
( g) <unk> Contracting Party
( h) <unk> regional economic integration organisation
( i) <unk> Chemicals Testing Committee
( 1) Dieses Übereinkommen findet Anwendung auf: This Convention shall apply to:
( a) chemicals subject to prohibitions or strict restrictions; and
( 2) Dieses Übereinkommen findet keine Anwendung auf: This Convention shall not apply to:
( a) Narcotic drugs and psychotropic substances;
( e) pharmaceutical products, including medicinal products for humans and animals;
( f) chemicals used as food additives;
( h) Chemicals in quantities so small that there is no risk of harm to human health or the environment, provided that they are imported for the following reasons:
( i) for research or analysis purposes, or
( ii) by an individual for his own personal use in quantities appropriate for such purpose.
( 1) Jede Vertragspartei bezeichnet eine oder mehrere nationale Behörden, die befugt sind, in ihrem Namen zu handeln und die nach diesem Übereinkommen erforderlichen Verwaltungsaufgaben wahrzunehmen. Each Contracting Party shall designate one or more national authorities empowered to act on its behalf and perform the administrative functions required under this Agreement.
( 2) Jede Vertragspartei bemüht sich zu gewährleisten, daß dieser Behörde oder diesen Behörden ausreichende Mittel zur wirksamen Erfuellung ihrer Aufgaben zur Verfügung stehen. Each Contracting Party shall endeavour to ensure that this authority or these authorities have sufficient resources available for the effective fulfilment of its functions.
( 3) Jede Vertragspartei teilt dem Sekretariat spätestens bis zum Tag des Inkrafttretens des Übereinkommens für diese Vertragspartei Namen und Anschrift dieser Behörde <unk> n) mit. Each Contracting Party shall notify the Secretariat, not later than the date of entry into force of the Convention, of the name and address of such Contracting Party.
It shall also promptly inform the Secretariat of any change in the name or address of such authorities.
( 4) Das Sekretariat setzt die Vertragsparteien unverzüglich über die gemäß Absatz 3 bei ihm eingegangenen Mitteilungen in Kenntnis. The Secretariat shall inform the Contracting Parties immediately of the notifications received pursuant to paragraph 3 of this Article.
( 1) Jede Vertragspartei, die eine unmittelbar geltende Rechtsvorschrift erlassen hat, notifiziert diese dem Sekretariat schriftlich. Any Contracting Party which has adopted a directly applicable legal provision shall notify the Secretariat thereof in writing.
This notification shall be made as soon as possible but not later than 90 days after the date on which the directly applicable legislation has entered into force and shall, where available, provide the information required by Annex I.
( 2) Jede Vertragspartei notifiziert dem Sekretariat zum Zeitpunkt des Inkrafttretens dieses Übereinkommens für diese Vertragspartei schriftlich ihre zu diesem Zeitpunkt unmittelbar geltenden Rechtsvorschriften, wobei Vertragsparteien, die bereits aufgrund der geänderten Londoner Leitlinien oder des Internationalen Verhaltenkodex unmittelbar geltende Rechtsvorschriften notifiziert haben, diese Notifikationen nicht erneut vorlegen müssen. Each Contracting Party shall notify the Secretariat in writing, at the time of the entry into force of this Agreement, of its legislation directly applicable to that Contracting Party at that date, whereby Contracting Parties which have already notified directly applicable legislation as a result of the amended London Guidelines or the International Code of Conduct shall not have to submit such notifications again.
( 3) Das Sekretariat prüft so bald wie möglich, spätestens jedoch sechs Monate nach Eingang einer Notifikation nach den Absätzen 1 und 2, ob die meldung die gemäß Anlage I erforderlichen Informationen enthält. Ist dies der Fall, übermittelt das Sekretariat allen Vertragsparteien unverzüglich eine Zusammenfassung der ihm zugeleiteten Informationen. If this is the case, the secretariat shall communicate to all Contracting Parties without delay a summary of the information provided to it.
If the notification does not contain the necessary information, the secretariat shall notify the notifying Party accordingly.
( 4) Das Sekretariat übermittelt den Vertragsparteien alle sechs Monate eine Brief Zusammenfassung der ihr aufgrund der Absätze 1 und 2 zugeleiteten Informationen, einschließlich Informationen über diejenigen Notifikationen, die nicht alle nach Anlage I erforderlichen Informationen enthalten. The Secretariat shall, every six months, provide the Contracting Parties with a brief summary of the information provided to it pursuant to paragraphs 1 and 2 of this Article, including information on notifications which do not contain all the information required in accordance with Annex I.
( 5) Sobald das Sekretariat aus zwei PIC-Regionen mindestens je eine Notifikation zu einer bestimmten Chemikalie erhalten hat, die nachweislich die Anforderungen der Anlage I erfuellt, leitet es diese Notifikationen an den Chemikalienprüfungsausschuss weiter. As soon as the secretariat, consisting of two PIC-Regions, has received at least one notification each of a particular chemical which verifiably meets the requirements of Annex I, it shall forward such notifications to the Chemical Testing Committee.
The composition of the PIC regions shall be decided upon by consensus at the first meeting of the Conference of the Parties.
( 6) Der Chemikalienprüfungsausschuss überprüft die in diesen Notifikationen enthaltenen Informationen und übermittelt der Konferenz der Vertragsparteien in Übereinstimmung mit den in Anlage II niedergelegten Kriterien Empfehlungen im Hinblick darauf, ob die betreffende Chemikalie dem Verfahren der vorherige Zustimmung nach Inkenntnissetzung unterliegen und demententsprechend in Anlage III aufgenommen werden soll. The Chemical Testing Committee shall review the information contained in such notifications and, in accordance with the criteria laid down in Annex II, shall make recommendations to the Conference of the Parties as to whether the chemicals concerned are subject to the prior informed consent procedure and should be included accordingly in Annex III.
( 1) Vertragsparteien, die Entwicklungsländer sind oder deren Wirtschaftssystem sich im Übergang befindet und in deren Hoheitsgebiet eine besonders gefährliche Pestizidformulierung unter Anwendungsbedingungen Probleme verursacht, können dem Sekretariat die Aufnahme dieser Pestizidformulierung in Anlage III vorschlagen. Contracting Parties which are developing countries or whose economies are in transition and in whose territory are causing problems with particularly hazardous pesticide formulation under application conditions may propose to the Secretariat the inclusion of this pesticide formulation in Annex III.
For the preparation of a proposal, the Contracting Party may seek technical assistance from any relevant source.
The proposal shall also contain the information required by Annex IV, Part 1.
( 2) Das Sekretariat prüft so bald wie möglich, spätestens jedoch sechs Monate nach Eingang eines Vorschlag nach Absatz 1, ob der Vorschlag die nach Anlage IV Teil 1 erforderlichen Informationen enthält. The Secretariat shall consider as soon as possible, but not later than six months after the receipt of a proposal in accordance with paragraph 1, whether the proposal contains the information required in accordance with Annex IV, Part 1.
If this is the case, the Secretariat shall promptly provide all Contracting Parties with a summary of the information provided to it.
If the proposal does not provide the necessary information, the secretariat shall notify the proposing Contracting Party accordingly.
( 3) Das Sekretariat sammelt die in Anlage IV Teil 2 vorgesehenen zusätzliche Informationen zu den nach Absatz 2 übermittelten Vorschläge. The Secretariat shall collect the additional information provided for in Annex IV, Part 2, to the proposals referred to in paragraph 2.
( 4) Sind die Anforderungen der Absätze 2 und 3 im Hinblick auf eine bestimmte besonders gefährliche Pestizidformulierung erfuellt worden, leitet das Sekretariat den Vorschlag und die dazugehörigen Informationen an den Chemikalienprüfungsausschuss weiter. If the requirements of paragraphs 2 and 3 of this Article have been met with regard to a particular particularly hazardous formulation of pesticides, the Secretariat shall forward the proposal and the relevant information to the Chemical Testing Committee.
( 5) Der Chemikalienprüfungsausschuss überprüft die in dem Vorschlag enthaltenen Informationen und die gesammelten zusätzliche Informationen und übermittelt der Konferenz der Vertragsparteien in Übereinstimmung mit den in Anlage IV Teil 3 niedergelegten Kriterien Empfehlungen im Hinblick darauf, ob die betreffende besonders gefährliche Pestizidformulierung dem Verfahren der vorherige Zustimmung nach Inkenntnissetzung unterliegt und demententsprechend in Anlage III aufgenommen werden soll. The Chemical Testing Committee shall review the information contained in the proposal and the additional information collected and, in accordance with the criteria laid down in Annex IV, Part 3, shall make recommendations to the Conference of the Parties as to whether the particularly hazardous pesticide formulation in question is subject to prior informed consent and should be included accordingly in Annex III.
( 1) Für jede Chemikalie, in deren Fall der Chemikalienprüfungsausschuss entschieden hat, sie für die Aufnahme in Anlage III zu empfehlen, arbeitet er einen Entwurf für ein Dokument zur Unterstützung des Entscheidungsprozesses aus. For each chemical in whose case the Chemical Assessment Committee has decided to recommend it for inclusion in Annex III, it shall draw up a draft document in support of the decision process.
The document in support of the decision making process should be based at least on the information contained in Annex I and Annex IV, respectively, and should also include information on uses of the chemical in a category other than that referred to by the directly applicable legislation.
( 2) Die in Absatz 1 bezeichnete Empfehlung wird zusammen mit dem Entwurf des Dokuments zur Unterstützung des Entscheidungsprozesses der Konferenz der Vertragsparteien zugeleitet. The recommendation referred to in paragraph 1 of this Article shall be transmitted together with the draft document in support of the decision making process to the Conference of the Parties.
The Conference of the Parties shall decide whether the chemical should be subject to the prior informed consent procedure and shall, accordingly, include the chemical in Annex III and approve the draft document in support of the decision making process.
( 3) Ist eine Entscheidung über die Aufnahme einer Chemikalie in Anlage III getroffen und das dazugehörige Dokument zur Unterstützung des Entscheidungsprozesses von der Konferenz der Vertragsparteien genehmigt worden, gibt das Sekretariat diese Informationen unverzüglich an alle Vertragsparteien weiter. Where a decision to include a chemical in Annex III has been taken and the relevant document in support of the decision making process has been approved by the Conference of the Parties, the secretariat shall promptly forward such information to all Parties.
Chemicals under the voluntary prior informed consent procedure
For all chemicals incorporated before the first session of the Conference of the Parties into the voluntary prior informed consent procedure, except those listed in Annex III, the Conference of the Parties at that meeting shall decide to include them in Annex III, provided that it is satisfied that all the requirements for inclusion in that Annex have been fulfilled.
( 1) Legt eine Vertragspartei dem Sekretariat Informationen vor, die beim Zeitpunkt der Entscheidung über die Aufnahme einer Chemikalie in Anlage III noch nicht zur Verfügung standen, und geht aus diesen Informationen hervorkunft, daß der Verbleib dieser Chemikalie in Anlage III nach den einschlägigen Kriterien in Anlage II bzw. Anlage IV nicht mehr JustiJustiJustiJustiJustitigt ist, so leitet das Sekretariat die Informationen an den Chemikalienprüfungsausschuss weiter. Where a Contracting Party provides to the Secretariat information which was not available at the time of the decision to include a chemical in Annex III, and where such information indicates that the whereabouts of that chemical in Annex III is no longer justified in accordance with the relevant criteria in Annex II or Annex IV, the Secretariat shall forward the information to the Chemical Testing Committee.
( 2) Der Chemikalienprüfungsausschuss überprüft die ihm nach Absatz 1 zugeleiteten Informationen. The Chemical Testing Committee shall review the information provided to it in accordance with paragraph 1 of this Article.
For each chemical in whose case it has decided, in accordance with the relevant criteria in Annex II or Annex IV, to recommend its removal from Annex III, it shall draw up an amended draft document in support of the decision making process.
( 3) Eine Empfehlung nach Absatz 2 wird der Konferenz der Vertragsparteien zusammen mit dem geänderten Entwurf des Dokuments zur Unterstützung des Entscheidungsprozesses zugeleitet. A recommendation in accordance with paragraph 2 of this Article shall be forwarded to the Conference of the Parties together with the amended draft of the document in support of the decision making process.
The Conference of the Parties shall decide whether to delete the chemical from Annex III and approve the amended draft document in support of the decision making process.
( 4) Ist eine Entscheidung über die Streiung einer Chemikalie aus Anlage III getroffen und das dazugehörige geänderte Dokument zur Unterstützung des Entscheidungsprozesses von der Konferenz der Vertragsparteien genehmigt worden, gibt das Sekretariat diese Informationen unverzüglich an alle Vertragsparteien weiter. If a decision to delete a chemical from Annex III has been taken and the relevant amended document in support of the decision making process has been approved by the Conference of the Parties, the secretariat shall immediately forward this information to all Parties.
Obligations in respect of imports of chemicals listed in Annex III
( 1) Jede Vertragspartei erlässt geeignete Rechts- bzw. Verwaltungsvorschriften, um eine frühzeitige Entscheidung über die Einfuhr von in Anlage III aufgenommenen Chemikalien zu gewährleisten. Each Contracting Party shall adopt appropriate laws and regulations to ensure an early decision on the importation of chemicals listed in Annex III.
( 2) Jede Vertragspartei übermittelt dem Sekretariat so bald wie möglich, spätestens jedoch neun Monate nach Absendung des in Artikel 7 Absatz 3 bezeichneten Dokuments zur Unterstützung des Entscheidungsprozesses, eine Antwort im Hinblick auf die künftige Einfuhr der betreffenden Chemikalie. Each Contracting Party shall, as soon as possible, but not later than nine months after the date of dispatch of the document referred to in Article 7 (3) in support of the decision making process, provide the Secretariat with a response with a view to the future importation of the chemicals concerned.
If a Contracting Party so amends its reply, it shall promptly submit the amended reply to the Secretariat.
( 3) Nach Ablauf der in Absatz 2 genannten Frist übermittelt das Sekretariat einer Vertragspartei, die eine solche Antwort nicht erteilt hat, unverzüglich eine entsprechende schriftliche Aufforderung. After the period referred to in paragraph 2 of this Article has expired, the secretariat shall promptly send a corresponding written request to a Contracting Party which has not given such a reply.
If the Contracting Party is unable to reply, the Secretariat shall, where appropriate, assist the Contracting Party in submitting a reply within the period referred to in Article 11 (2), last sentence.
( 4) Eine Antwort nach Absatz 2 besteht entweder aus An answer under paragraph 2 shall consist of either:
( a) a final decision based on laws, regulations or administrative provisions;
( ii) not to consent to imports; or
( iii) consent to imports subject to certain conditions; or
( b) a provisional reply which may include:
( i) a provisional decision on consent to import with or without certain conditions or on disagreement to import during the transitional period;
( ii) a declaration that a final decision is under intensive consideration;
( iii) a request for further information to be made to the secretariat or to the Contracting Party which has notified the directly applicable legislation;
( iv) a request to the Secretariat for assistance in the evaluation of the chemical.
( 5) Eine Antwort nach Absatz 4 Buchstabe a) oder b) bezieht sich auf die für die Chemikalie in Anlage III spezizierte<unk> n) Kategorie orie<unk> n). A response in accordance with paragraph 4 (a) or (b) of this Article shall refer to the categories specified for the chemical in Annex III.
( 6) Eine endgültigen Entscheidung soll auch eine Beschreibung aller Rechts- bzw. Verwaltungsvorschriften beiliegen, auf die sie sich stützt. A final decision shall also be accompanied by a description of all the laws and regulations on which it is based.
( 7) Jede Vertragspartei übermittelt dem Sekretariat spätestens bis zum Datum des Inkrafttretens dieses Übereinkommens für diese Vertragspartei Antworten zu jeder in Anlage III aufgenommenen Chemikalie. Each Contracting Party shall provide to the Secretariat, not later than the date of entry into force of this Agreement, for that Contracting Party, answers to each of the chemicals listed in Annex III.
Contracting Parties that have provided such replies under the revised London Guidelines or the International Code of Conduct shall not be required to submit them again.
( 8) Jede Vertragspartei stellt ihre Antwort nach diesem Artikel in Übereinstimmung mit ihren Rechts- bzw. Verwaltungsvorschriften den betroffenen innerhalb ihres Hoheitsbereichs zur Verfügung. Each Contracting Party shall, in accordance with its laws and / or regulations, provide the persons concerned with its answers in accordance with this Article within its jurisdiction.
( 9) Eine Vertragspartei, die aufgrund der Absätze 2 und 4 oder des Artikels 11 Absatz 2 entscheidet, der Einfuhr einer Chemikalie nicht oder nur unter bestimmten Bedingungen zuzustimmen, muss - sofern sie dies nicht bereits getan - Simultaneously folgendes verbieten oder es den selben Bedingungen unterwerfen: A Contracting Party which, on the basis of paragraphs 2 and 4 or paragraph 2 of Article 11, decides not to agree to the importation of a chemical or to do so only under certain conditions, shall, provided that it has not already done so, ban the following or shall subject it to the same conditions:
( a) imports of the chemical from any source; and
( b) domestic production of the chemical for domestic consumption.
( 10) Alle sechs Monate informiert das Sekretariat sämtliche Vertragsparteien über die ihm zugangenen Replies. Every six months the Secretariat shall inform all Contracting Parties of the replies it receives.
This information shall include, where available, a description of the laws, regulations or administrative provisions on which the decisions are based.
The Secretariat shall also inform the Contracting Parties of any failure to reply.
Obligations relating to exports of chemicals listed in Annex III
( 1) Jede führende Vertragspartei Each exporting Party
( a) apply appropriate laws, regulations and administrative provisions to provide, within their jurisdiction, the replies provided by the Secretariat in accordance with Article 10 (10);
( b) adopt appropriate laws, regulations and administrative provisions to ensure that exporters, within their jurisdiction, comply with the decisions in such replies not later than six months after the date on which the Secretariat first informed the Contracting Parties of the individual replies provided in accordance with Article 10 (10);
( c) advise and assist importing Contracting Parties, upon request and as appropriate, in:
( i) in obtaining further information enabling them to take action in accordance with Article 10 (4) and Article 11 (2) (c); and
( ii) strengthening their capacities and capabilities for the safe management of chemicals throughout their lifetime.
( 2) Jede Vertragspartei stellt sicher, daß eine in Anlage III aufgenommene Chemikalie nicht aus ihrem Hoheitsgebiet an eine einführende Vertragspartei ausgeführt wird, die unter außergewöhnlichen Umständen keine Antwort übermittelt hat oder die eine vorläufige Antwort übermittelt hat, die keine vorläufige Entscheidung enthält, es sei, Each Contracting Party shall ensure that a chemical product listed in Annex III is not exported from its territory to an importing Contracting Party which, under exceptional circumstances, has not provided a response or which has provided a provisional response which does not contain a provisional decision, unless:
( a) a chemical registered as a chemical with the importing Contracting Party at the time of import;
( b) it is a chemical which has been shown to have been imported or used by the importing Party and for which no legislation banning its use has been adopted;
( c) the exporter, through a designated national authority, has sought and obtained explicit consent to the importation from the importing Contracting Party.
The importing Contracting Party shall reply to such a request within 60 days and shall promptly notify the Secretariat of its decision.
The obligations of the exporting Contracting Parties under this paragraph shall enter into force six months after the date on which the Secretariat first informed the Contracting Parties, in accordance with Article 10 (10), that a Contracting Party had not provided a reply or that it had provided a provisional reply which did not contain a provisional decision and shall be valid for one year.
( 1) Wird eine von einer Vertragspartei verboten oder strengen Beschränkungen unterworfene Chemikalie aus dem Hoheitsgebiet dieser Vertragspartei ausgeführt, so notifiziert diese Partei der einführenden Vertragspartei die Ausfuhr. If a chemical product banned or subject to stringent restrictions by a Contracting Party is exported from the territory of that Contracting Party, that Party shall notify the importing Contracting Party of its export.
The export notification shall contain the information set out in Annex V.
( 2) Die Notifikation der Ausfuhr der betreffenden Chemikalie erfolgt vor der ersten Ausfuhr nach Erlass der entsprechenden unmittelbar geltenden Rechtsvorschriften. The notification of the export of the chemicals concerned shall be made before the first export after the enactment of the relevant directly applicable legislation.
Thereafter it shall be carried out before the first export of each calendar year.
The designated national authority of the importing Contracting Party may waive the requirement of prior notification.
( 3) Sobald eine führende Vertragspartei unmittelbar geltende Rechtsvorschriften erlassen hat, die zu wesentlichen Änderungen im Hinblick auf das Verbot oder die strenge Beschränkung der Chemikalie führen, legt sie eine aktualisierte Ausfuhrnotifikation vor. As soon as an exporting Contracting Party has adopted directly applicable legislation leading to substantial amendments to the prohibition or strict restriction of the chemicals, it shall submit an updated export notification.
( 4) Die einführende Vertragspartei bestätigt den Empfang der ersten nach Erlass der unmittelbar geltenden Rechtsvorschriften bei ihr eingegangenen Ausfuhrnotifikation. The importing Contracting Party shall confirm receipt of the first export notification received by the importing Party after the adoption of the directly applicable legislation.
If the exporting Contracting Party has not received such confirmation within 30 days of the dispatch of the export notification, it shall submit a second export notification.
The exporting Contracting Party shall make every effort to ensure that the importing Contracting Party receives the second notification.
( 5) Die in Absatz 1 niedergelegten Verpflichtungen einer Vertragspartei entfallen, The obligations of a Contracting Party specified in paragraph 1 of this Article shall cease to apply:
( a) once the chemical has been listed in Annex III;
( b) as soon as the importing Contracting Party has replied to the secretariat for that chemical in accordance with Article 10 (2);
( c) as soon as the Secretariat has forwarded the reply referred to in Article 10 (10) to the Contracting Parties.
( 1) Die Konferenz der Vertragsparteien re+ gt die Weltzollorganisation an an, den in Anlage III aufgenommenen einzelnen Chemikalien bzw. Chemikalienggruppen im Rahmen des Harmonisierten Systems bestimmte Zollcodes zuzuordnen. The Conference of the Parties shall encourage the World Customs Organization to allocate certain customs codes to the individual chemicals or groups of chemicals included in Annex III within the framework of the Harmonized System.
Each Contracting Party shall require that a code associated with such a chemical be noted on export in the chemical <unk> s transit documents.
( 2) Unbeschadet etwaiger Vorschriften der einführenden Vertragspartei schreibt jede Vertragspartei vor, daß sowohl für die in Anlage III aufgenommenen Chemikalien sowie für die in ihrem Hoheitsgebiet verboten oder striengen Beschränkungen unterliegenden Chemikalien bei der Ausfuhr Kennzeichnungsvorschriften gelten, die unter Berücksichtigung der einschlägigen internationalen Normen gewährleisten, daß ausreichende Informationen über Gefahren und/ oder Gefahren für die menschlichen Gesundheit oder die Umwelt zur Verfügung stehen. Without prejudice to any regulations of the importing Contracting Party, each Contracting Party shall require that export labelling regulations apply to both chemicals listed in Annex III and to chemicals subject to strict restrictions in its territory, which, taking into account the relevant international standards, ensure that sufficient information is available on risks and / or hazards to human health or the environment.
( 3) Unbeschaiger etwaiger Vorschriften der einführenden Vertragspartei kann jede Vertragspartei vorschreiben, daß für die in ihrem Hoheitsgebiet umwelt- oder gesundheitsbezogenen Kennzeichnungsvorschriften unterliegenden Chemikalien bei der Ausfuhr Kennzeichnungsvorschriften gelten, die unter Berücksichtigung der einschlägigen internationalen Normen gewährleisten, daß ausreichende Informationen über Gefahren und/ oder Gefahren für die menschlichen Gesundheit oder die Umwelt zur Verfügung stehen. Without prejudice to any regulations of the importing Contracting Party, any Contracting Party may prescribe that for the chemicals subject to labelling or health regulations in its territory, export labelling regulations apply which, taking into account the relevant international standards, ensure that sufficient information is available on risks and / or hazards to human health or the environment.
( 4) Für diejenigen der in Absatz 2 genannten Chemikalien, die zur berufliche Verwendung bestimmt sind, schreibt jede führende Vertragspartei vor, daß jedem Einführer ein Sicherheitsdatenblatt zugesandt wird, das in internationally anerkannter Form die neuesten verfügbaren Informationen enthält. For those chemicals referred to in paragraph 2 of this Article intended for professional use, each exporting Contracting Party shall prescribe that a safety data sheet shall be sent to each importer containing the latest available information in an internationally recognised form.
( 5) Die Angaben auf dem Etikett und auf dem Sicherheitsdatenblatt sollen soweit wie möglich in einer oder mehreren Amtssprachen der einführenden Vertragspartei abgefasst sein. The information on the label and the safety data sheet shall, as far as possible, be in one or more official languages of the importing Contracting Party.
( 1) Soweit angebracht und im Einklang mit dem Ziel dieses Übereinkommens erleichtert jede Vertragspartei As far as appropriate and consistent with the objective of this Convention, each Contracting Party shall facilitate:
( a) the exchange of scientific, technical, economic and legal information on chemicals falling within the scope of the Convention, including toxicological, ecotoxicological and safety information;
( b) the provision of publicly available information on internal legislation relevant to the objectives of the Convention;
( c) the provision to other Contracting Parties, either directly or through the secretariat, of information on internal legislation which significantly restricts one or, where appropriate, several uses of the chemical.
( 2) Vertragsparteien, die im Rahmen dieses Übereinkommens Informationen austauschen, schützen im gegenseitigen Einvernehmen alle vertraulichen Informationen. Parties which exchange information under this Agreement shall, by mutual agreement, protect all confidential information.
( 3) Folgende Informationen werden nicht als vertraulich im Sinne dieses Übereinkommens angesehen: The following information shall not be considered confidential within the meaning of this Agreement:
( a) the information referred to in Annexes I and IV, provided in accordance with Articles 5 and 6, respectively;
( b) the information contained in the safety data sheet referred to in Article 13 (4);
( c) the expiry date of the chemical;
( d) information on precautionary measures, including the classification of hazards, the nature of the risk and the relevant safety notices;
( e) the summary of the results of toxicological and ecotoxicological tests.
( 4) Das Herstellungsdatum der Chemikalie wird im Allgemeinen nicht als vertraulich im Sinne dieses Übereinkommens angesehen. The date of manufacture of the chemicals shall generally not be regarded as confidential within the meaning of this Agreement.
( 5) Eine Vertragspartei, die Auskünfte über den Transit von in Anlage III aufgeführten Chemikalien durch ihr Hoheitsgebiet benötigt, kann ihr Anliegen dem Sekretariat vortragen, dieses setzt alle Vertragsparteien davon in Kenntnis. A Contracting Party which needs information on the transit of chemicals listed in Annex III may make its request to the Secretariat, which shall inform all Contracting Parties thereof.
( 1) Jede Vertragspartei ergreift die erforderlichen Maßnahmen, um ihre innerstaatliche Infrastruktur und eigene staatliche Institutionen für die wirksame Durchführung des Übereinkommens zu schaffen oder zu verstärken. Each Contracting Party shall take the necessary measures to create or strengthen its domestic infrastructure and its own governmental institutions for the effective implementation of the Convention.
Such measures, which may include, where appropriate, the adoption or amendment of national laws, regulations or administrative provisions, may also include:
( a) the establishment of national registers and databases, including safety relevant information on chemicals;
( b) support for industry initiatives to promote chemical safety;
( c) the promotion of voluntary arrangements taking into account the provisions of Article 16.
( 2) Jede Vertragspartei stellt im Rahmen des Möglichen sicher, daß die Öffentlichkeit angemessenen Zugang zu Informationen über die Handhabung von Chemikalien und das verhalten bei Acfällen sowie über Alternatives hat, die für die menschlichen Gesundheit oder die Umwelt unbedenklicher sind als die in Anlage III aufgenommenen Chemikalien. Each Contracting Party shall, to the extent practicable, ensure that the public has adequate access to information on the handling of chemicals and behaviour in the event of accidents and on alternatives that are less harmful to human health or the environment than the chemicals listed in Annex III.
( 3) Die Vertragsparteien kommen überein, unmittelbar oder gegebenenfalls im Rahmen der zuständigen internationalen Organisationen bei der Durchführung dieses Übereinkommens auf subregionaler, regionaler und globaler Ebene zusammenarbeiten. The Contracting Parties agree to cooperate, directly or, where appropriate, within the framework of the competent international organizations, in the implementation of this Agreement on a subregional, regional and global level.
( 4) Dieses Übereinkommen ist nicht so auszulegen, als beschränke es das Recht der Vertragsparteien, Maßnahmen zu treffen, die die die menschlichen Gesundheit und die Umwelt strenger schützen als die in dem Übereinkommen fordergten, sofern diese Maßnahmen im Einklang mit dem Übereinkommen und dem Völkerrecht stehen. This Agreement shall not be interpreted as limiting the right of the Contracting Parties to take measures to protect human health and the environment more strictly than those required by the Agreement, provided that such measures are consistent with the Agreement and international law.
In order to implement this Agreement, the Parties shall cooperate in promoting technical assistance for the development of the necessary infrastructure and capacity for chemicals management, taking particular account of the needs of developing countries and countries with economies in transition.
Parties with more advanced chemical control programmes should provide other Parties with technical assistance, including training, in developing their chemical management infrastructure and capacities throughout their lifetime.
The Conference of the Parties shall elaborate and approve as soon as possible procedures and institutional mechanisms for determining non-compliance with the provisions of this Convention and for dealing with Parties in whose case such non-compliance has been established.
( 1) Hiermit wird eine Konferenz der Vertragsparteien eingesetzt. A Conference of the Parties shall be hereby established.
( 2) Die erste Tagung der Konferenz der Vertragsparteien wird vom Exekutivdirektor des UNEP gemeinsam mit dem Generaldirektor der FAO spätestens ein Jahr nach Inkrafttreten dieses Übereinkommens einberufen. The first meeting of the Conference of the Parties shall be convened by the Executive Director of UNEP together with the Director-General of FAO not later than one year after the entry into force of this Agreement.
Thereafter, regular meetings of the Conference of the Parties shall be held at regular intervals as determined by the Conference.
( 3) Extraordinary meetings of the Conference of the Parties shall take place if the Conference considers it necessary or if a Party so requests in writing, provided that this request is supported by at least one third of the Parties.
( 4) Die Konferenz der Vertragsparteien vereinbart und beschließt auf ihrer ersten Tagung einvernehmlich eine Geschäftsordnung und eine Finanzordnung für sich und für alle Nebenorgane sowie Finanzbestimmungen für die Tätigkeit des Sekretariats. The Conference of the Parties, at its first meeting, shall agree and adopt its own rules of procedure and financial regulations for itself and for all subsidiary bodies and financial provisions for the activities of the secretariat.
( 5) Die Konferenz der Vertragsparteien prüft und bewertet laufend die Durchführung dieses Übereinkommens. The Conference of the Parties shall examine and assess on an ongoing basis the implementation of this Agreement.
It shall carry out the functions conferred on it by the Convention by:
( a) in addition to the requirements of paragraph 6 of this Article, it shall use the subsidiary bodies it considers necessary for the implementation of the Agreement;
( b) cooperate, as appropriate, with relevant international organizations and intergovernmental and non-governmental agencies;
( c) consider and take further measures necessary to achieve the objectives of the Convention.
( 6) Die Konferenz der Vertragsparteien setzt auf ihrer ersten Tagung ein als Chemikalienprüfungsausschuss zu bezeichnendes Nebenorgan ein, das die diesem Ausschuss aufgrund des Übereinkommens zugewiesenen Aufgaben wahrnimmt. The Conference of the Parties shall, at its first meeting, establish a subsidiary body to be referred to as the Chemical Testing Committee, which shall perform the functions assigned to that Committee by virtue of the Convention.
( a) the members of the Chemicals Testing Committee shall be appointed by the Conference of the Parties.
The Committee shall be composed of a limited number of specialists in chemicals management designated by governments.
The members of the Committee shall be appointed on the basis of a balanced geographical distribution, including a balanced relationship between developed and developing countries;
( b) the Conference of the Parties shall decide on the mandate, organisation and functioning of the Committee;
( c) the Committee shall make every effort to reach consensus on its recommendations.
When all efforts at consensus have been exhausted and no agreement has been reached, the recommendation shall be adopted as a last resort by a two-thirds majority of the members present and voting.
( 7) Die Vereinten Nationen, ihre Sonderorganisationen und die Internationale Atomenergie-Organisation sowie jeder Staat, der nicht Vertragspartei dieses Übereinkommens ist, können auf den Tagungen der Konferenz der Vertragsparteien als Beobachter vertreten sein. The United Nations, its specialized agencies and the International Atomic Energy Agency, as well as any State not party to this Agreement, may be represented as observers at meetings of the Conference of the Parties.
Other national or international, governmental or non-governmental bodies or bodies which are competent in the matters covered by the Convention and which have notified the Secretariat of their wish to be represented as observers at a meeting of the Conference of the Parties may be admitted, unless at least one third of the Parties present object.
Admission and participation of observers shall be subject to the rules of procedure adopted by the Conference of the Parties.
( 1) Hiermit wird ein Sekretariat eingerichtet. A secretariat shall be hereby established.
( 2) Das Sekretariat hat folgende Aufgaben: The secretariat shall have the following functions:
( a) arrange meetings of the Conference of the Parties and its subsidiary bodies and provide the necessary services;
( b) assist, upon request, the Contracting Parties, in particular developing countries and parties with economies in transition, in the implementation of this Agreement;
( c) provide for the necessary coordination with the secretariats of other relevant international bodies;
( d) conclude, under the general supervision of the Conference of the Parties, the administrative and contractual arrangements necessary for the effective performance of its functions;
( e) perform the other secretarial functions provided for in this Agreement and any other functions determined by the Conference of the Parties.
( 3) Die SekretariatsAufgaben im Rahmen dieses Übereinkommens werden vom Exekutivdirektor des UNEP und vom Generaldirektor der FAO vorbehaltlich der zwischen ihnen vereinbarten und von der Konferenz der Vertragsparteien genehmigten Regelungen gemeinsam wahrgenommen. The secretariat functions under this Agreement shall be jointly performed by the Executive Director of UNEP and by the Director-General of FAO, subject to the arrangements agreed between them and approved by the Conference of the Parties.
( 4) Die Konferenz der Vertragsparteien kann mit dreiviertelmehrheit der anwesenden und abstimmenden Vertragsparteien beschließen, eine oder mehrere andere zuständigen internationale Organisationen mit den Sekretariatsaufgaben zu betrusten, wenn sie befindet, daß das Sekretariat nicht wie vorgesehen arbeitet. The Conference of the Parties may, by a three-quarters majority vote of the Parties present and voting, decide to entrust the secretarial duties to one or more other competent international organizations, if it considers that the secretariat is not functioning as foreseen.
( 1) Die Vertragsparteien legen alle zwischen ihnen entstehenden Streitigkeiten über die Auslegung oder Anwendung dieses Übereinkommens durch Verhandlungen oder andere friedliche Mittel ihrer Wahl bei. The Contracting Parties shall settle any dispute arising between them concerning the interpretation or application of this Agreement by negotiation or other peaceful means of their choice.
( 2) Bei der Ratifikation, der Annahme oder der Genehmigung dieses Übereinkommens oder beim Beitritt zu diesem Übereinkommen oder jederzeit danach kann eine Vertragspartei, die keine Organisation der regionalen Wirtschaftsintegration ist, in einer dem Verwahrer vorgelegten Urkunde erklären, daß sie in Bezug auf jede Streitigkeit über die Auslegung oder Anwendung des Übereinkommens eines der folgenden Mittel der Streitbeilegung oder beide gegenüber jeder Vertragspartei, welche dieselbe Verpflichtung übernimmt, als obligatorisch anerkennt: In the event of ratification, acceptance or approval of this Agreement or accession to, or at any time thereafter, a Contracting Party which is not a regional economic integration organisation may declare, in an instrument submitted to the depositary, that, with respect to any dispute concerning the interpretation or application of this Agreement, it recognises as obligatory one of the following means of dispute settlement, or both, with respect to any Contracting Party
( a) arbitration in accordance with a procedure to be decided by the Conference of the Parties as soon as possible in an Annex;
( b) submission of the dispute to the International Court of Justice.
( 3) Eine Vertragspartei, die eine Organisation der regionalen Wirtschaftsintegration ist, kann in Bezug auf ein Schiedsverfahren nach dem in Absatz 2 Buchstabe a) vorgesehenen Verfahren eine Erklärung mit gleicher Wirkung abgeben. A Contracting Party which is a regional economic integration organization may make a declaration having equivalent effect with respect to arbitration under the procedure provided for in paragraph 2 (a) of this Article.
( 4) Eine nach Absatz 2 abgegebene Erklärung bleibt in Kraft, bis sie nach den darin enthaltenen Bedingungen erlischt, oder bis zum Ablauf von drei Monaten nach Hinterlegung einer schriftlichen Rücknahmenotifikation beim Verwahrer. A declaration made in accordance with paragraph 2 of this Article shall remain in force until it ceases to exist in accordance with the conditions contained therein, or until the expiration of three months after the deposit of a notification of written withdrawal with the depositary.
( 5) Das Erlöschen einer Erklärung, eine Rücknahmenotifikation oder eine neue Erklärung berührt nicht die beim Internationalen Gerichtshof oder bei dem Schiedsgericht anpending Verfahren, sofern die Streitparteien nichts anderes vereinbaren. The lapse of a declaration, notification of withdrawal or new declaration shall not affect proceedings pending before the International Court of Justice or the arbitral tribunal, unless the parties to the dispute agree otherwise.
( 6) Haben sich die Streitparteien nicht auf ein Verfahren oder auf dasselbe Verfahren der Streitbeilegung gemäß Absatz 2 vereinbart und können sie ihre Streitigkeit nicht binnen zwölf Monaten, nachdem eine Vertragspartei einer anderen notifiziert hat, daß eine Streitigkeit zwischen ihnen besteht, beilegen, so wird der Streitfall auf Ersuchen einer der Streitparteien einer Vergleichskommission vorgelegt. If the parties to the dispute have not agreed on a procedure or on the same dispute settlement procedure as referred to in paragraph 2 of this Article and have not been able to settle their dispute within twelve months of one Contracting Party notifying another that a dispute exists between them, the dispute shall, at the request of one of the parties to the dispute, be referred to a conciliation commission.
The Comparative Commission shall draw up a report with recommendations.
Further procedures relating to the Settlement Commission shall be set out in an Annex to be adopted by the Conference of the Parties not later than the second session of the Conference.
( 1) Änderungen dieses Übereinkommens können von jeder Vertragspartei vorgeschlagen werden. Amendments to this Convention may be proposed by any Contracting Party.
( 2) Änderungen dieses Übereinkommens werden auf einer Tagung der Konferenz der Vertragsparteien beschlossen. Amendments to this Convention shall be adopted at a meeting of the Conference of the Parties.
The text of a proposed amendment shall be communicated to the Contracting Parties by the Secretariat at least six months before the meeting at which the amendment is proposed for decision.
The Secretariat shall also communicate proposed amendments to the signatories to the Convention and to the depositary for information.
( 3) Die Vertragsparteien bemühen sich nach Kräften um eine einvernehmliche Einigung über eine vorgeschlagene Änderung des Übereinkommens. The Contracting Parties shall endeavour to the best of their abilities to reach an amicable agreement on a proposed amendment to the Convention.
When all efforts at consensus have been exhausted and no agreement has been reached, the amendment shall, as a last resort, be adopted by a three-quarters majority of the Parties present and voting at the meeting.
( 4) Die Änderung wird vom Verwahrer allen Vertragsparteien zur Ratifikation, Annahme oder Genehmigung übermittelt. The amendment shall be communicated by the depositary to all Contracting Parties for ratification, acceptance or approval.
( 5) Die Ratifikation, Annahme oder Genehmigung einer Änderung wird dem Verwahrer schriftlich notifiziert. Ratification, acceptance or approval of an amendment shall be notified to the depositary in writing.
An amendment adopted in accordance with paragraph 3 of this Article shall enter into force for the Contracting Parties which have accepted it on the 90th day following the deposit of instruments of ratification, acceptance or approval by at least three quarters of the Contracting Parties.
Thereafter, the amendment shall enter into force for any other Contracting Party on the 90th day following the date on which that Contracting Party deposits its instrument of ratification, acceptance or approval of the amendment.
( 1) Die Anlagen dieses Übereinkommens sind Bestandteil des Übereinkommens; sofern nicht ausdrücklich etwas anderes vorgesehen ist, stellt eine Bezugnahme auf dieses Übereinkommen Simultaneously eine Bezugnahme auf die Anlagen dar. The Annexes to this Agreement shall form an integral part of the Agreement, unless expressly provided otherwise, and at the same time constitutes a reference to the Annexes.
( 2) Die Anhänge beschränken sich auf verfahrensmäßige, wissenschaftliche, technische und Verwaltungsmäßige Angelegenheiten. The Annexes shall be limited to procedural, scientific, technical and administrative matters.
( 3) Folgendes Verfahren findet auf den Vorschlag weiterer Anhänge dieses Übereinkommens, die Beschlussfassung darüber und das Inkrafttreten derselben Anwendung: The following procedure shall apply to the proposal of further Annexes to this Agreement, the decision making thereon and the entry into force thereof:
( a) further Annexes shall be proposed and adopted in accordance with the procedure laid down in Article 21 (1), (2) and (3);
( b) a Contracting Party which is unable to accept another Annex shall notify the Depositary in writing within one year of the date on which the Depositary has notified that the further Annex has been decided.
The depositary shall promptly notify all Contracting Parties of the receipt of any such notification.
A Contracting Party may withdraw such notification at any time and the Annex shall subsequently enter into force for that Contracting Party subject to subparagraph (c) of this Article;
( c) at the end of one year from the date on which the depositary notifies that a further Annex has been decided, the latter shall enter into force for all Contracting Parties which have not submitted a notification in accordance with subparagraph (b) of this Article.
( 4) Mit Ausnahme der Anlage III unterliegen der Vorschlag von Änderungen von Anlagen dieses Übereinkommens, die Beschlussfassung darüber und das Inkrafttreten derselben demselben Verfahren wie der Vorschlag weiterer Anlagen des Übereinkommens, die Beschlussfassung darüber und das Inkrafttreten derselben. With the exception of Annex III, the proposal for amendments to Annexes to this Agreement, the decision making thereto and the entry into force thereof shall be subject to the same procedure as the proposal for further Annexes to this Agreement, the decision making thereof and the entry into force thereof.
( 5) Folgendes Verfahren findet beim Vorschlag von Änderungen der Anlage III, bei der Beschlussfassung darüber und beim Inkrafttreten derselben Anwendung: The following procedure shall apply to the proposal for amendments to Annex III, to the decision making thereon and to the entry into force thereof:
( a) Amendments to Annex III shall be proposed and adopted in accordance with the procedure laid down in Articles 5 to 9 and Article 21 (2);
( b) the decision of the Conference of the Parties shall be taken by consensus;
( c) a decision amending Annex III shall be communicated without delay by the depositary to the Contracting Parties.
The amendment shall enter into force for all Contracting Parties on a date to be fixed in the Decision.
( 6) Bezog sich eine weitere Anlage oder eine Änderung einer Anlage auf eine Änderung dieses Übereinkommens, so tritt die weitere Anlage oder die geänderte Anlage erst in Kraft, wenn die Änderung des Übereinkommens in Kraft tritt. If a further Annex or an amendment to an Annex relates to an amendment to this Agreement, the further Annex or the amended Annex shall not enter into force until the amendment to the Agreement enters into force.
( 1) Vorbehaltlich des Absatzes 2 hat jede Vertragspartei dieses Übereinkommens eine Stimme. Subject to paragraph 2 of this Article, each Contracting Party to this Agreement shall have one vote.
( 2) Eine Organisation der regionalen Wirtschaftsintegration übt in Angelegenheiten ihrer Zuständigkeit ihr Stimmrecht mit der Anzahl von Stimmen aus, die der Anzahl ihrer Mitgliedstaaten entspricht, die Vertragsparteien dieses Übereinkommens sind. In matters within its competence, a regional economic integration organization shall exercise its right to vote with the number of votes equal to the number of its Member States which are Contracting Parties to this Agreement.
Such an organisation shall not exercise its right to vote when one of its Member States exercises its right to vote and vice versa.
( 3) Im Sinne dieses Übereinkommens bedeutet <unk> anwesende und abstimmende Vertragsparteien <unk> die anwesenden Vertragsparteien, die eine Ja- oder eine Neinstimme abgeben. For the purposes of this Convention, <unk> present and voting Contracting Parties
This Agreement shall be open for signature by all States and all regional economic integration organisations at Rotterdam on 11 September 1998 and at United Nations Headquarters in New York from 12 September 1998 to 10 September 1999.
( 1) Dieses Übereinkommen bedarf der Ratifikation, Annahme oder Genehmigung durch Staaten und durch Organisationen der regionalen Wirtschaftsintegration. This Agreement shall be subject to ratification, acceptance or approval by States and regional economic integration organisations.
It shall be open to accession by States and regional economic integration organisations from the date on which it ceases to be open for signature.
Instruments of ratification, acceptance, approval or accession shall be deposited with the depositary.
( 2) Jede Organisation der regionalen Wirtschaftsintegration, die Vertragspartei dieses Übereinkommens wird, ohne daß einer ihrer Mitgliedstaaten Vertragspartei ist, ist durch alle Verpflichtungen aus dem Übereinkommen gebunden. Any regional economic integration organisation which becomes a Contracting Party to this Agreement, without one of its Member States being a Contracting Party, shall be bound by any obligations under this Agreement.
If one or more Member States of such an organisation are Contracting Parties to the Convention, the Agency and its Member States shall decide on their respective responsibilities in respect of the fulfilment of their obligations under the Convention.
In such cases, the Agency and the Member States shall not be entitled to exercise rights under the Convention at the same time.
( 3) In ihrer Ratifikations-, Annahme-, Genehmigungs- oder Beitrittsurkunde gibt eine Organisation der regionalen Wirtschaftsintegration an, in dem Umfang sie in Bezug auf die durch das Übereinkommen erfassten Angelegenheiten zuständig ist. In its instrument of ratification, acceptance, approval or accession, an organization of regional economic integration shall specify to what extent it is competent with respect to matters covered by the Convention.
Any such organisation shall also notify the depositary of any substantial change in the scope of its competences, which in turn shall inform the Contracting Parties.
( 1) Dieses Übereinkommen tritt am neunzigsten Tag nach dem Zeitpunkt der Hinterlegung der fünfzigsten Ratifikations-, Annahme-, Genehmigungs- oder Beitrittsurkunde in Kraft. This Convention shall enter into force on the 90th day following the date of deposit of the fiftieth instrument of ratification, acceptance, approval or accession.
( 2) Für jeden Staat oder für jede Organisation der regionalen Wirtschaftsintegration, die nach Hinterlegung der fünfzigsten Ratifikations-, Annahme-, Genehmigungs- oder Beitrittsurkunde das Übereinkommen ratifiziert, annimmt, genehmigt oder ihm beitritt, tritt das Übereinkommen am neunzigsten Tag nach dem Zeitpunkt der Hinterlegung der Ratifikations-, Annahme-, Genehmigungs- oder Beitrittsurkunde durch den betreffenden Staat oder die betreffende Organisation der regionalen Wirtschaftsintegration in Kraft. For any State or regional economic integration organisation which ratifies, accepts, approves or accedes to the Agreement after the deposit of its fiftieth instrument of ratification, acceptance, approval or accession, the Agreement shall enter into force on the 90th day following the deposit of the instrument of ratification, acceptance, approval or accession by that State or regional economic integration organisation.
( 3) Für die Zwecke der Absätze 1 und 2 zählt eine von einer Organisation der regionalen Wirtschaftsintegration hinterlegte Urkunde nicht als zusätzliche Urkunde zu den von den Mitgliedstaaten der Organisation hintergelegten Urkunden. For the purposes of paragraphs 1 and 2 of this Article, an instrument deposited by a regional economic integration organisation shall not be considered as an additional instrument to those deposited by the Member States of the organisation.
No reservations may be made with respect to this Agreement.
( 1) Eine Vertragspartei kann jederzeit nach Ablauf von drei Jahren nach dem Zeitpunkt, zu dem dieses Übereinkommen für sie in Kraft getreten ist, durch eine an den Verwahrer gerichtete schriftliche Notifikation von dem Übereinkommen zurücktreten. A Contracting Party may withdraw from the Agreement at any time after three years from the date on which this Agreement has entered into force for it by notifying the depositary in writing.
( 2) Der Rücktritt wird nach Ablauf eines Jahres nach dem Eingang der Notifikation beim Verwahrer oder zu einem gegebenenfalls in der Rücktrittsnotifikation genannten späteren Zeitpunkt wirksam. Withdrawal shall take effect after one year from the date of receipt of such notification by the depositary or at a later date as may be specified in the notification of withdrawal.
The Secretary-General of the United Nations shall be the depositary of this Convention.
The original of this Agreement, of which the Arabic, Chinese, English, French, Russian and Spanish texts are equally authentic, shall be deposited with the Secretary-General of the United Nations.
between the European Atomic Energy Community (Euratom) and non-member States of the European Union on participation in arrangements within the Community for the rapid exchange of information in a radiological emergency (Ecurie)
Considering that Council Decision 87 / 600 / Euratom establishes a framework in the form of the Ecurian Arrangements for the rapid exchange of information in a radiological emergency;
the effectiveness of the Ecurian arrangements shall be improved by the participation of third countries, in particular neighbouring countries of the European Union;
Bulgaria, Cyprus, the Czech Republic, Estonia, Hungary, Latvia, Lithuania, Malta, Poland, Romania, the Slovak Republic, Slovenia, Switzerland and Turkey, hereinafter referred to as the participating countries, should be invited to accede to these Agreements;
The Agreement shall apply to notification and exchange of information in all cases where one of the participating countries or a Member State of Euratom decides to take comprehensive measures to protect the population in the event of a radiological emergency, namely:
( a) following an accident on their respective territories, in the following facilities or in the framework of the following activities:
- the transport and storage of nuclear fuel or radioactive waste;
- the production, use, storage, disposal and transport of radioisotopes for agricultural, industrial, medical and related scientific or research purposes;
- the use of radioisotopes for generating electricity in space objects,
( b) after other accidents which have or may have led to a significant release of radioactive substances;
( c) after detection, on or outside their respective territories, of anomalous levels of radioactivity likely to be harmful to the health of the respective populations.
Exchange of information in the case of the measures referred to in Article 1 within the territory of a participating country or in a Euratom Member State
( 1) Beschließt ein teilnehmendes Land, Maßnahmen nach Artikel 1 zu ergreifen, so übermittelt dieses Land der Kommission der Europäischen Gemeinschaften (hereinafter referred to as <unk> the Commission
The Commission shall promptly inform the Member States of Euratom and the other participating countries.
( 2) Hat ein Mitgliedstaat von Euratom beschlossen, derartige Maßnahmen zu ergreifen und die Kommission davon unterrichtet, so unterrichtet die Kommission unverzüglich die teilnehmenden Länder. Where a Member State of Euratom has decided to take such measures and has informed the Commission thereof, the Commission shall promptly inform the participating countries.
The information to be supplied in accordance with paragraph 2 above shall, as far as possible and indicated, include:
( a) the nature, timing and location of the event and the installation or activity concerned;
( b) information on the suspected or identified cause of the accident and on the likely development of the accident with respect to the release of radioactive substances;
( c) the general characteristics of the radioactive substances released, including species, probable physical and chemical form, quantity, composition and effective level of such releases;
( d) information on the existing and anticipated meteorological and hydrological conditions necessary for predicting the spread of the released radioactive substances;
( e) the results of environmental monitoring;
( f) the results of measurements of foodstuffs, feedingstuffs and drinking water;
( g) information on the protective measures taken or planned;
( h) information on measures taken or planned to educate the public;
( i) information on the likely behaviour of the radioactive substances released over time.
This information shall be supplemented at appropriate intervals by further relevant information, in particular information on the further development of the emergency situation and its likely or actual termination.
( 1) Nach Eingang der in Artikel 2 und 3 genannten Informationen müssen die Kommission unter Berücksichtigung der von den Mitgliedstaaten von Euratom eingegangenen Informationen After receipt of the information referred to in Articles 2 and 3, the Commission shall, taking into account the information received from the Member States of Euratom,:
( a) promptly inform the participating countries of the measures taken and recommendations made after such information has been received;
( b) inform the participating countries, at appropriate intervals, of radioactivity levels in foodstuffs, feedingstuffs, drinking water and the environment measured by the monitoring facilities of the Euratom Member States.
( 2) Nach Eingang der in Artikel 2 und 3 oben erwähnten Informationen müssen die teilnehmenden Länder Upon receipt of the information referred to in Articles 2 and 3 above, the participating countries shall:
( a) promptly inform the Commission of the measures taken and recommendations made after such information has been received;
( b) inform the Commission at appropriate intervals of radioactivity levels measured by its monitoring facilities in foodstuffs, feedingstuffs, drinking water and the environment.
Participating countries shall not be obliged to provide the European Commission with information which would prejudice national security, and the Commission shall not provide any information to participating countries provided by a Member State of Euratom or by a Contracting Party if such information has been reported as confidential.
( 1) Die teilnehmenden Länder setzen die bestehenden detaillierten Ecurie-Modalitäten für den Informationsaustausch gemäß Artikel 2, 3 und 4 binnen dreier Monate nach Unterzeichnung dieses Abkommens um. The participating countries shall implement the existing detailed modalities for the exchange of information provided for in Articles 2, 3 and 4 within three months of the date of signature of this Agreement.
( 2) danach sind die detaillierten Modalitäten für den Informationsaustausch nach Artikel 2, 3 und 4 in einem gemeinsamen Abkommen zwischen den teilnehmenden Ländern, der Kommission und den Mitgliedstaaten von Euratom festzulegen und in regelmäßigen Abständen zu überprüfen. The detailed modalities for the exchange of information referred to in Article 2, 3 and 4 shall thereafter be laid down in a joint agreement between the participating countries, the Commission and the Member States of Euratom and reviewed at regular intervals.
Each Contracting Party shall bear the costs of implementing these Arrangements.
( 1) Die teilnehmenden Länder nennen der Kommission die zuständigen Behörde und die zur Weiterleitung und Entgegennahme der Informationen nach Artikel 2, 3 und 4 benannte Kontaktstelle sowie ihre Kontaktinformation. Die Kommission meldet den teilnehmenden Länder, welche ihrer departungen die zuständigen Stelle oder Kontaktstelle ist. The participating countries shall inform the Commission of the competent authority and the contact point designated for forwarding and receiving information pursuant to Articles 2, 3 and 4, and of their contact information.
( 2) Die Kontaktstellen in den teilnehmenden Länder und die zuständigen Abteilung der Kommission müssen jederzeit erreichen sein. The contact points in the participating countries and the competent department of the Commission shall be reachable at any time.
( 1) Die teilnehmenden Länder werden zu den Sitzungen der von der Kommission für die Verwaltung der Ecurie-Vereinbarungen eingesetzten Gruppe eingeladen. Participating countries shall be invited to attend meetings of the Group established by the Commission for the Management of the Ecurian Arrangements.
( 2) Diese Gruppe kann beschließen, Vertreter der teilnehmenden Länder zu den Sitzungen der eingesetzten Arbeitsgruppen einzuladen. This Group may decide to invite representatives of the participating countries to the meetings of the working parties set up.
( 3) Die Vertreter der teilnehmenden Länder haben Beobachterstatus; sämtliche hierbei anfallenden Kosten werden von den jeweiligen nationalen Behörden getragen. The representatives of the participating countries shall have observer status and all costs incurred shall be borne by the respective national authorities.
Ecurian arrangements and other relevant international agreements
This Agreement shall not affect the rights and obligations of the participating countries and of the European Atomic Energy Community under any bilateral or multilateral agreement or agreement currently in force or yet to be concluded in the fields covered by this Agreement which are consistent with its objective.
( 1) Nach Unterzeichnung dieses Abkommens durch Euratom können die Republik Bulgaria, die Republik Zypern, die Czech Republik, die Republik Estonia, die Republik Ungarn, die Republik Lettland, die Republik Lithuauen, die Republik Malta, die Republik Polen, Republik Romania, die Slovakkische Republik, die Republik Slovenia, die Schweizerische Eidgenossenschaft und die Republik Türkei dieses Abkommen ratifizieren. After signature of this Agreement by Euratom, the Republic of Bulgaria, the Republic of Cyprus, the Czech Republic, the Republic of Estonia, the Republic of Hungary, the Republic of Latvia, the Republic of Lithuania, the Republic of Malta, the Republic of Poland, the Republic of Romania, the Slovak Republic, the Republic of Slovenia, the Swiss Confederation and the Republic of Turkey may ratify this Agreement.
To this end, Euratom shall send certified copies of the Agreement to those countries for signature.
Euratom may invite other countries to accede to this Agreement.
( 2) Dieses Abkommen wird bei der Kommission hinterlegt. This Agreement shall be deposited with the Commission.
( 3) Dieses Abkommen tritt drei Monate nach Beitritt von mindestens einem der oben aufgeführten Länder in Kraft. This Agreement shall enter into force three months after the accession of at least one of the countries listed above.
For each country acceding to this Agreement after its entry into force, the Agreement shall enter into force three months later.
( 4) Jedes beitretende Land unterrichtet die Kommission über den Abschluss der internen Verfahren bezüglich des Abschlusses dieses Abkommens. Each acceding country shall inform the Commission of the completion of internal procedures relating to the conclusion of this Agreement.
The Commission shall inform other Parties to this Agreement of the accession of any new Party, including the date of entry into force of the Agreement for that Party.
( 5) Jedes beitretende Land nimmt provisorisch als Mitglied der Ecurie-Vereinbarungen ab dem Datum teil, an dem die Kommission ein beglaubigtes Copemplar dieses ordnungsgemäß durch die mit der erforderlichen Vollmacht ausgestattete nationale Behörde unterzeichneten Abkommens sowie die für die volle Umsetzung nach Artikel 7 erforderliche Kontaktinformation erhalten hat. Each acceding country shall participate provisionally as a member of the Ecurian Arrangements from the date on which the Commission has received a certified copy of this Agreement duly signed by the national authority empowered by the requisite authority and the contact information required for its full implementation under Article 7.
( 1) Beschließt eine Vertragspartei dieses Abkommen zu kündigen, so ist dies den anderen Vertragsparteien schriftlich zu melden. If a Contracting Party decides to terminate this Agreement, it shall notify the other Contracting Parties in writing.
After the expiry of a period of three months from the date of notification, this Agreement shall cease to have legal effect between the denouncing Contracting Party and the other Contracting Parties to this Agreement.
The date of denunciation shall be the date of notification to the Commission.
The Commission shall inform the other Contracting Parties to this Agreement of the relevant date.
( 2) Nach Beitritt eines teilnehmenden Landes zur Europäischen Union gilt die Entscheidung 87 / 600/ Euratom des Rates, und dieses Abkommen verlieren die unmittelbare individuelle Rechtswirkung für dieses Land. After the accession of a participating country to the European Union, Decision 87 / 600 / Euratom of the Council shall apply, and this Agreement shall lose its immediate individual legal effect for that country.
( 3) Dieses Abkommen erlischt, falls Euratom beschließt, dieses Abkommen gemäß den Bestimmungen in Absatz 1 zu kündigen. This Agreement shall lapse if Euratom decides to terminate this Agreement in accordance with the provisions of paragraph 1.
This Declaration, in the form of an Exchange of Letters between Euratom and Switzerland on 21 June 1995 (OJ L 183, 9.9.1995, p.
4) Agreement shall be repealed with effect from the date of entry into force of this Agreement for Switzerland after its accession.
in the form of an exchange of letters between the European Community and the Republic of Croatia on the ecopoint system applicable as from 1 January 2003 to transit traffic of the Republic of Croatia through Austria
I have the honour to inform you that following negotiations between the Delegation of the Republic of Croatia and the Delegation of the European Community, in accordance with the provisions of Article 2 (2) (b) of Protocol 6 to the Interim Agreement between the European Community and the Republic of Croatia, the following has been agreed:
1. Ecopoints (transit rights) for Croatian lorries in transit through Austria for 2003: 171904 Ecopoints.
Additional ecopoints for Croatian users of the <unk> Rolling Road <unk> (RoLa) (up to a maximum of 40% of the total ecopoints for 2003): 68762 ecopoints.
Ecopoints for users of RoLa shall be allocated to the Croatian authorities in such a way as to award ecopoints for two road trips on the RoLa for each round trip.
The Austrian combined transport companies shall notify the Ministry of Maritime, Transport and Communications of the Republic of Croatia on a monthly basis of the number of Croatian users of combined transport in transit through Austria.
Transit journeys carried out under the conditions set out in Annex A or on the basis of CBMT authorisation shall be excluded from the ecopoint system.
2. Der driver eines kroatischen Lastkraftwagens hat auf Österreichischem Staatsgebiet folgendes mitzführen und den Aufsichtsbehörden auf Verlangen zur Überprüfung vorzulegen, entweder: The driver of a Croatian lorry shall carry the following items with him on Austrian territory and, upon request, submit them for verification to the supervisory authorities, either:
( a) a duly completed standard form or an Austrian certificate confirming payment of ecopoints for the journey in question (see Annex B), hereinafter referred to as the <unk> eco map <unk>; or
( b) an electronic device attached to the vehicle enabling the automatic debiting of ecopoints, hereinafter referred to as the <unk> ecotag <unk>; or
( c) appropriate documentation proving that the voyage is an ecopoint free transit trip in accordance with Annex A or with a CBMT permit; or
( d) appropriate documentation proving that the journey is not a transit and that the environmental data carrier, where present on the vehicle, has been duly adjusted.
The competent Austrian authorities shall issue the eco card in return for payment of the costs of the production and distribution of eco points and eco cards.
3. Die Umweltdatenträger werden nach den allgemeinen technischen Spezifikationen in Anhang C. hergestellt, programmiert und angebracht. Das ministerium für Seefahrt, Verkehr und Kommunikation der Republik Croatia ist befugt, die Umweltdatenträger zu genehmigen, zu programmierung und anzubringen. Environmental data carriers shall be prepared, programmed and attached in accordance with the general technical specifications set out in Annex C. The Ministry of Navigation, Transport and Communication of the Republic of Croatia shall be empowered to approve, programme and attach the environmental data carriers.
The environmental data carrier shall contain information on the country of origin and NOx emissions of the vehicle, in accordance with the indications in the COP-Bescheinigung (Conformity of Production), and on the conformity of current production in accordance with paragraph 4.
The environmental data carrier shall be affixed to the windscreen of the vehicle.
Its position is set out in Annex D. It is not transferable.
4. Der fahrer eines am oder nach dem 1. Oktober 1990 zugelassenen kroatischen Lastkraftwagens hat ebenfalls eine COP-Bescheinigung gemäß Anhang E zum Nachweis der NOx-Emissionen dieses Fahrzeugs mit sich zu führen und auf Verlangen vorzuweisen. The driver of a Croatian lorry registered on or after 1 October 1990 shall also carry with him a COP-certificate in accordance with Annex E to prove the NOx emissions of that vehicle and, on request, must provide it.
For heavy goods vehicles registered for the first time before 1 October 1990 or for which no document can be provided, a COP-value of 15,8 g/ kWh shall be used.
5. The Ministry of Navigation, Transport and Communication of the Republic of Croatia is empowered to issue the documents and environmental data carriers referred to in paragraphs 2 to 4.
6. Sofern das Fahrzeug keinen Umweltdatenträger verwendet, werden die erforderlichen Ökoppunkten auf der Ökokarte angebracht und entwertet. Unless the vehicle uses an environmental data carrier, the ecopoints required shall be placed on the ecological map and validated.
The eco card shall be validated as follows:
( a) By stamping the eco card in an eco card stamping machine;
( b) stamping of the eco card by the Austrian border control upon entry into Austria;
( c) by stamping and dating of the ecomap by the national authorities of the road haulage undertaking prior to its entry into Austrian territory;
( d) by stamping of the eco-map by a body carrying out the initial activation of environmental data carriers.
The Austrian border crossing points equipped with an eco-card stamping machine are listed in Annex F.
For statistical purposes, page 1 of the completed eco card shall be collected either by the Austrian authorities or returned by the competent authorities to the Austrian authorities within three months of the end of the journey.
The resulting statistical information shall be used by the Commission for proposals for the distribution of the ecopoint reserve.
Where the vehicle is equipped with an environmental data carrier, a number of ecopoints corresponding to the information on the vehicle <unk> s NOx emissions stored on the environmental data carrier shall be subtracted from the total ecopoints allocated to the Republic of Croatia during an ecopoint transit.
This shall be carried out through an infrastructure provided and operated by the Austrian authorities.
In the case of vehicles carrying environmental data carriers, any bilateral journeys of the environmental data carriers prior to driving on Austrian territory shall be adjusted in such a way as to permit proof that the journey is not a transit one.
If an eco card is used and a tractor is exchanged during a transit journey, the confirmation of payment issued at the time of entry shall remain valid and shall be kept.
If the COP-value of the new tractor exceeds the value indicated on the form, additional ecopoints affixed to a new map shall be invalidated upon departure.
7. Durchgehende trip, die die einmalig Überschreitung der Österreichische Grenze per Bahn - ob im konventionellen Eisenbahnverkehr oder im kombinierten Verkehr - und die Grenzüberschreitung auf der Strasse vor oder nach der Überschreitung per Bahn umfassen, werden nicht als Straßengfreitertransitverkehr durch Österreich, sondern als bilaterale Reisen gewertet. Crossings which include the single crossing of the Austrian border by rail, whether by conventional rail or combined transport, and the crossing by road before or after the crossing by rail shall not be considered as road freight transit through Austria, but as bilateral journeys.
Bilateral journeys shall be transit journeys through Austria using the following railway terminals:
Fürnitz, Villach Süd, Sillian, Innsbruck / Hall, Brennersee, Graz.
8. Die Ökoppunkte sind vom 1. Januar des Jahres, für das sie vergeben wurden, bis zum 31. Januar des folgenden jahres gültig. Ecopoints shall be valid from 1 January of the year for which they were awarded to 31 January of the following year.
9. Violations of this Agreement by the driver of a Croatian lorry or undertaking shall be punished in accordance with the applicable national legislation.
The Commission and the competent Austrian and Croatian authorities shall, within the limits of their competence, assist each other in the investigation and prosecution of such violations and, in particular, shall ensure that ecomaps and environmental data carriers are used and handled correctly.
Checks may be carried out at the discretion of the Member State of the European Community at a location other than the internal frontier, provided that the principle of non-discrimination is not violated.
10. Die Österreichische Aufsichtsbehörden können unter Wahrung des Proznismäigkeitsgrundsatzes geeignete Maßnahmen ergreifen, wenn ein Fahrzeug mit einem Umweltdatenträger ausgestattet ist und mindestens einer der folgenden Sachverhalte vorliegen: The Austrian supervisory authorities may, in accordance with the principle of proportionality, take appropriate measures where a vehicle is equipped with an environmental data carrier and at least one of the following circumstances is present:
( a) repeated violations, either caused by the vehicle or committed by the operator;
( b) there are no longer sufficient ecopoints available for Croatia;
( c) the environmental data medium has been manipulated or exchanged by a Party other than the party authorized under paragraph 3;
( d) Croatia has not allocated sufficient ecopoints to the vehicle for transit;
( e) the vehicle does not have appropriate documentation in accordance with paragraph 2 (c) or (d) to prove that the setting up of the environmental data carrier after which the voyage in question is not considered as a transit voyage on Austrian territory is permissible;
( f) the environmental data medium described in Annex C is not equipped with sufficient ecopoints for transit.
The Austrian supervisory authorities may, in accordance with the principle of proportionality, take appropriate measures where a vehicle is not equipped with an environmental data carrier and at least one of the following facts is present:
( a) no ecomap shall be submitted to the supervisory authorities in accordance with the provisions of this Agreement;
( b) submit an ecomap which is incomplete or incorrect or on which the ecopoints are not correctly affixed;
( c) the vehicle does not have the relevant documentation to prove that it does not need ecopoints; or
( d) the eco card has not been validated in accordance with the procedure referred to in paragraph 6.
11. Die gedruckten Ökoppunkte, die zum Ansetzen auf den Ökokarten bestimmt sind, werden jährlich vor dem 1. November des Vorjahres zur Verfügung gestellt. Printed ecopoints intended for affixing to eco maps shall be made available annually before 1 November of the previous year.
12. For vehicles registered before 1 October 1990 and whose engines have since been replaced, the COP-value of the new engine shall apply.
In this case, the certificate issued by the competent authority shall include a note of engine replacement and specify the new COP value for NOx emissions.
13. Eine Transitfahrt ist von der Bezahlung mit Ökopunkten ausgenommen, wenn die folgenden drei Bedingungen zuttreffen: A transit journey shall be exempt from payment with ecopoints if the following three conditions apply:
( a) the sole purpose of the journey is to transport a brand new vehicle or combination of vehicles from the manufacturer to the destination in another State;
( b) no goods shall be transported;
( c) the vehicle or combination of vehicles shall have relevant international registration documents and export plates.
14. Eine Transitfahrt ist von der Bezahlung mit Ökopunkten ausgenommen, wenn es es um die unladen Teilstrecke einer Fahrt handelt, für die gemäß Anhang A keine Ökoppunkten zu entrichten sind und geeignete Unterlagen mitführen werden, die dies voucher. A transit journey shall be exempt from payment with ecopoints if it is the unloaded section of a journey for which no ecopoints are payable in accordance with Annex A and appropriate documentation is carried to prove this.
( a) a waybill, or
( b) a completed eco card without any ecopoints attached to it, or
( c) a completed eco card with ecopoints which may be reused at a later date.
15. Alle Probleme im Zusammenhang mit der Verwaltung dieses Ökopunktesystems werden dem nach Artikel 41 des Interimsabkommens eingesetzten Interimsunterausschuss Verkehr Gemeinschaft/ Republik Croatia vorgelegt; der Ausschuss bewertet die Situation und recommennete Maßnahmen. Any problems relating to the administration of this ecopoint system shall be referred to the Interim Subcommittee on Transport, Community / Republic of Croatia, established pursuant to Article 41 of the Interim Agreement, which shall assess the situation and recommend appropriate measures.
All measures to be taken shall be implemented immediately, in accordance with the principles of proportionality and non-discrimination.
I should be obliged if you would confirm the agreement of your Government to the contents of this letter.
Please accept, Sir, the assurance of my highest consideration.
On behalf of the Council of the European Union
between the European Union and the United States of America on extradition
THE EUROPEAN UNION AND THE UNITED STATES OF AMERICA,
DESIRING to further facilitate cooperation between the Member States of the European Union and the United States of America,
DESIRING to combat crime more effectively in order to protect their democratic societies and their common values,
BEARING IN MIND the rights of the individual and the rule of law,
BEARING IN MIND the guarantees embodied in their respective legal systems that provide for the right of extradited persons to a fair trial, including the right to a judgment by an impartial and duly established tribunal,
DESIRING to conclude an agreement on the extradition of criminals,
The Contracting Parties undertake, in accordance with the provisions of this Agreement, to take measures to strengthen cooperation in the framework of extradition relations between the Member States and the United States of America applicable to the extradition of criminals.
1. Der Begriff <unk> Vertragsparteien <unk> bedeutet die Europäische Union und die Vereinigten Staaten von Amerika. <unk> Parties <unk> means the European Union and the United States of America.
2. Der Begriff <unk> Mitgliedstaat <unk> bedeutet einen Mitgliedstaat der Europäischen Union. <unk> Member State
3. Der Begriff <unk> Justizministerium <unk> bedeutet im Falle der Vereinigten Staaten von Amerika das Justizministerium der Vereinigten Staaten; im Falle eines Mitgliedstaats dessen Justizministerium, mit der Ausnahme, daß im Falle eines Mitgliedstaats, in dem die in den Artikeln 3, 5, 6, 8 und 12 beschriebenen Aufgaben vom Generalstaatsanwalt wahrgenommen werden, dieser nach Artikel 19 benannt werden kann, um die Rolle des Justizministerium zu übernehmen, es sei denn, die Vereinigten Staaten und der betreffende Mitgliedstaat vereinbaren, eine andere Stelle zu benennen. <unk> The term <unk> Ministry of Justice
Scope of this Agreement in relation to bilateral extradition treaties with the Member States
( 1) Die Europäische Union entsprechend dem Vertrag über die Europäischen Union und die Vereinigten Staaten von Amerika tragen dafür Sorge, daß die Bestimmungen dieses Abkommens wie folgt Anwendung in Bezug auf bilaterale AuslieferungsVerträge finden, die zwischen den Mitgliedstaaten und den Vereinigten Staaten von Amerika zum Zeitpunkt des Inkrafttretens dieses Abkommens in Kraft sind: The European Union, in accordance with the Treaty on the European Union and the United States of America, shall ensure that the provisions of this Agreement apply, as follows, to bilateral extradition treaties concluded between the Member States and the United States of America at the time of entry into force of this Agreement:
( a) Article 4 shall apply in lieu of provisions of bilateral treaties which permit extradition solely for a list of specific offences.
( b) Article 5 shall apply in lieu of provisions of bilateral treaties concerning the transmission, confirmation, legalization or legalization of a request for extradition of the documentation supplied therefor by the requesting State.
( c) Article 6 shall apply in the absence of provisions in bilateral treaties concerning the direct transmission of requests for provisional arrest between the United States Department of Justice and the Department of Justice of the Member State concerned.
( d) Article 7 shall apply in addition to provisions of bilateral treaties concerning the transmission of requests for extradition.
( e) Article 8 shall apply in the absence of provisions of bilateral treaties providing for supplementary information; if the provisions of bilateral treaties do not specify the method of transmission to be applied, paragraph 2 of that Article shall also apply.
( f) Article 9 shall apply, in the absence of provisions of bilateral treaties, for the temporary transfer of persons subject to proceedings in the requested State or who are serving a sentence therein.
( g) Article 10, unless otherwise provided, shall apply in lieu of or in the absence of provisions of bilateral treaties concerning the decision on multiple requests for extradition of the same person.
( h) Article 11 shall apply in the absence of provisions in bilateral treaties concerning the waiver of the formal extradition procedure or simplified extradition procedures.
( i) Article 12 shall apply in the absence of provisions of bilateral contracts for transit; if the provisions of bilateral treaties do not specify the procedure for an unscheduled landing of aircraft, paragraph 3 of that Article shall also apply.
( j) Article 13 may be applied by the requested State in place of, or in the absence of, provisions of bilateral treaties on the death penalty.
( k) Article 14 shall apply in the absence of provisions in bilateral treaties concerning the treatment of confidential information in the framework of a request.
( 2) a) Die Europäische Union trägt entsprechend dem Vertrag über die Europäischen Union dafür Sorge, daß jeder Mitgliedstaat in einer zwischen ihm und den Vereinigten Staaten von Amerika erstellten Urkunde anerkennt, daß sein geltender Auslieferungsvertrag mit den Vereinigten Staaten von Amerika in der in diesem Artikel dargelegten Weise zur Anwendung gelangt. The European Union shall, in accordance with the Treaty on the European Union, ensure that each Member State, in an instrument drawn up between it and the United States of America, recognises that its current extradition treaty with the United States of America applies in the manner set out in this Article.
( b) The European Union shall, in accordance with the Treaty on European Union, ensure that new Member States which accede to the European Union after the entry into force of this Agreement and which have concluded bilateral extradition treaties with the United States of America take the measures referred to in subparagraph (a) of this Article.
( c) The Contracting Parties shall endeavour to complete the operation described in subparagraph (b) of this Article before the planned accession of a new Member State or as soon as possible thereafter.
The European Union shall inform the United States of America of the date of accession of new Member States.
( 3) Ist der in Absatz 2 Buchstabe b) genannte Vorgang am Tag des Beitrittsts nicht abgeschlossen, so gelten die Bestimmungen dieses Abkommens im Rahmen der Beziehungen zwischen dem betreffenden neuen Mitgliedstaat und den Vereinigten Staaten von Amerika ab dem Datum, an dem sie sich einander einander und die Europäische Union davon unterrichtet haben, daß ihre diesbezüglichen internen Verfahren abgeschlossen sind. If the operation referred to in paragraph 2 (b) of this Article has not been completed on the date of accession, the provisions of this Agreement shall apply in the framework of relations between the new Member State concerned and the United States of America from the date on which they have informed each other and the European Union that their respective internal procedures have been completed.
( 1) Ausgeliefert wird wegen Verbrechen, die nach dem Recht des ersuchenden und des ersuchten Staates mit einer Freiheit punishment im Hoechstmaß von mindestens einem Jahr oder einer strengeren Strafe bedroomed sind. Extradition shall be made for offences under the law of the requesting and requested State punishable by a maximum term of imprisonment of at least one year or more.
He shall also be extradited for attempting or agreeing to commit, or participating in, an extraditable offence.
Where the request relates to the enforcement of a sentence imposed on a person for a crime capable of extradition, the term of imprisonment to be served shall be not less than four months.
( 2) Wird die Auslieferung für eine auslieferungsfähige Strafat bewilligt, so gilt sie auch für jede andere in dem Ersuchen genannte Strafat, die mit Freiheit fined von einem Jahr oder weniger drohist ist, wenn alle anderen Auslieferungsbedingungen erfuellt sind. If extradition is granted for an extradition capable offence, it shall also apply to any other offence referred to in the request which is threatened with imprisonment of one year or less if all other extradition conditions are met.
( 3) Für die Zwecke dieses Artikels gilt eine Strafat unabhängig davon als auslieferungsfähig, For the purposes of this Article, a criminal offence shall be deemed capable of extradition independently thereof,
( a) whether the law of the requesting State and that of the requested State places it in the same category of crime or describes it in the same terms;
( b) whether it is an offence for which United States federal law requires, solely for the purpose of establishing the jurisdiction of a United States Federal Tribunal, elements of a crime such as the movement of persons or goods between States or the use of mail or other means of conducting trade between States or foreign trade;
( c) whether in charges, taxes, customs, foreign exchange and foreign trade matters the law of the requesting State and that of the requested State provide for the same kind of charges, taxes, customs duties or foreign exchange restrictions or foreign trade restrictions in respect of the same type of goods.
( 4) Was die Strafat außerhalb des Hoheitsgebiets des ersuchenden Staates begangen, so wird die Auslieferung unter den anderen für sie geltenden Bedingungen bewilligt, wenn nach dem Recht des ersuchten Staates eine unter derartigen Umständen außerhalb seiner Hoheitsgebiet begangen ist Strafbar ist. If the offence was committed outside the territory of the requesting State, extradition shall be granted under the other conditions applicable to it, if under the law of the requested State an act committed under such circumstances outside its territory is punishable.
If, under such circumstances, an act committed outside its territory is not a criminal offence under the law of the requested State, it shall be at the discretion of the competent authority of the requested State to grant the extradition, provided that all other conditions of extradition have been fulfilled.
( 1) Auslieferungsersuchen und die dazugehörigen Unterlagen werden auf dem diplomatischen Weg übermittelt, wozu auch die Übermittlung gemäß Artikel 7 gehört. Requests for extradition and related documents shall be communicated by diplomatic means, including transmission pursuant to Article 7.
( 2) Unterlagen, die den Stempel oder das Siegel des Justizministerium oder des für Auswärtige Angelegenheiten zuständigen Ministeriums des ersuchenden Staates tragen, gelten in Auslieferungsverfahren im ersuchten Staat ohne weitere Bestätigung, Beglaubigung oder sonstige Legalisierung. Documents bearing the stamp or seal of the Ministry of Justice or the ministry of the requesting State responsible for foreign affairs shall be considered in extradition proceedings in the requested State without further confirmation, authentication or other legalization.
Requests for provisional arrest may also be communicated directly between the ministries of justice of the requesting State and of the requested State, except through diplomatic channels.
The channels of the International Criminal Police Organisation (Interpol) may also be used for the transmission of such a request.
Submission of documentation following the provisional arrest
( 1) Wird die Person, um deren Austradition ersucht wird, vom ersuchten Staat in vorläufigen Haft hält, so kann der ersuchende Staat seiner Verpflichtung nach Artikel 5 Absatz 1, sein Auslieferungsersuchen und die dazugehörigen Unterlagen auf dem diplomatischen Weg zu übermitteln, dadurch nachkommen, daß er das Ersuchen und die Unterlagen der Embassy des ersuchten Staates im ersuchenden Staat vorlegt. If the requested State holds the person in provisional detention, the requesting State may, in accordance with Article 5 (1), fulfil its obligation to communicate its request for extradition and the relevant documents by diplomatic route by presenting the request and the documents to the requested State <unk> s embassy in the requesting State.
In this case, the date of receipt of the request by the Embassy shall be considered to be the date of receipt by the requested State for the purpose of applying the time limits to be observed in accordance with the extradition treaty in force for the purpose of holding the person in question in custody.
( 2) Kann ein Mitgliedstaat am Tag der Unterzeichnung dieses Abkommens aufgrund der an diesem Tag in seiner innerstaatlichen Rechtsordnung geltenden ständigen Rechtsprechung die in Absatz 1 genannten Maßnahmen nicht treffen, so findet dieser Artikel auf diesen Mitgliedstaat so lange keine Anwendung, bis dieser Mitgliedstaat und die Vereinigten Staaten von Amerika durch diplomatischen Notenwechsel eine andere Vereinbarung treffen. If, on the date of signature of this Agreement, a Member State is unable to meet the measures referred to in paragraph 1 of this Article on the basis of the consistent case law applicable on that date in its domestic legal system, this Article shall not apply to that Member State until that Member State and the United States of America reach another agreement by exchanging diplomatic notes.
( 1) Der ersuchte Staat kann den ersuchenden Staat suchen, binnen einer von ihm gesetzten angemessenen Frist ergänzende Angaben vorzulegen, wenn seines Erachtens die zur Begründung des Auslieferungsersuchens zur Verfügung gestellten Unterlagen die Anforderungen des geltenden Auslieferungsvertrags nicht sufficiend erfuellen. The requested State may ask the requesting State to provide supplementary information within a reasonable period set by it if, in its opinion, the documents made available to justify the request for extradition do not satisfy sufficiently the requirements of the extradition treaty in force.
( 2) Solche ergänzenden Angaben können unmittelbar zwischen den Justizministen der betreffenden Staaten erbeten und übermittelt werden. Such supplementary information may be requested and communicated directly between the Ministries of Justice of the States concerned.
( 1) Wird ein Austradition ersuchen im Falle einer Person bewilligt, gegen die im ersuchten Staat ein Verfahren anhäng ist oder die dort eine Strafverbüßt, so kann der ersuchte Staat die betreffende Person an den ersuchenden Staat zum Zwecke der Strafverfolgung vorübergehend überstellen. If a request for extradition is granted in the case of a person against whom proceedings are pending in the requested State or who is serving a sentence there, the requested State may temporarily transfer that person to the requesting State for the purpose of criminal prosecution.
( 2) Die so überstellte Person wird im ersuchenden Staat in Haft hält und nach Abschluss des Verfahrens gegen sie unter Bedingungen, die vom ersuchenden und ersuchten Staat einvernehmlich festzulegen sind, an den ersuchten Staat zurücküberstellt. The person so transferred shall be held in custody in the requesting State and shall be returned to the requested State upon completion of the proceedings against him, subject to conditions to be agreed by the requesting and requesting State.
The period of detention in the territory of the requesting State in the course of prosecution in that State may be subtracted from the period of detention to be served in the requested State.
Requests for extradition and surrender from several States
( 1) Erhält der ersuchte Staat vom ersuchenden Staat und von einem anderen Staat oder anderen Staaten Ersuchen um Auslieferung der selben Person entweder wegen derselben Strafat oder wegen verschiedener Verbrechen, so entscheidet die führende Behörde des ersuchten Staates, dem Staat die Person gegebenenfalls überstellt wird. If the requested State receives a request from the requesting State and from another State or other States for the extradition of the same person, either for the same offence or for various offences, the executing authority of the requested State shall decide which State the person may be transferred.
( 2) Erhält ein ersuchter Mitgliedstaat ein Austradition ersuchen der Vereinigten Staaten von Amerika und ein Übergabeersuchen nach dem Europäischen Warrant for the Same Person entweder wegen derselben Strafat oder wegen verschiedener Verbrechen, so entscheidet die zuständigen Behörde des ersuchten Mitgliedstaats, dem Staat die Person gegebenenfalls übertragen wird. If a requested Member State receives a request for extradition from the United States of America and a request for surrender pursuant to the European Arrest Warrant for the Same Person, either for the same offence or for different offences, the competent authority of the requested Member State shall decide which State may hand over the person.
For this purpose, the competent authority shall be the executive authority of the requested Member State when, under the bilateral extradition treaty in force between the United States and the Member State, decisions on competing requests are taken by that authority; if this is not governed by the bilateral extradition treaty, the competent authority shall be designated by the Member State concerned in accordance with Article 19.
( 3) Bei seiner Entscheidung nach den Absätzen 1 und 2 berücksichtigt der ersuchte Staat alle berechgeblichen Umstände, einschließlich unter anderem solcher, die bereits im geltenden Auslieferungsvertrag genannt sind, und in Ermangelung solcher Angaben der folgenden Umstände: In making its decision in accordance with paragraphs 1 and 2 of this Article, the requested State shall take into account all relevant circumstances, including, inter alia, those already mentioned in the applicable extradition treaty, and in the absence of such information, the following circumstances:
( a) the contractual basis for the requests;
( b) the places where the offences were committed;
( c) the respective interests of the requesting States;
( d) the seriousness of the offences;
( e) the nationality of the victim;
( f) the possibility of further delivery between the requesting States;
( g) the chronological sequence of receipt of the requests from the requesting States.
If the person to be extradited consents to his surrender to the requesting State, the requested State may transfer that person as quickly as possible without further procedures, in accordance with the principles and procedures of its legal system.
The consent of the person to be extradited may include the waiver of the protection of the principle of speciality.
( 1) Ein Mitgliedstaat kann gestatten, daß eine Person, die von einem Drittstaat an die Vereinigten Staaten von Amerika oder von den Vereinigten Staaten von Amerika an einen Drittstaat überstellt wird, durch sein Hoheitsgebiet befördert wird. A Member State may allow a person transferred from a third State to the United States of America or from the United States of America to a third State to be transported through its territory.
The United States of America may authorize the carriage through its territory of a person transferred from a third State to a Member State or from a Member State to a third State.
( 2) Ein Durchlieferungsersuchen wird auf diplomatischem Weg oder unmittelbar zwischen dem Justizministerium der Vereinigten Staaten und dem Justizministerium des betreffenden Mitgliedstaats gestellt. A request for transit shall be made by diplomatic route or directly between the Ministry of Justice of the United States and the Ministry of Justice of the Member State concerned.
The channels of Interpol may also be used for the transmission of such a request.
The request shall contain a description of the person to be surrendered and a brief summary of the facts of the case.
A person to be extradited shall be held in custody for the duration of the transit.
( 3) Eine Genehmigung ist nicht erforderlich, wenn der Luftweg benutzt wird und keine Zwischenlandung im Hoheitsgebiet des Durchlieferungsstaates vorgesehen ist. No authorisation shall be required if the air route is used and no stopover is provided in the territory of the transit State.
In the event of an unscheduled landing, the State in which it is made may request that a request for transit be made in accordance with paragraph 2 of this Article.
All necessary measures shall be taken to prevent the person in question from fleeing until the transit has been completed, provided that the request for transit is received within 96 hours of the unscheduled landing.
If the offence for which extradition is sought is threatened with the death penalty under the laws of the requesting State, but not under the laws of the requested State, the requested State may grant extradition on condition that the requested person is not subject to the death penalty or, if such a condition cannot be satisfied by the requesting State for procedural reasons, on condition that the death penalty, if imposed, is not enforced.
If the requesting State accepts extradition under the conditions set out in this Article, it shall fulfil those conditions.
If the requesting State does not accept the conditions, the request for extradition may be refused.
If the requesting State considers, in response to its request for extradition, the provision of particularly sensitive information, it may seek information from the requested State as to the extent to which that information can be protected by the requested State.
If the requested State is unable to protect the information in the manner desired by the requesting State, the requesting State shall decide whether the information is nevertheless provided.
The Contracting Parties shall consult each other to the appropriate extent for the purpose of making the most effective use of this Agreement and for the purpose of facilitating the settlement of any disputes concerning the interpretation and application of this Agreement.
( 1) Dieses Abkommen gilt für vor oder nach seinem Inkrafttreten begangen Straftaten. This Agreement shall apply to crimes committed before or after its entry into force.
( 2) Dieses Abkommen gilt für nach seinem Inkrafttreten gestellte Auslieferungsersuchen. This Agreement shall apply to requests for extradition made after its entry into force.
However, Articles 4 and 9 shall also apply to requests pending in a requested State at the time of the entry into force of this Agreement.
( 1) Dieses Abkommen schließt nicht aus, daß der ersuchte Staat Gründe für eine Ablehnung aufgrund eines Umstandes geltend macht, der durch dieses Abkommen nicht geregelt ist, sich jedoch aus einem geltenden bilateralen Auslieferungsvertrag zwischen einem Mitgliedstaat und den Vereinigten Staaten von Amerika ergibt. This Agreement does not preclude the requested State from making a claim for refusal on the basis of a circumstance not covered by this Agreement but arising out of a valid bilateral extradition treaty between a Member State and the United States of America.
( 2) In den Fällen, in denen die Verfassungsgrundsätze des ersuchten Staates oder die für diesen verbindlichen endgülterlichen Entscheidungen ein Hindernis für die Erfuellung seiner Auslieferungspflicht darstellen können und dieses Abkommen oder der geltende bilaterale Vertrag keine Regelung dieser Angelegenheit vorsehen, konsultieren sich der ersuchte und der ersuchende Staat. In cases where the constitutional principles of the requested State or the final binding decisions of that State may constitute an obstacle to the fulfilment of its extradition obligation and where this Agreement or the bilateral Treaty in force do not provide for any regulation of this matter, the requested State and the requesting State shall consult each other.
This Agreement shall not preclude the conclusion, after its entry into force, of bilateral agreements between a Member State and the United States of America in conformity with this Agreement.
The European Union shall notify the United States of America of any designation made pursuant to Article 2 (3) and Article 10 (2) before the instruments referred to in Article 3 (2) are exchanged between the Member States and the United States of America.
( 1) Dieses Abkommen gilt für: This Agreement shall apply to:
( a) the United States of America;
( b) the European Union, for:
- territories for which external relations fall within the competence of a Member State, or for countries which are not Member States for which a Member State has other external relations obligations, provided that the Contracting Parties have reached an agreement by means of the exchange of a diplomatic note duly confirmed by that Member State.
( 2) Die Anwendung dieses Abkommens auf Gebiete oder Länder, für die eine Ausdehnung der Geltung in Einklang mit Absatz 1 Buchstabe b) vorgesehen wurde, kann von jeder der Vertragsparteien gegenüber der anderen Vertragspartei mit einer Frist von sechs Monaten schriftlich auf diplomatischem Wege vorbehaltlich einer ordnungsgemäßen Bestätigung zwischen dem betreffenden Mitgliedstaat und den Vereinigten Staaten von Amerika gekündigen werden. Application of this Agreement to territories or countries for which an extension of validity in accordance with paragraph 1 (b) of this Article has been provided may be terminated by either of the Contracting Parties in writing to the other Contracting Party by a period of six months, subject to proper confirmation between the Member State concerned and the United States of America.
The Contracting Parties agree to undertake a joint review of this Agreement as soon as necessary, but not later than five years after its entry into force.
The review shall relate in particular to the practical implementation of the Agreement and may also include aspects such as the impact of any further development of the European Union on the subject matter of this Agreement, including Article 10.
( 1) Dieses Abkommen tritt am ersten Tag nach Ablauf des dritten Monats nach dem Zeitpunkt in Kraft, zu dem die Vertragsparteien die Urkunden über den Abschluss ihrer diesbezüglichen internen Verfahren Exchange haben. This Agreement shall enter into force on the first day following the expiry of the third month following the date on which the Contracting Parties have exchanged their instruments of conclusion of their respective internal procedures.
These instruments also indicate that the steps referred to in paragraph 2 of Article 3 have been taken.
( 2) Jede Vertragspartei kann dieses Abkommen jederzeit durch schriftliche Mitteilung an die andere Vertragspartei kündigen, und diese Kündigung wird sechs Monate nach dem Zeitpunkt der Mitteilung wirksam. Any Contracting Party may, at any time, denounce this Agreement by giving written notice to the other Contracting Party, and such denunciation shall take effect six months after the date of such notification.
on mutual legal assistance between the European Union and the United States of America
THE EUROPEAN UNION AND THE UNITED STATES OF AMERICA,
DESIRING to further facilitate cooperation between the Member States of the European Union and the United States of America,
DESIRING to combat crime more effectively in order to protect their democratic societies and their common values,
BEARING IN MIND the rights of the individual and the rule of law,
BEARING IN MIND the guarantees embodied in their respective legal systems which provide for the right of defendants to a fair trial, including the right to a judgment by an impartial and duly established tribunal,
DESIRING to conclude an Agreement on mutual legal assistance in criminal matters,
The Contracting Parties undertake to take measures to strengthen cooperation and mutual legal assistance in accordance with the provisions of this Agreement.
1. Der Begriff <unk> Vertragsparteien <unk> bedeutet die Europäische Union und die Vereinigten Staaten von Amerika, <unk> Contracting Parties
2. Der Begriff <unk> Mitgliedstaat <unk> bedeutet einen Mitgliedstaat der Europäischen Union. <unk> Member State
Scope of this Agreement in relation to and in the absence of bilateral agreements with Member States on mutual legal assistance
( 1) Die Europäische Union entsprechend dem Vertrag über die Europäischen Union und die Vereinigten Staaten von Amerika tragen dafür Sorge, daß dieses Abkommen wie folgt Anwendung in Bezug auf bilaterale Verträge über Rechtshilfe findet, die zwischen den Mitgliedstaaten und den Vereinigten Staaten von Amerika zum Zeitpunkt des Inkrafttretens dieses Abkommens in Kraft sind: The European Union, in accordance with the Treaty on the European Union and the United States of America, shall ensure that this Agreement applies, as follows, to bilateral treaties on mutual legal assistance between the Member States and the United States of America in force at the time of the entry into force of this Agreement:
( a) Article 4 shall apply in order to permit the identification of bank balances and transactions in addition to powers already available under the provisions of bilateral treaties.
( b) Article 5 shall apply in order to permit the formation and operation of joint investigation teams in addition to powers already available under the provisions of bilateral treaties.
( c) Article 6 shall apply in order to permit, in addition to powers already available under the provisions of bilateral treaties, the interrogation of a person in the requested State by video transmission technology between the requesting State and the requested State.
( d) Article 7 shall apply in order to permit the use of accelerated means of communication in addition to powers already available under the provisions of bilateral treaties.
( e) Article 8 shall apply in order to permit mutual legal assistance to the administrative authorities concerned, in addition to powers already available under the provisions of bilateral treaties.
( f) Subject to the provisions of paragraphs 4 and 5 of Article 9, Article 9 shall apply in lieu of or in the absence of provisions of bilateral treaties relating to limitations on the use of information or evidence made available by the requesting State and to conditions on mutual legal assistance or refusal thereof on data protection grounds.
( g) Article 10 shall apply in the absence of provisions in bilateral treaties concerning the circumstances in which a requesting State may require its request to be treated as confidential.
( 2) a) Die Europäische Union trägt entsprechend dem Vertrag über die Europäischen Union dafür Sorge, daß jeder Mitgliedstaat in einer zwischen ihm und den Vereinigten Staaten von Amerika erstellten Urkunde anerkennt, daß sein geltender bilateraler Vertrag über Rechtshilfe mit den Vereinigten Staaten von Amerika in der in diesem Artikel dargelegten Weise zur Anwendung gelangt. The European Union shall, in accordance with the Treaty on European Union, ensure that each Member State, in an instrument drawn up between it and the United States of America, recognises that its current bilateral mutual legal assistance treaty with the United States of America applies in the manner set out in this Article.
( b) The European Union shall, in accordance with the Treaty on European Union, ensure that new Member States which accede to the European Union after the entry into force of this Agreement and which have concluded bilateral treaties on mutual legal assistance with the United States of America take the measures referred to in subparagraph (a) of this Article.
( c) The Contracting Parties shall endeavour to complete the operation described in subparagraph (b) of this Article before the planned date of accession of a new Member State or as soon as possible thereafter.
The European Union shall inform the United States of America of the date of accession of new Member States.
( 3) a) Die Europäische Union entsprechend dem Vertrag über die Europäischen Union und die Vereinigten Staaten von Amerika tragen auch dafür Sorge, daß die Bestimmungen dieses Abkommens zur Anwendung gelangen, wenn zwischen einem Mitgliedstaat und den Vereinigten Staaten von Amerika kein bilateraler Vertrag über Rechtshilfe in Kraft ist. The European Union, in accordance with the Treaty on the European Union and the United States of America, shall also ensure that the provisions of this Agreement are applied where no bilateral mutual legal assistance treaty is in force between a Member State and the United States of America.
( b) The European Union shall, in accordance with the Treaty on European Union, ensure that each Member State, in an instrument drawn up between it and the United States of America, recognises that the provisions of this Agreement are being applied.
( c) The European Union shall, in accordance with the Treaty on European Union, ensure that new Member States which accede to the European Union after the entry into force of this Agreement and which have not concluded bilateral treaties on mutual legal assistance with the United States of America, take the measures referred to in subparagraph (b) of this Article.
( 4) Ist der in Absatz 2 Buchstabe b) und Absatz 3 Buchstabe c) genannten Vorgang am Tag des Beitritts nicht abgeschlossen, so gelten die Bestimmungen dieses Abkommens im Rahmen der Beziehungen zwischen den Vereinigten Staaten von Amerika und dem betreffenden neuen Mitgliedstaat ab dem Datum, an dem sie sich gegenseitig und die Europäische Union davon haben, daß ihre diesbezüglichen internen Verfahren abgeschlossen sind. If the operation referred to in paragraph 2 (b) and paragraph 3 (c) of this Article has not been completed on the date of accession, the provisions of this Agreement shall apply in the framework of relations between the United States of America and the new Member State concerned, as from the date on which they have informed each other and the European Union that their respective internal procedures have been completed.
( 5) Die Vertragsparteien kommen überein, daß dieses Abkommen nur die Rechtshilfe zwischen den betreffenden Staaten regelt. The Contracting Parties agree that this Agreement shall govern only mutual legal assistance between the States concerned.
The provisions of this Agreement shall not give rise to any right of a private person to obtain, dispose of or exclude evidence or to prevent the execution of a request and shall not extend or restrict any other domestic law.
( 1) a) At the request of the requesting State, the requested State shall, in accordance with the provisions of this Article, immediately investigate whether the banks established in its territory can provide information as to whether a particular natural or legal person suspected of a criminal offence or charged with such a crime is the holder of one or more bank accounts.
The requested State shall promptly communicate the results of its enquiries to the requesting State.
( b) The steps referred to in subparagraph (a) of this Article may also be taken to provide information on:
( i) information concerning natural or legal persons convicted or otherwise involved in criminal activities;
( ii) information held by non-banking financial institutions; and
( iii) financial transactions not related to bank accounts.
( 2) Ein Request um Informationen nach Absatz 1 umfasst A request for information pursuant to paragraph 1 shall include:
( a) the identity of the natural or legal person relevant to the location of such accounts; and
( b) information sufficient to enable the competent authority of the requested State to:
( i) reasonably believe that the natural or legal person concerned was involved in an offence and that banks or non-banking financial institutions in the territory of the requested State are in possession of the requested information;
( ii) establish that the information requested relates to criminal investigations or criminal proceedings;
( c) as far as possible, information as to which bank or non-banking financial entity may be affected and other information the availability of which may help to limit the scope of the investigation.
( 3) Rechtshilfeersuchen nach diesem Artikel erfolgen zwischen: Requests for legal assistance under this Article shall be made between:
( a) the central authorities in the Member States having jurisdiction over mutual legal assistance designated in accordance with Article 15 (2), or the national authorities of the Member States having jurisdiction over the investigation and prosecution of criminal offences; and
( b) the national authorities of the United States designated in accordance with Article 15 (2) with jurisdiction over the investigation and prosecution of criminal offences.
The Contracting Parties may, after the entry into force of this Agreement, arrange, by exchanges of diplomatic notes, an amendment to the channels of communication through which requests under this Article shall be made.
( 4) a) Vorbehaltlich des Buchstabens (b) kann ein Staat nach Artikel 15 seine Verpflichtung zur Leistung von Rechtshilfe nach diesem Artikel begrenzen auf Subject to subparagraph (b), a State may, pursuant to Article 15, limit its obligation to provide mutual legal assistance under this Article to:
( i) acts liable to prosecution under the laws of both the requested and the requesting State;
( ii) offences punishable by imprisonment or imprisonment of a maximum of not less than four years in the requesting State and not less than two years in the requested State; or
( iii) certain serious offences liable to prosecution under the laws of both the requested and the requesting State.
( b) A State which limits its obligations in accordance with subparagraphs (a) (ii) and (iii) shall at least permit the identification, under the law of both the requesting and the requested State, of bank accounts related to terrorist activities and the laundering of proceeds from a wide range of serious crimes.
( 5) Die Rechtshilfe darf im Rahmen dieses Artikels nicht aus Gründen des Bankgeheimnisses verweigert werden. Mutual legal assistance shall not be denied under this Article for reasons of bank secrecy.
( 6) Der ersuchte Staat reagiert Ersuchen um Vorlage von Aufzeichnungen über die nach diesem Artikel ermittelten Bankguthaben oder Transaktionen entsprechend den Bestimmungen des zwischen den betreffenden Staaten geltenden Vertrags über Rechtshilfe oder in Ermangelung eines solchen Vertrags entsprechend den Anforderungen seines internen Rechts. The requested State shall respond to requests for records of bank deposits or transactions established pursuant to this Article in accordance with the provisions of the mutual legal assistance treaty between the States concerned or, in the absence of such a treaty, in accordance with the requirements of its internal law.
( 7) Die Vertragsparteien ergreifen Maßnahmen, damit sich für die ersuchten Staaten aufgrund der Anwendung dieses Artikels keine außergewöhnliche belastung ergibt. The Contracting Parties shall take measures to ensure that the application of this Article does not give rise to an exceptional burden on the States concerned.
Nevertheless, if an exceptional burden should arise for a requested State, including for banks or through the provision of the communication channels provided for in this Article, the Contracting Parties shall enter into consultations without delay with a view to facilitating the application of this Article also by taking measures to reduce the existing and future burden.
( 1) Soweit die Vertragsparteien dies noch nicht getan haben, ergreifen sie die erforderlichen Maßnahmen, damit gemeinsame Ermittlungteams gebildet und im Hoheitsgebiet jedes Mitgliedstaats und der Vereinigten Staaten von Amerika eingesetzt werden können, so daß kriminalPolizeiliche Ermittlungen und eine Strafverfolgung, an der einer oder mehrere der Mitgliedstaaten und die Vereinigten Staaten von Amerika beteiligt sind, erleichtert werden, wenn der betreffende Mitgliedstaat und die Vereinigten Staaten von Amerika dies für zweckmäßig erachten. To the extent that the Contracting Parties have not yet done so, they shall take the necessary steps to establish joint investigation teams and to facilitate criminal investigations and prosecutions involving one or more of the Member States and the United States of America where appropriate by the Member State concerned and the United States of America.
( 2) Die für das jeweiligen Team berechgeblichen Modalitäten wie Zusammensetzung, Bestandsdauer, Standort, Organisation, Funktionen, Zweck und Umfang der Beteiligung von Teammitglieder aus einem Staat an Ermittlungen im Gebiet eines anderen Staates werden im Einvernehmen zwischen den betreffenden für die Ermittlung und Verfolgung von Straftaten und von den jeweiligen Staaten bestimmten zuständigen Behörden festgelegt. The modalities relevant to the respective team, such as composition, duration, location, organisation, functions, purpose and scope of participation of team members from one State in investigations in the territory of another State, shall be determined by mutual agreement between the competent authorities concerned for the investigation and prosecution of criminal offences and the competent authorities designated by the respective States.
( 3) Die betreffenden von den jeweiligen Staaten bestimmten zuständigen Behörden treten zum Zwecke der Bildung und des Einsatzes solcher Ermittlungteams in unmittelbaren Kontakt, außer wenn sich die Staaten diesbezüglich auf andere geeignete Kommunikationsmittel einigen, weil außergewöhnliche Komplexität, große Tragweite oder andere Umstände in Bezug auf einige oder auf alle Aspekte eine zentralere Koordinierung erforderlich erscheinen lassen. The competent authorities concerned, as determined by the respective States, shall enter into direct contact for the purpose of establishing and deploying such investigative teams, except when the States agree on other appropriate means of communication in this respect because of exceptional complexity, broad scope or other circumstances with respect to some or all aspects of central coordination may appear necessary.
( 4) Verlangt die Arbeit eines gemeinsamen Ermittlungteams Ermittlungen maßnahmen in einem der Staaten, von denen es gebildet wurde, so kann ein von diesem Staat in das Team entsentes Mitglied die zuständigen Behörden seines Staates ersuchen, diese Maßnahmen zu ergreifen, ohne daß die übrigen Staaten ein Rechtshilfeersuchen einreichen müssen. If the work of a joint investigative team requests investigative measures in one of the States from which it has been constituted, a member of that State may request the competent authorities of that State to take such measures without the other States having to submit a request for legal assistance.
The legal standard required for taking the measure in that State shall be that required for domestic investigations.
( 1) Die Vertragsparteien treffen die erforderlichen Vorkehrungen, damit zwischen jedem Mitgliedstaat und den Vereinigten Staaten von Amerika für die VerHearing eines Zeugen oder eines Sachverständigen in einem Strafverfahren, in dem Rechtshilfe gewährt wird, in einem ersuchten Staat der Einsatz der Video-Übertragungstechnik möglich ist, sofern diese Möglichkeit derzeit noch nicht besteht. The Contracting Parties shall make the necessary arrangements to permit the use of video transmission technology in criminal proceedings between any Member State and the United States of America, in a requested State, provided that such possibility does not currently exist.
In the absence of specific provisions in this Article, the arrangements shall be those provided for in the Treaty in force on mutual legal assistance between the States concerned or, where appropriate, in accordance with the law of the requested State.
( 2) Sofern zwischen dem ersuchenden und dem ersuchten Staat nichts anderes vereinbart wird, trägt der ersuchende Staat die Kosten für die Einrichtung und den Betrieb der Video-Übertragung. Unless otherwise agreed between the requesting State and the requested State, the requesting State shall bear the costs of the installation and operation of the video transmission.
Other costs related to the provision of such assistance (including, inter alia, travel expenses of the persons concerned in the requested State) shall be borne in accordance with the applicable provisions of the applicable mutual legal assistance treaty between the States concerned or, in the absence of such a treaty, in accordance with the arrangement between the requesting State and the requested State.
( 3) Der ersuchende und der ersuchte Staat können Konsultationen aufnehmen, um die Lösung rechtlicher, technischer und logistischen Fragen, die bei der Ausführung des Ersuchens auftreten können, zu erleichtern. The requesting State and the requested State may enter into consultations to facilitate the resolution of legal, technical and logistical issues which may arise in the course of the execution of the request.
( 4) Unbeschadet der Rechtsprechung des ersuchenden Staats ist die Abgabe einer absichtlich falsche Erklärung oder eine andere Verfehlung eines Zeugen oder Sachverständigen während der Video-Konferenz im ersuchten Staat in derselben Weise Strafbar, wie dies in einem innerstaatlichen Verfahren der Fall wäre. Without prejudice to the jurisprudence of the requesting State, the issuing of a deliberately false declaration or any other misconduct by a witness or expert during the video conference in the requested State shall be punishable in the same way as would be the case in domestic proceedings.
( 5) Dieser Artikel gilt unbeschadet des Einsatzes sonstiger Mittel zur Vernehmung im ersuchten Staat gemäß dem anwendbaren Vertrags- oder Gesetzrecht. This Article shall apply without prejudice to the use of other means of interrogation in the requested State in accordance with applicable treaty or law.
( 6) Dieser Artikel gilt unbeschadet der Anwendung der Bestimmungen der bilateralen Abkommen über Rechtshilfe zwischen den Mitgliedstaaten und den Vereinigten Staaten von Amerika, die den Einsatz der Video-Übertragungstechnik für andere als die in Absatz 1 genannten Zwecke vorschreiben oder gestatten, wie beispielsweise für Zwecke der Identifizierung von Personen oder Gegenständen oder der Festhaltung von Ermittlungen feststellungen. This Article shall apply without prejudice to the application of the provisions of the bilateral mutual legal assistance agreements between the Member States and the United States of America which prescribe or permit the use of video transmission technology for purposes other than those referred to in paragraph 1, such as, for example, for purposes of identification of persons or objects or the detention of investigative findings.
A State may also authorize the use of video transmission technology in such cases where this is not already provided for in applicable contract or statutory law.
Requests for mutual legal assistance and corresponding communications may be made by means of accelerated means of communication such as fax or electronic mail, followed by formal confirmation, if so requested by the requested State.
The requested State shall reply to the request by one of these accelerated means of communication.
( 1) Rechtshilfe wird auch einer nationalen Verwaltungsbehörde gewährt, die Ermittlungen zu Handlungen mit Blick auf deren strafrechtliche Verfolgung oder Verweisung an die Ermittlungen oder Strafverfolgungsbehörden führt und diese Ermittlungen aufgrund ihrer spezifischen Verwaltungsrechtlichen oder rechtlichen Befugnis führt. Mutual assistance shall also be granted to a national administrative authority which conducts investigations into acts with a view to their criminal prosecution or referral to the investigative or criminal prosecution authorities and which conducts such investigations on the basis of its specific administrative or statutory powers.
In such circumstances, mutual legal assistance may also be provided to other administrative authorities.
No mutual legal assistance shall be granted in respect of matters in which the administrative authority considers that there will be no persecution or referral.
( 2) a) Requests for mutual legal assistance under this Article shall be made between the central authorities designated under the bilateral mutual legal assistance treaty between the States concerned, or between other bodies in accordance with an agreement of the central authorities.
( b) In the absence of a Treaty, requests shall be made between the Ministry of Justice of the United States of America and the Ministry of Justice of the Member State concerned, or a ministry with jurisdiction over the transmission of requests for mutual assistance which is comparable to that provided for in Article 15 (1), or between other authorities designated by such Ministries on both sides.
( 3) Die Vertragsparteien ergreifen Maßnahmen, damit sich für die ersuchten Staaten aufgrund der Anwendung dieses Artikels keine außergewöhnliche belastung ergibt. The Contracting Parties shall take measures to ensure that the application of this Article does not give rise to an exceptional burden on the States concerned.
Nevertheless, if an exceptional burden should arise for a requested State, the Contracting Parties shall enter into consultations without delay with a view to facilitating the application of this Article also by taking measures to reduce the existing and future burden.
Limited use to protect personal and other data
( 1) Der ersuchende Staat kann alle vom erlangten Staat erlangten Beweismittel oder Informationen verwenden The requesting State may use any evidence or information obtained from the requested State.
( a) for the purposes of its criminal investigations and criminal proceedings;
( b) to avert a direct and serious threat to its public security;
( c) in its non-criminal judicial and administrative procedures, which are directly related to investigations and procedures;
( i) those referred to in subparagraph (a); or
( ii) mutual legal assistance has been provided in accordance with Article 8;
( d) for any other purpose, where the information or evidence has become public knowledge in the course of the proceedings for which it has been communicated or in any of the cases referred to in subparagraphs (a), (b) and (c); and
( e) for any other purpose, only with the prior consent of the requested State.
( 2) a) Dieser Artikel schließt nicht aus, daß der ersuchte Staat in einem besonderen Fall zusätzliche Bedingungen aufstellen kann, wenn das spezifische Rechtshilfeersuchen ohne solche Bedingungen nicht erledigt werden könnte. This Article does not preclude the possibility of the requested State, in a special case, imposing additional conditions where the specific request for mutual legal assistance could not be made without such conditions.
Where additional conditions have been laid down in accordance with this subparagraph, the requested State may require the requesting State to provide information on the use of the evidence and information.
( b) The requested State shall not, as a condition for the provision of evidence and information within the meaning of subparagraph (a), impose any general restrictions with respect to the legal standards of the requesting State relating to the handling of personal data.
( 3) Stellt der ersuchte Staat nach der Weitergabe an den ersuchenden Staat Umstände fest, die ihn veranlassen können, in einem bestimmten Fall eine zusätzliche Bedingung zu stellen, so kann der ersuchte Staat sich mit dem ersuchenden Staat ins Benehmen setzen, um festzulegen, inwieweit die Beweismittel und die Informationen geschützt werden können. If, after transfer to the requesting State, the requested State finds circumstances which may induce it to make an additional condition in a particular case, the requested State may engage with the requesting State to determine to what extent the evidence and information may be protected.
( 4) Ein ersuchter Staat kann anstelle dieses Artikels die in dem geltenden bilateralen Vertrag über Rechtshilfe enthaltene Bestimmung über die beschränte Verwendung von Daten anwenden, wenn dies zu einer weniger stark Begrenzung der Verwendung von Informationen und Beweismitteln als nach den Bestimmungen dieses Artikels führt. An requested State may, in lieu of this Article, apply the provision in the bilateral mutual legal assistance treaty in force on the limited use of data, if this results in a less severe limitation on the use of information and evidence than under the provisions of this Article.
( 5) Ist nach einem beim Zeitpunkt der Unterzeichnung dieses Abkommens geltenden bilateralen Vertrag über Rechtshilfe zwischen einem Mitgliedstaat und den Vereinigten Staaten von Amerika die Einschränkung der Verpflichtung zur Leistung von Rechtshilfe in Bezug auf bestimmte Steuerzuwiderhandlungen zulässig, so kann der betreffende Mitgliedstaat in seinem Austausch von Urkunden mit den Vereinigten Staaten von Amerika nach Artikel 3 Absatz 2 angeben, daß er in Bezug auf solche Zuwiderhandlungen weiterhin die in diesem Vertrag enthaltene Bestimmung über die beschränte Verwendung von Daten anwendet. If, after a bilateral mutual legal assistance treaty in force at the time of signature of this Agreement between a Member State and the United States of America permits the restriction of the obligation to provide mutual legal assistance in respect of certain tax offences, the Member State concerned may, in its exchange of documents with the United States of America in accordance with Article 3 (2), specify that, with respect to such offences,
The requested State shall make every effort to keep a request and its contents confidential when the requesting State requests such confidentiality.
If the request cannot be carried out without breaching the desired confidentiality, the central authority of the requested State shall inform the requesting State, which shall then decide whether the request should nevertheless be carried out.
The Contracting Parties shall consult each other to the appropriate extent for the purpose of making the use of this Agreement as effective as possible and for the purpose of facilitating the settlement of any dispute concerning the interpretation and application of this Agreement.
( 1) Dieses Abkommen gilt für vor oder nach seinem Inkrafttreten begangen Straftaten. This Agreement shall apply to crimes committed before or after its entry into force.
( 2) Dieses Abkommen gilt für nach seinem Inkrafttreten gestellte Rechtshilfeersuchen. This Agreement shall apply to requests for legal assistance made after its entry into force.
However, Articles 6 and 7 shall also apply to requests pending in a requested State at the time of the entry into force of this Agreement.
Subject to the provisions of Articles 4 (5) and 9 (2) (b), this Agreement shall not preclude the requested State from claiming grounds for rejecting mutual legal assistance arising out of a bilateral mutual legal assistance treaty or, where such a treaty does not exist, from its applicable legal principles, including in the event that the execution of the request would prejudice the sovereignty, security, public policy and other fundamental interests of that State.
Future bilateral agreements with Member States on mutual legal assistance
This Agreement shall not constitute an obstacle to the conclusion, after its entry into force, of bilateral agreements between a Member State and the United States of America in conformity with this Agreement.
( 1) Was im Rahmen von Artikel 8 Absatz 2 Buchstabe b) ein anderes ministerium als das Justizministerium benannt, so notifiziert die Europäische Union den Vereinigten Staaten von Amerika eine solche Benennung vor Austausch der Urkunden zwischen den Mitgliedstaaten und den Vereinigten Staaten von Amerika nach Artikel 3 Absatz 3. If, under Article 8 (2) (b), a different Ministry than the Ministry of Justice is designated, the European Union shall notify the United States of America of such designation prior to the exchange of instruments between the Member States and the United States of America in accordance with Article 3 (3).
( 2) Vor Austausch der Urkunden zwischen den Mitgliedstaaten und den Vereinigten Staaten von Amerika nach Artikel 3 Absätze 2 und 3 notifizieren sich die Vertragsparteien nach gegenseitigen Konsultationen darüber, welche nationalen Behörden mit Zuständigkeit für die Ermittlung und Verfolgung von Verbrechen nach Artikel 4 Absatz 3 zu benennen sind, welche die benannten nationalen Behörden sind. Prior to the exchange of instruments between the Member States and the United States of America pursuant to Article 3 (2) and (3), the Contracting Parties shall, after consultation with each other, notify themselves of which national authorities with jurisdiction for the investigation and prosecution of offences referred to in Article 4 (3) are to be designated, which are the designated national authorities.
For those Member States which do not have a mutual legal assistance treaty with the United States of America, the European Union shall, prior to such exchange, notify the United States of America, which is the central authority in accordance with Article 4 (3).
( 3) Die Vertragsparteien notifizieren einander vor Austausch der Urkunden zwischen den Mitgliedstaaten und den Vereinigten Staaten von Amerika nach Artikel 3 Absätze 2 und 3 jede nach Artikel 4 Absatz 4 geltend gegrenzung der Verwendung von Daten. The Contracting Parties shall notify each other before the exchange of instruments between the Member States and the United States of America pursuant to Article 3 (2) and (3) of any limitation on the use of data made in accordance with Article 4 (4).
( 1) Dieses Abkommen gilt für: This Agreement shall apply to:
( a) the United States of America;
( b) the European Union, for:
- territories for which external relations fall within the competence of a Member State, or for countries which are not Member States for which a Member State has other external relations obligations, provided that the Contracting Parties have concluded an arrangement by way of exchange of a diplomatic note duly confirmed by that Member State.
( 2) Die Anwendung dieses Abkommens auf Gebiete oder Länder, für die eine Ausdehnung der Geltung in Einklang mit Buchstabe b) vorgesehen wurde, kann von jeder der Parteien gegenüber der anderen Vertragspartei mit einer Frist von sechs Monaten schriftlich auf diplomatischem Wege vorbehaltlich einer ordnungsgemäßen Bestätigung zwischen dem betreffenden Mitgliedstaat und den Vereinigten Staaten von Amerika gekündigen werden. Application of this Agreement to territories or countries for which an extension of validity has been provided in accordance with subparagraph (b) of this Article may be terminated by either of the Parties in writing to the other Contracting Party by a period of six months, subject to proper confirmation between the Member State concerned and the United States of America.
The Contracting Parties agree to undertake a joint review of this Agreement not later than five years after its entry into force.
The review shall relate in particular to the practical implementation of the Agreement and may also include aspects such as the impact of the further development of the European Union on the subject matter of this Agreement.
( 1) Dieses Abkommen tritt am ersten Tag nach Ablauf des dritten Monats nach dem Zeitpunkt in Kraft, zu dem die Vertragsparteien untereinander die Urkunden über den Abschluss ihrer diesbezüglichen internen Verfahren Exchange haben. This Agreement shall enter into force on the first day following the expiry of the third month following the date on which the Contracting Parties have exchanged among themselves their instruments of conclusion of their respective internal procedures.
These instruments also indicate that the steps referred to in paragraphs 2 and 3 of Article 3 have been taken.
( 2) Jede Vertragspartei kann dieses Abkommen jederzeit durch schriftliche Mitteilung an die andere Vertragspartei kündigen, und diese Kündigung wird sechs Monate nach dem Zeitpunkt der Mitteilung wirksam. Any Contracting Party may, at any time, denounce this Agreement by giving written notice to the other Contracting Party, and such denunciation shall take effect six months after the date of such notification.
Cooperation on anti-competitive activities between the European Community and the Government of Japan
( hereinafter referred to as <unk> the Contracting Parties
RECOGNISING that the interdependence of the economies of all countries, including the European Community and Japan, is progressing,
CONSCIOUS that the well considered and effective enforcement of competition law by the European Community and Japan, respectively, is important for the performance of their markets and for their trade with each other,
CONSCIOUS that cooperation and, where appropriate, coordination between the Contracting Parties would facilitate the well considered and effective enforcement of competition law in the European Community and Japan respectively,
CONSCIOUS that from time to time differences may arise between the Contracting Parties in the application of the competition laws of the European Community and Japan respectively,
RESOLVED to take into account the important interests of the other Contracting Party in the application of the competition laws of the European Community or Japan (hereinafter referred to as <unk> the competition laws of the Contracting Parties <unk>), and
CONSIDERING the recommendation of the Council of the Organisation for Economic Cooperation and Development of 27 and 28 July 1995 on cooperation between Member States in the field of restrictive practices affecting international trade and the recommendation of the Council of the Organisation for Economic Cooperation and Development of 25 March 1998 on measures to be taken against harmful cartels (
( 1) Ziel dieses Abkommens ist es, durch Förderung der Zusammenarbeit und Abstimmung zwischen den Wettbewerbsbehörden der Vertragsparteien zu einer wirksamen Durchsetzung des Wettbewerbsrechts der Vertragsparteien beizutragen und die Möglichkeiten für Konflikte zwischen den Vertragsparteien in allen Angelegenheiten, die die Anwendung ihres Wettbewerbsrechts berühren, zu vermeiden oder zu begrenzen. The objective of this Agreement is to contribute, by promoting cooperation and coordination between the competition authorities of the Parties, to effective enforcement of the competition laws of the Parties and to avoid or limit the possibilities for conflict between the Parties in all matters affecting the application of their competition laws.
( 2) Für die Zwecke dieses Abkommens bezeichnet: For the purposes of this Agreement:
( a) <unk> anti-competitive activities
( b) <unk> competent competition authority of a Member State
At the time of signature of this Agreement, the Commission of the European Communities shall transmit a list of such authorities to the Government of Japan.
The Commission shall provide the Government of Japan with an updated list as soon as necessary.
Information referred to in Article 9 (6) of this Agreement shall not be transmitted to the competent authority of a Member State until that authority is on the list provided by the Commission to the Government of Japan;
( c) <unk> competent competition authorities
( i) for the European Community: the Commission of the European Communities in respect of its powers under European Community competition law; and
( ii) for Japan: the Fair Competition Commission;
( d) <unk> competition law
( i) for the European Community: Articles 81, 82 and 85 of the Treaty establishing the European Community, Council Regulation (EEC) No 4064 / 89 on the control of concentrations between undertakings and their implementing regulations in accordance with the Treaty, and any amendments thereto; and
( ii) for Japan: the Law on the Prohibition of Private Monopolies and on the Preservation of Fair Competition (Law 54 of 1947, hereinafter referred to as <unk> the Antimonopoly Law <unk>), with its implementing regulations and all its amendments;
( e) <unk> enforcement activities
Except where studies, studies or surveys are carried out with a view to examining the general economic situation or economic conditions in a particular sector of the economy.
Such investigations, studies or surveys shall not be designed to include investigations into suspected infringements of competition law;
( f) <unk> the territory of one Contracting Party
( g) <unk> the law of one Contracting Party <unk>, <unk> the law of the Contracting Party <unk> and <unk> the law of the other Contracting Party
( 1) Die Wettbewerbsbehörde einer Vertragspartei unterrichtet die Wettbewerbsbehörde der anderen Vertragspartei von den Durchsetzungsmaßnahmen, die ihrer Ansicht nach wichtige Belange der anderen Vertragspartei berühren können. The competition authority of a Contracting Party shall inform the competition authority of the other Contracting Party of enforcement measures which it considers may affect important interests of the other Contracting Party.
( 2) Durchsetzungsmaßnahmen, die wichtige Belange der anderen Vertragspartei berühren können, sind Maßnahmen, die Important Belange der anderen Vertragspartei berühren können, sind Maßnahmen, die
( a) are relevant to the enforcement activities of the other Contracting Party;
( b) against nationals of the other Contracting Party (in the case of the European Community nationals of the Member States of the European Community) or against companies registered or established in the territory of the other Contracting Party in accordance with the applicable law;
( c) relate to anti-competitive activities, other than mergers or acquisitions, a substantial part of which take place in the territory of the other Party;
( d) a merger or acquisition involving:
( i) at least one of the undertakings concerned; or
( ii) an undertaking controlling at least one of the undertakings concerned;
means a company registered or established in the territory of the other Party in accordance with the applicable law;
( e) relate to conduct which the teaching competition authority considers to have been required, encouraged or approved by the other Contracting Party; or
( f) the imposition by a competition authority of or request for sanctions or remedies which would require or prohibit certain conduct in the territory of the other Contracting Party.
( 3) Mitteilungen nach Absatz 1 ergehen in Bezug auf Zusammenschlüsse oder Übernahmen spätestens: Notifications pursuant to paragraph 1 shall be made with respect to mergers or takeovers not later than:
( a) in the case of the European Community:
( i) the decision to initiate the procedure provided for in Article 6 (1) (c) of Regulation (EEC) No 4064 / 89; and
( ii) a statement of objections;
( b) for Japan:
( i) the date on which documents, reports or other information relating to the proposed concentration are requested pursuant to the Antimonopoly Act; and
( ii) the date on which a recommendation or decision to call a hearing is made.
( 4) Mitteilungen nach Absatz 1 ergehen in allen Fällen mit Ausnahme von Zusammenschlüssen oder Übernahmen so rechtzeitig vor den nachstehend aufgeführten Maßnahmen, wie es praktisch möglich ist: In all cases, with the exception of mergers or takeovers, notifications referred to in paragraph 1 of this Article shall be made in good time before the measures listed below, as practically possible:
( a) in the case of the European Community:
( i) a statement of objections; or
( ii) the adoption of a decision or settlement;
( b) for Japan:
( i) initiation of criminal proceedings;
( ii) the filing of a complaint requesting a preliminary injunction;
( iii) the adoption of a recommendation or decision to call a hearing; and
( iv) the imposition of a fine where no recommendation has previously been made to the payer.
( 5) Die Mitteilungen müssen ausreichende Angaben enthalten, damit die unterrichtete Vertragspartei eine erste Bewertung der Auswirkungen der Durchsetzungsmaßnahmen auf ihre eigenen wichtigen Belange vornehmen kann. The notifications shall contain sufficient information to enable the Contracting Party to make an initial assessment of the impact of enforcement activities on its own important interests.
( 1) Die Wettbewerbsbehörde jeder Vertragspartei unterstützt die Wettbewerbsbehörde der anderen Vertragspartei bei ihren Durchsetzungsmaßnahmen im Rahmen ihrer üblicherweise verfügbaren Mittel in einem Umfang, das mit dem für die unterstützende Vertragspartei maßgebenden Recht und den für sie maßgebenden wichtigen Belangen vereinbar ist. The competition authority of each Contracting Party shall assist the competition authority of the other Contracting Party in its enforcement activities to an extent consistent with the law applicable to the supporting Contracting Party and the important interests relevant to it.
( 2) Der Wettbewerbsbehörde jeder Vertragspartei obliegen in einem mit dem Recht der jeweiligen Vertragspartei und ihren wichtigen Belangen zu vereinbarenden Umfang folgende Aufgaben: The competition authority of each Contracting Party shall, to an extent consistent with the law of the respective Contracting Party and its important interests, have the following functions:
( a) inform the competition authority of the other Contracting Party of enforcement measures against anti-competitive activities which the receiving competition authority considers may adversely affect competition in the territory of the other Contracting Party;
( b) provide to the competition authority of the other Contracting Party important information held or of which the forwarding competition authority is aware and which relates to anti-competitive activities which the forwarding competition authority considers may be material to the enforcement activities of the competition authority of the other Contracting Party or may justify its enforcement activities; and
( c) Transmission to the competition authority of the other Contracting Party, at its request and in accordance with the terms of this Agreement, of information held by the transmitting competition authority relevant to the enforcement activities of the competition authority of the other Contracting Party.
( 1) Führen die Wettbewerbsbehörden beider Vertragsparteien Durchsetzungsmaßnahmen in Bezug auf miteinander verbundene Vorgänge durch, ziehen sie eine Abstimmung ihrer Durchsetzungsmaßnahmen in Erwägung. Where the competition authorities of both Parties carry out enforcement activities with respect to interrelated transactions, they shall consider coordinating their enforcement activities.
( 2) Bei der Erwägung, ob im Zusammenhang mit bestimmten Durchsetzungsmaßnahmen eine Abstimmung erfolgen sollte, berücksichtigen die Wettbewerbsbehörden der Vertragsparteien unter anderem folgende Gesichtpunkten: When considering whether coordination should be made in connection with specific enforcement activities, the competition authorities of the Parties shall, inter alia, take into account the following aspects:
( a) the impact of the coordination on their ability to achieve the objectives of their enforcement activities;
( b) the relative capacity of the competition authorities of the Contracting Parties to obtain the information necessary to carry out the enforcement activities;
( c) the extent to which the competition authority of either Party may take effective remedies against the anti-competitive activities in question;
( d) the possibility of more efficient use of resources;
( e) possible cost savings for the benefit of those affected by the enforcement activities; and
( f) the potential benefits to Contracting Parties and to persons affected by enforcement activities of concerted remedies.
( 3) Stimmen die Wettbewerbsbehörden der Vertragsparteien ihre Durchsetzungsmaßnahmen ab, berücksichtigt jede Wettbewerbsbehörde bei ihren Durchsetzungsmaßnahmen sorgfältig die Ziele, die die andere Wettbewerbsbehörde mit ihren Maßnahmen verfolgt. If the competition authorities of the Contracting Parties vote to adopt their enforcement measures, each competition authority shall take due account of the objectives pursued by the other competition authority in its enforcement activities.
( 4) Führen die Wettbewerbsbehörden beider Vertragsparteien Durchsetzungsmaßnahmen in Bezug auf miteinander verbundene Vorgänge durch, prüft die Wettbewerbsbehörde jeder Vertragspartei auf Ersuchen der Wettbewerbsbehörde der anderen Vertragspartei, soweit dies mit den wichtigen Belangen der ersuchten Vertragspartei vereinbar ist, ob Personen, die vertrauliche Informationen im Zusammenhang mit den betreffenden Durchsetzungsmaßnahmen mitgeteilt haben, der Weitergabe dieser Informationen an die Wettbewerbsbehörde der anderen Vertragspartei zustimmen. Where the competition authorities of both Contracting Parties carry out enforcement activities with respect to interrelated transactions, the competition authority of each Contracting Party, at the request of the competition authority of the other Contracting Party, shall, to the extent that is compatible with the important interests of the requested Contracting Party, examine whether persons who have communicated confidential information relating to the enforcement activities in question agree to the disclosure of such information to the competition authority of the other
( 5) Vorbehaltlich einer ordnungsgemäßen Mitteilung an die Wettbewerbsbehörde der anderen Vertragspartei können die Wettbewerbsbehörden jeder Vertragspartei die Abstimmung der Durchsetzungsmaßnahmen jederzeit einschränken oder beenden und ihre Durchsetzungsmaßnahmen allein fortführen. Subject to proper notification to the competition authority of the other Party, the competition authorities of each Party may at any time restrict or terminate the coordination of enforcement activities and may continue their enforcement activities alone.
( 1) Nimmt die Wettbewerbsbehörde einer Vertragspartei an, daß deren wichtige Belange durch wettbewerbswidrige Verhaltensweisen im Gebiet der anderen Vertragspartei beeinträchtigt werden, kann sie in Ansehcht der Wichtigkeit, Zuständigkeitskonflikte zu vermeiden, und unter Berücksichtigung des Umstands, daß die Wettbewerbsbehörde der anderen Vertragspartei in einer besseren Position sein könnte, um wirksamer gegen die betreffenden wettbewerbswidrigen Verhaltensweisen vorzugehen, die Wettbewerbsbehörde der anderen Vertragspartei ersuchen, geeignete Durchsetzungsmaßnahmen zu ergreifen. In the event that the competition authority of a Contracting Party accepts that its important interests are affected by anti-competitive activities in the territory of the other Contracting Party, it may, taking into account the importance of avoiding conflicts of jurisdiction, and taking into account the fact that the competition authority of the other Contracting Party might be in a better position
( 2) In dem Ersuchen sind die Merkmale des wettbewerbswidrigen Verhaltens und dessen Auswirkungen auf wichtige Belange der Vertragspartei der ersuchenden Wettbewerbsbehörde so genau wie möglich anzugeben und zusätzliche Informationen und sonstige Formen der Zusammenarbeit anzubieten, die bereitzustellen die ersuchende Wettbewerbsbehörde in der Lage ist. The request shall specify the characteristics of competitive conduct and its impact on important interests of the Contracting Party to the requesting competition authority as accurately as possible and shall offer additional information and other forms of cooperation that the requesting competition authority is able to provide.
( 3) Die ersuchte Wettbewerbsbehörde erwägt sorgfältig, ob gegen das im Ersuchen angegebene wettbewerbswidrige verhalten Durchsetzungsmaßnahmen eingeleitet oder laufenden Durchsetzungsmaßnahmen ausgebreitet werden sollen. The competition authority concerned shall carefully consider whether enforcement action should be taken against the anticompetitive activities referred to in the request, or whether current enforcement activities should be expanded.
The Requested Competition Authority shall communicate its decision to the Requesting Competition Authority as soon as practicable.
Where enforcement action is initiated, the requested competition authority shall inform the requesting competition authority of the outcome of the action and, where possible, of important developments that have occurred in the meantime.
( 4) Dieser Artikel schränkt weder das Ermessen der ersuchten Wettbewerbsbehörde ein, nach Maßgabe ihres Wettbewerbsrechts und ihrer Durchsetzungspraxis gegen die in dem Ersuchen mitgeteilten wettbewerbswidrigen Verhaltensweisen vorzugehen, noch steht er der Rücknahme des Ersuchens durch die ersuchende Wettbewerbsbehörde entgegen. This Article shall not restrict the discretion of the requested competition authority to act, in accordance with its competition laws and enforcement practices, against the anticompetitive activities referred to in the request, nor shall it preclude the requesting competition authority from withdrawing the request.
( 1) Die Wettbewerbsbehörde jeder Vertragspartei erwägt sorgfältig die wichtigen Belange der anderen Vertragspartei in allen Phasen der Durchführung ihrer Durchsetzungsmaßnahmen, einschließlich der Entscheidung über die Einleitung von Durchsetzungsmaßnahmen, den Umfang von Durchsetzungsmaßnahmen und die Art der im Einzelfall angestrebten Sanktionen oder Abhilfemaßnahmen. The competition authority of each Contracting Party shall carefully consider the other Contracting Party <unk> s important interests in all phases of the implementation of its enforcement activities, including the decision on the initiation of enforcement activities, the scope of enforcement activities and the nature of the sanctions or remedies sought in individual cases.
( 2) Teilt eine Vertragspartei der anderen Vertragspartei mit, daß bestimmte Durchsetzungsmaßnahmen der letzteren Vertragspartei ihre wichtigen Belange beeinträchtigen könnten, sorgt die letztere Vertragspartei dafür, daß die erstere Vertragspartei rechtzeitig über wichtige Entwicklungen bei der Durchführung der Durchsetzungsmaßnahmen unterrichtet wird. If a Contracting Party notifies the other Contracting Party that certain enforcement activities of the latter Contracting Party may affect its important interests, the latter Contracting Party shall ensure that the former Contracting Party is notified in good time of important developments in the implementation of the enforcement activities.
( 3) Ist eine Vertragspartei der Ansicht, daß wichtige Belange der anderen Vertragspartei durch Durchsetzungsmaßnahmen beeinträchtigt werden könnten, sollte die Vertragsparteien zusätzlich zu allen anderen Faktoren, die unter den gegebenen Umständen für eine angemessene Abwiegung ihrer konkurrierenden Belange relevsind, folgende Gesichtpunkte berücksichtigen: If a Party considers that the other Party <unk> s important interests could be adversely affected by enforcement activities, the Parties should, in addition to any other factors relevant under the circumstances to an appropriate assessment of its competing interests, consider the following:
( a) the relative importance of the anti-competitive activities or transactions in question in the territory of one Contracting Party as compared to the activities or transactions in the territory of the other Contracting Party;
( b) the relative impact of anti-competitive activities on the important interests of each Party;
( c) the presence or absence of evidence in the territory of the Contracting Party which is carrying out the enforcement activities of any intention of the parties to the anti-competitive activities to prejudice consumers, suppliers or competitors;
( d) the extent to which anti-competitive activities significantly restrict competition on the markets of the European Community or Japan;
( e) the degree of discrepancy or consistency between one Contracting Party <unk> s enforcement activities and the law or policy or important interests of the other Contracting Party;
( f) whether natural or legal persons shall be subject to conflicting requirements of the Contracting Parties;
( g) the location of the assets concerned and the whereabouts of those involved in the operation;
( h) the extent to which the Contracting Party <unk> s enforcement activities can provide for effective sanctions or other remedies against the anti-competitive activities; and
( i) the extent to which enforcement action by the other Contracting Party against the same natural or legal persons would be affected.
( 1) Die Vertragsparteien können einander erforderlichenfalls in allen Fragen im Zusammenhang mit diesem Abkommen auf diplomatischem Weg konsultieren. The Contracting Parties may consult each other diplomatically on any matter relating to this Agreement.
( 2) Das Ersuchen um Konsultation nach diesem Artikel wird auf diplomatischem Weg übermittelt. The request for consultation under this Article shall be communicated by diplomatic route.
( 1) Die Wettbewerbsbehörden der Vertragsparteien konsultieren einander auf Ersuchen der Wettbewerbsbehörde einer der Vertragsparteien in allen Fragen, die sich bei der Durchführung dieses Abkommens stellen könnten. The competition authorities of the Contracting Parties shall, at the request of the competition authority of one of the Contracting Parties, consult each other on all matters which may arise in the implementation of this Agreement.
( 2) Die Wettbewerbsbehörden der Vertragsparteien treten mindestens einmal im Jahr zusammen, um The competition authorities of the Parties shall meet at least once a year to:
( a) exchange information on their ongoing enforcement activities and priorities in respect of each Contracting Party <unk> s competition law;
( b) exchange information on sectors of common interest;
( c) to discuss any changes they may consider to the approach; and
( d) to discuss other issues of mutual interest relating to the application of the competition laws of the Contracting Parties.
( 1) Ungeachtet der sonstigen Bestimmungen dieses Abkommens ist keine Vertragspartei verpflichtet, Informationen an die andere Vertragspartei weiterzugeben, wenn diese Weitergabe nach dem Recht der Vertragspartei, die über die Informationen verfügt, verboten ist oder mit ihren wichtigen Belangen unvereinbar wäre. Notwithstanding the other provisions of this Agreement, no Contracting Party shall be obliged to disclose information to the other Contracting Party if such disclosure is prohibited under the law of the Contracting Party which has the information or would be incompatible with its important interests.
( 2) a) Andere als allgemein zugängliche Informationen, die eine Vertragspartei der anderen Vertragspartei nach Maßgabe dieses Abkommens übermittelt, werden von der empfangenden Vertragspartei nur für die Zwecke des Artikels 1 Absatz 1 benutzt. Information transmitted by one Party to the other Party in accordance with the provisions of this Agreement other than generally available information shall be used by the receiving Party only for the purposes of Article 1 (1).
( b) Where a Contracting Party discloses information in confidence in accordance with the terms of this Agreement, the receiving Contracting Party shall maintain such confidentiality in accordance with its laws.
( 3) Eine Vertragspartei kann verlangen, daß die nach diesem Abkommen weitergegebenen Informationen gemäß den von ihr genannten Bedingungen verwendet werden. A Contracting Party may require that the information transferred pursuant to this Agreement be used in accordance with the conditions specified by it.
Without the prior consent of the other Contracting Party, the receiving Contracting Party shall not use such information in a manner contrary to these conditions.
( 4) Jede Vertragspartei kann die Informationen, die sie der anderen Vertragspartei übermittelt, einschränken, wenn letztere nicht die von ersterer geforderte Gewähr für die Wahrung der Vertraulichkeit, die Einhaltung der genannten Bedingungen oder der Beschränkungen des Verwendungszwecks bieten kann. Any Contracting Party may restrict the information it transmits to the other Contracting Party if the latter is unable to provide the guarantee requested by the former for the maintenance of confidentiality, compliance with the said conditions or the limitations of the intended use.
( 5) Dieser Artikel steht der Nutzung oder Weitergabe von anderen als allgemein zugänglichen Informationen durch die empfangende Vertragspartei nicht entgegen, sofern This Article shall not prejudice the use or disclosure by the receiving Contracting Party of information other than generally available information, provided that:
( a) the Contracting Party providing the information has previously consented to the use or disclosure of the information; or
( b) the receiving Contracting Party is obliged to do so under the law applicable to it.
In this case, the following shall apply to the receiving Contracting Party:
( i) refrain from taking any measures which would give rise to a legal obligation to disclose confidential information under this Agreement to third parties or other authorities without the prior consent of the Contracting Party supplying the information;
( ii) inform the Contracting Party which provided the information of such use or disclosure in advance, as far as possible, and, upon request, consult with the other Contracting Party, taking due account of its important interests; and
( iii) use all means at its disposal under applicable law to maintain the confidentiality of information in respect of requests by third parties or other authorities to disclose the information in question, unless otherwise agreed with the Contracting Party that provided the information.
( 6) Die Wettbewerbsbehörde der Europäischen Gemeinschaft The competition authority of the European Community
( a) after informing the Japanese competition authority, inform the competent authorities of the Member State (s) concerned of the notifications sent to it by the Japanese competition authority;
( b) after consultation with the Japanese competition authority, inform the competent authorities of the Member State / Member States of any cooperation or coordination with respect to enforcement activities; and
( c) ensure that information provided to the competent authorities of the Member State / Member States in accordance with subparagraphs (a) and (b) of this Article which is not generally available is neither used nor disclosed for purposes other than those referred to in Article 1 (1) of this Agreement.
( 1) Dieses Abkommen wird von den Vertragsparteien nach Maßgabe des jeweils in der Europäischen Gemeinschaft und in Japan geltenden Rechts im Rahmen der ihren Wettbewerbsbehörden zur Verfügung stehenden Mittel durchgeführt. This Agreement shall be implemented by the Contracting Parties, in accordance with the laws applicable in the European Community and Japan, within the means available to their competition authorities.
( 2) Die Wettbewerbsbehörden der Vertragsparteien können zur Durchführung dieses Abkommens besondere Vereinbarungen treffen. The competition authorities of the Contracting Parties may enter into special agreements to implement this Agreement.
( 3) Dieses Abkommen hindert die Vertragsparteien nicht daran, auf der Grundlage anderer bilateraler oder multilateraler Übereinkünfte oder sonstiger Vereinbarungen zwischen den Vertragsparteien einander Hilfe zu leisten oder die andere Vertragspartei um Hilfe zu suchen. This Agreement shall not prevent the Contracting Parties from providing assistance on the basis of other bilateral or multilateral agreements or other agreements between the Contracting Parties or from requesting assistance from the other Contracting Party.
( 4) Dieses Abkommen lässt die politische oder rechtliche Position der Vertragsparteien in Fragen, die die Zuständigkeit betreffen, unberührt. This Agreement shall not prejudice the political or legal position of the Contracting Parties in matters relating to their competence.
( 5) Dieses Abkommen lässt die Rechte und Pflichten der Europäischen Gemeinschaft und Japans nach Maßgabe anderer internationalen Übereinkünfte oder des für sie geltenden Rechts unberührt. This Agreement shall not prejudice the rights and obligations of the European Community and of Japan in accordance with other international agreements or with the laws applicable to them.
Unless otherwise agreed in this Agreement, the competition authority of one Contracting Party may address notifications under this Agreement directly to the competition authority of the other Contracting Party.
However, notifications under Article 1 (2) (b) and Article 2 and requests under Article 5 (1) shall be confirmed in writing by diplomatic channels.
Confirmation shall be given as soon as practically possible after the notification concerned has been communicated to the competition authority of the other Contracting Party.
( 1) Dieses Abkommen tritt am dreißigsten Tag nach seiner Unterzeichnung in Kraft. This Agreement shall enter into force on the 30th day following its signature.
( 2) Dieses Abkommen bleibt bis 60 Tage nach dem Zeitpunkt in Kraft, in dem eine Vertragspartei der anderen Vertragspartei schriftlich auf diplomatischem Weg mitgeteilt hat, daß sie dessen Beendigung begehrt. This Agreement shall remain in force until 60 days after the date on which one Contracting Party has notified the other Contracting Party in writing by diplomatic route that it is seeking its termination.
( 3) Die Vertragsparteien überprüfen die Funktionsweise dieses Abkommens spätestens fünf Jahre nach seinem Inkrafttreten. The Contracting Parties shall review the functioning of this Agreement not later than five years after its entry into force.
between the European Union and the Russian Federation on the participation of the Russian Federation in the Police Mission of the European Mission (EUPM) in Bosnia and Herzegovina
hereinafter referred to as <unk> Participating Parties
- the United Nations International Police Intervention Force (IPTF) has been present in Bosnia and Herzegovina since 1996 and the European Union has offered to provide the follow-up mission to the IPTF mission in Bosnia and Herzegovina as from 1 January 2003,
- Bosnia and Herzegovina, by exchange of letters dated 2 and 4 March 2002, has accepted this offer, which provides, inter alia, for the EUPM planning team to enjoy the same status currently enjoyed by members of the European Union Monitoring Mission (EUMM) in Bosnia and Herzegovina,
- the Council of the European Union has adopted Joint Action 2002 / 210 / CFSP of 11 March 2002 on the European Union Police Mission (1) and Joint Actions 2003 / 141 / CFSP of 27 February 2003 (2) and 2003 / 188 / CFSP of 17 March 2003 (3) amending Joint Action 2002 / 210 / CFSP on the Police Mission of the European Union, which invites the non-EU European members of NATO and other States which are candidates for accession to the Union, as well as other non-EU OSCE Member States which currently provide staff for the IPTF, to contribute to the EUPM,
- an Agreement between the EU and Bosnia and Herzegovina on the activities of the EUPM in Bosnia and Herzegovina (4) was concluded on 4 October 2002, including the status of EUPM staff,
The Russian Federation aligns itself with Joint Action 2002 / 210 / CFSP on the European Union Police Mission (EUPM) in Bosnia and Herzegovina, adopted by the Council of the European Union on 11 March 2002, as amended by Joint Action 2003 / 141 / CFSP of 27 February 2003 and by Joint Action 2003 / 188 / CFSP of 17 March 2003, including the Annex to Joint Action 2002 / 210 / CFSP concerning the mandate to be given to EUPM pursuant to the following Articles.
( 1) Die Russische Föderation leistet einen Beitrag zur EUPM durch die AbDelegation von fünf Polizeiamte. The Russian Federation shall make a contribution to the EUPM by the delegation of five police officers.
Such staff should be seconded for at least one year, with due regard to rotation.
( 2) Die Russische Föderation sorgt dafür, daß das zur EUPM Delegation Personal seinen Auftrag im Einklang mit den Bestimmungen der Gemeinsamen Aktion 2002/ 210/ GFSP, geändert durch die Gemeinsamen Maßnahmen 2003 / 141/ GFSP und 2003/ 188/ GFSP, durchführt. The Russian Federation shall ensure that staff seconded to the EUPM carry out their duties in accordance with the provisions of Joint Action 2002 / 210 / CFSP, as amended by Joint Actions 2003 / 141 / CFSP and 2003 / 188 / CFSP.
( 3) Die Russische Föderation unterrichtet die EUPM und das Generalsekretariat des Rates der Europäischen Union rechtzeitig über jede Änderung ihres Beitrags zur EUPM. The Russian Federation shall inform the EUPM and the General Secretariat of the Council of the European Union in good time of any amendment to its contribution to the EUPM.
( 4) Das zur EUPM seconded Personal wird einer umfassende ärztlichen Untersuchung unterzogen und erhält die erforderlichen Immunfungen; seine Tauglichkeit ist von einer hierzu befugten Behörde der Russischen Föderation zu bescheinigen. The staff seconded to the EUPM shall undergo a comprehensive medical examination and shall receive the necessary vaccinations; its suitability shall be certified by a competent authority of the Russian Federation.
The staff seconded to the EUPM shall carry with them a copy of the certificate of medical fitness.
( 5) Die Russische Föderation trägt die Kosten für die posting der von ihr seconded Polizeiamte, einschließlich der Gehälter, Vergütungen, Krankenkosten, Versicherungen und Kosten der Reisen nach und aus Bosnia und Herzegovina. The Russian Federation shall bear the costs of secondment of police officers seconded by the Russian Federation, including salaries, remuneration, medical expenses, insurance and travel expenses to and from Bosnia and Herzegovina.
( 1) Das von der Russischen Föderation zur EUPM bezeichnete Personal fällt unter das Abkommen zwischen der Europäischen Union und Bosnia und Herzegovina vom 4. Oktober 2002 über die Tätigkeiten der EUPM in Bosnia und Herzegovina. The staff seconded by the Russian Federation to EUPM shall be covered by the Agreement between the European Union and Bosnia and Herzegovina of 4 October 2002 on EUPM activities in Bosnia and Herzegovina.
( 2) Die Russische Föderation ist für Ansprüche im Zusammenhang mit der AbDelegation eines Mitglieds des EUPM-Personals zuständig, die von einem Mitglied des Personals oder bezüglich eines Mitglieds des Personals erhoben werden. The Russian Federation shall deal with claims relating to the secondment of a member of the EUPM staff raised by a member of the staff or relating to a member of the staff.
The Russian Federation shall be competent to take legal action against the seconded person.
( 3) Die EUPM ist eine unbewaffnete Mission und hat als solche keine Einsatzregeln. The EUPM shall be an unarmed mission and shall have as such no rules of engagement.
( 4) Die delegated Polizeiamte tragen im Dienst ihre nationalen Polizeiuniformen. The seconded police officers shall wear their national police uniforms on duty.
Berets and badges shall be provided by the EUPM.
( 1) Der Beitrag der Russischen Föderation zur EUPM erfolgt unbeschadet der Beschlussfassungsautonomie der Union. The contribution of the Russian Federation to the EUPM shall be made without prejudice to the decision making autonomy of the Union.
In the performance of its functions and in its conduct, the staff seconded by the Russian Federation shall be guided by the interests of the EUPM.
( 2) Alle Mitglieder des EUPM-Personals unterstehen weiterhin der jeweiligen nationalen Behörde. All members of EUPM staff shall continue to be subject to the respective national authority.
( 3) Die nationalen Behörden übertragen dem Leiter der Mission/ Polizeizeichef der EUPM die Einsatzleitung (OPCOM), der diese Leitung über eine hierarchische Struktur ausübt. The national authorities shall assign operational command and control (OPCOM) to the head of the mission / police chief of EUPM, who shall exercise such command and control through a hierarchical structure.
( 4) Der Leiter der Mission/ Polizeizeichef leitet die EUPM und führt die laufenden Geschäfte. The head of the mission / police chief shall head the EUPM and shall conduct the current operations.
( 5) Die Russische Föderation hat gemäß Artikel 8 Absatz 2 der Gemeinsamen Aktion 2002/ 210 / CFSP hinsichtlich der laufenden Durchführung des Einsatzes dieselben Rechte und Pflichten wie die an dem Einsatz beteiligten EU-Mitgliedstaaten. Pursuant to Article 8 (2) of Joint Action 2002 / 210 / CFSP, the Russian Federation shall have the same rights and obligations with respect to the ongoing implementation of the deployment as the Member States of the EU participating in the deployment.
This shall apply to the performance of normal operational tasks on the ground, including at the headquarters of the police mission.
( 6) Der Leiter der Mission/ Polizeizeichef der EUPM übt die disziplinargewalt über das EUPM -Personal aus. The head of the mission / police chief of the EUPM shall exercise disciplinary authority over the EUPM staff.
Where appropriate, the competence for disciplinary action shall lie with the relevant national authority.
( 7) Zur Vertretung seines nationalen Kontingents im Rahmen der Mission ernennt die Russische Föderation einen nationalen Kontingentsleiter (NPC). For the representation of its national contingent within the framework of the mission, the Russian Federation shall appoint a national contingent leader (NPC).
The NPC shall report to the Head of Mission / Police of the EUPM on national matters and shall be responsible for the ongoing maintenance of discipline in their contingent.
( 8) Die Europäische Union beschließt die Beendigung des Einsatzes erst nach Hearing der Russischen Föderation, sofern dieser Staat zum Zeitpunkt der Beendigung der Mission noch immer einen Beitrag zur EUPM leistet. The European Union shall decide on the termination of the mission only after consultation with the Russian Federation, provided that that State, at the time of the termination of the mission, still contributes consistently to the EUPM.
The Russian Federation shall take appropriate measures to ensure that staff seconded to EUPM, when handling classified EU information, comply with the security requirements of the Council of the European Union as set out in Council Decision 2001 / 264 / EC of 19 March 2001 (5) on the adoption of the Council <unk> s security requirements.
( 1) Die Russische Föderation stellt jedes Jahr 25000 EUR zur Deckung der laufenden Ausgaben der EUPM bereit. The Russian Federation shall provide EUR 25000 each year to cover EUPM <unk> s current expenditure.
The Russian Federation shall consider the voluntary provision of additional contributions, taking into account its resources and its level of participation.
( 2) Der Leiter der Mission/ Polizeizeichef der EUPM und die zuständigen Verwaltungsdienststellen der Russischen Föderation unterzeichnen eine Vereinbarung über die Beiträge der Russischen Föderation zu den laufenden Ausgaben der EUPM. The head of the mission / police chief of the EUPM and the relevant administrative services of the Russian Federation shall sign an agreement on the contributions of the Russian Federation to the current expenditure of the EUPM.
This Arrangement shall establish that:
( a) the amount of the contribution in question, including any voluntary contributions;
( b) the modalities of payment and management of the contribution in question;
( c) where appropriate, the agreed control and verification procedures for the contribution in question.
( 3) Die Russische Föderation unterrichtet die EUPM und das Generalsekretariat des Rates der Europäischen Union zum 31. Juli 2003 förmlich über den Gesamtbetrag seiner Beteiligung an den laufenden Ausgaben für das Jahr 2003 und in den Folgejahre zum 1. November jeder Jahres und schließt die finanzielle Vereinbarung für das Jahr 2003 zum 15. August 2003 ab; in den Folgejahre schließt sie zum 15. Dezember jeden Jahres die finanzielle Vereinbarung für ihre Beteiligung an den laufenden Kosten des folgenden Jahres ab. The Russian Federation shall inform the EUPM and the General Secretariat of the Council of the European Union as from 31 July 2003 formally of the total amount of its participation in current expenditure for the year 2003 and in subsequent years for the year 2003 and shall conclude the financial agreement for its participation in the current costs of the following year on 15 December of each year.
( 4) Die Beiträge der Russischen Föderation zu den laufenden Kosten der EUPM werden zum 15. September 2003 und in den Folgejahre zum 31. März jeder Jahres auf ein diesem Staat mitzuteilendes Bankkonto eingezahlt. The contributions of the Russian Federation to the running costs of the EUPM shall be deposited into a bank account of that State by 15 September 2003 and in subsequent years by 31 March of each year.
( 1) ABl. L 70 vom 13.3.2002, S. 1. 1.
( 2) ABl. L 53 vom 28.2.2003, S. 63.
( 3) ABl. L 73 vom 19.3.2003, S. 9. 9.
