between the European Union and the Russian Federation concerning an Agreement on the participation of the Russian Federation in the European Union Police Mission (EUPM) in Bosnia and Herzegovina
between the European Union and the Republic of Turkey on the participation of the Republic of Turkey in the EU-led intervention forces in the former Yugoslav Republic of Macedonia
hereinafter referred to as the <unk> Parties <unk>,
- the Council of the European Union having adopted Joint Action 2003 / 92 / CFSP of 27 January 2003 on the military operation of the European Union in the former Yugoslav Republic of Macedonia (1),
- the Republic of Turkey has been invited to participate in the EU-led operation,
- the troop deployment process has been successfully completed and Operation Commander and the EU-Military Committee have recommended that the participation of the operational forces of the Republic of Turkey in the EU-led operation be agreed,
- the Political and Security Committee decided on 11 March 2003 to approve the contribution of the Republic of Turkey to the EU-led operation,
- an exchange of letters has taken place between the Government of the former Yugoslav Republic of Macedonia and the Secretary-General / High Representative concerning the conduct of the operation,
- an Agreement between the EU and the Government of the former Yugoslav Republic of Macedonia on the status of the EU-led forces and their members was concluded on 21 March 2003,
( 1) Die Republik Türkei schließt sich der vom Rat der Europäischen Union am 27. Januar 2003 angenommenen Gemeinsamen Aktion 2003 / 92 / CFSP nach Maßgabe der nachstehenden Artikel an. The Republic of Turkey shall join the Joint Action 2003 / 92 / CFSP adopted by the Council of the European Union on 27 January 2003, in accordance with the provisions of the following Articles.
( 2) Im Sinne dieses Abkommens bezeichnet der Ausdruck For the purposes of this Agreement: the expression
( a) <unk> Operation Concordia <unk> is the military operation of the European Union in the former Yugoslav Republic of Macedonia under Joint Action 2003 / 92 / CFSP;
( b) <unk> EU-led forces
( c) <unk> EUF personnel
( d) the <unk> operational financing mechanism for financing the common costs of the European Union military operation in the former Yugoslav Republic of Macedonia established by the Council Decision of 27 January 2003;
( e) <unk> participating States
( f) <unk> Joint Complaints Commission <unk> means the Joint Complaints Commission established in accordance with Article 13 of the Agreement between the European Union and the former Yugoslav Republic of Macedonia on the status of EU-led forces (EUF) in the former Yugoslav Republic of Macedonia.
( 1) Die Republik Türkei beteiligt sich an der Operation Concordia mit dem auf der Streitkräfteplanungskonferenz festgelegten Kontingent. The Republic of Turkey shall participate in Operation Concordia with the contingent established at the Armed Forces Planning Conference.
Where necessary, appropriate rotation of seconded staff shall be ensured.
( 2) Die Republik Türkei sorgt dafür, daß die Forces und das Personal der Türkei ihrem Auftrag im Einklang mit den Bestimmungen der Gemeinsamen Aktion 2003 / 92 / GFSP, dem Einsatzplan sowie den entsprechenden Durchführungsbestimmungen nachkommen. The Republic of Turkey shall ensure that the forces and personnel of Turkey carry out their mission in accordance with the provisions of Joint Action 2003 / 92 / CFSP, the operational plan and the relevant implementing provisions.
( 3) Die Republik Türkei unterrichtet den Operation Commander der der EU, den EUF Commander und den Militärstab der EU über jede Änderung der Beteiligung der Türkei an der Operation Concordia. The Republic of Turkey shall inform the EU <unk> s Operation Commander, the EUF Commander and the Military Staff of any amendment to Turkey <unk> s participation in Operation Concordia.
( 1) Für die Forces und das Personal, die an der Operation Concordia teilnehmen, gelten die Bestimmungen des Abkommens zwischen der Europäischen Union und der ehemaligen jugoslawischen Republik Mazedonien über den Status der EU-geführten Forces (EUF) in der ehemaligen jugoslawischen Republik Mazedonien sowie die entsprechenden Durchführungsbestimmungen. The provisions of the Agreement between the European Union and the former Yugoslav Republic of Macedonia on the status of the EU-led Forces (EUF) in the former Yugoslav Republic of Macedonia and the relevant implementing provisions shall apply to the forces and personnel participating in Operation Concordia.
( 2) Der Status des Personals, das zu Stabs- oder Führstruppenteilen außerhalb der ehemaligen jugoslawischen Republik Mazedonien beitragen wird, wird durch Vereinbarungen zwischen den betreffenden Stabs- und Führstruppenteilen und der Republik Türkei geregelt. The status of personnel contributing to staff or command units outside the former Yugoslav Republic of Macedonia shall be governed by agreements between the staff or command and control units concerned and the Republic of Turkey.
( 1) Die Beteiligung der Republik Türkei an der Operation Concordia erfolgt unbeschadet der Beschlussfassungsautonomie der Europäischen Union. Participation of the Republic of Turkey in Operation Concordia shall take place without prejudice to the decision making autonomy of the European Union.
( 2) Freiwillige und Personal unterstehen in ihrer Gesamtheit weiterhin voll und ganz den jeweiligen nationalen Behörden. The forces and personnel in their entirety shall continue to be fully and wholly subject to the respective national authorities.
( 3) Die nationalen Behörden übertragen dem Operation Commander der der EU die Operational Control. The national authorities shall assign operational control to the EU Operation Commander.
Operation Commander shall have the power to delegate its powers of action.
( 4) Die Republik Türkei hat gemäß Artikel 8 Absatz 4 der Gemeinsamen Aktion 2003/ 92 / CFSP und des Beschlusses FYROM / 1/ 2003 des Politischen und Sicherheitspolitischen Komitees zur Einsetzung des Ausschusses der beitragenden Länder hinsichtlich der laufenden Durchführung der Operation Concordia dieselben Rechte und Pflichten wie die teilnehmenden Mitgliedstaaten. Pursuant to Article 8 (4) of Joint Action 2003 / 92 / CFSP and the Decision FYROM / 1 / 2003 of the Political and Security Committee on the establishment of the Committee of Contributing Countries, the Republic of Turkey shall enjoy the same rights and obligations as the participating Member States with respect to the ongoing implementation of Operation Concordia.
( 5) Die Republik Türkei übt die Gerichtsbarkeit über das Personal der Türkei aus. The Republic of Turkey shall exercise jurisdiction over the staff of Turkey.
Operation Commander and Force Commander may at any time request the withdrawal of personnel from the Republic of Turkey.
( 6) Die Republik Türkei ernennt einen hochrangigen MilitärVertreter (SMR), der das nationale Kontingent seines Landes bei den EUF vertreten. The Republic of Turkey shall appoint a high ranking military representative (SMR) to represent the national contingent of its country with the EUF.
The High Level Military Representative shall consult the EUF Commander on all matters relating to Operation Concordia and shall be responsible for the day to day maintenance of discipline in his contingent.
The Republic of Turkey shall take appropriate measures to ensure that Turkish personnel handling classified EU information comply with the security requirements of the Council of the European Union as set out in Council Decision 2001 / 264 / EC (2) and, where appropriate, with further guidance from the Operation Commander.
( 1) Unbeschadet der Bestimmungen von Artikel 7 trägt die Republik Türkei alle im Zusammenhang mit ihrer Beteiligung an der Operation Concordia entstehenden Kosten, sofern gemäß der Regelung im Verwaltungshaushaltsplan für die Operation keine gemeinsame Finanzierung der Kosten vorgesehen ist. Without prejudice to the provisions of Article 7, the Republic of Turkey shall bear all costs incurred in connection with its participation in Operation Concordia, provided that no joint financing of the costs is provided for in accordance with the regulation in the administrative budget for the operation.
( 2) Bewilligt die Gemeinsame Beschwerdekommission natürlichen oder juristischen Personen in der ehemaligen jugoslawischen Republik Mazedonien Schadensatz, so übernimmt die Republik Türkei die Schadendigungszahlung, wenn durch Personal oder Mittel der Türkei Todesfälle, Körperinjuries, Schäden oder Verluste verursacht werden, sofern nicht der Mechanismus gemäß Artikel 9 Absatz 3 des Beschlusses des Rates vom 27. Januar 2003 betreffend die Einrichtung des Mechanismus die Schadensersatzleistung beschließt. If the Joint Complaints Commission grants damages to natural or legal persons in the former Yugoslav Republic of Macedonia, the Republic of Turkey shall make the payment of compensation if death, bodily injury, damage or loss is caused by Turkey <unk> s staff or resources, unless the mechanism referred to in Article 9 (3) of the Council <unk> s Decision of 27 January 2003 concerning the establishment of the mechanism decides on the payment of damages.
( 1) Die Republik Türkei beteiligt sich an den gemeinsamen Kosten der Operation mit dem Betrag von 136087,80 EUR für einen Zeitraum von sechs Monaten. The Republic of Turkey shall contribute to the joint costs of the operation with the sum of EUR 136087,80 for a period of six months.
( 2) Zwischen dem gemäß dem Entscheidung des Rates vom 27. Januar 2003 eingesetzten Verwalter des Mechanismus und den zuständigen Verwaltungsbehörden der Republik Türkei wird eine Vereinbarung über die Finanzierung der gemeinsamen Kosten der Operation geschlossen. An agreement on the financing of the joint costs of the operation shall be concluded between the mechanism administrator established pursuant to the Council Decision of 27 January 2003 and the competent administrative authorities of the Republic of Turkey.
( a) the arrangements for the payment and management of the financial contribution;
( b) where appropriate, the agreed control and audit procedures for the financial contribution.
( 3) Die Beiträge der Republik Türkei zu den gemeinsamen Kosten der Operation Concordia werden von der Republik Türkei auf ein Bankkonto eingezahlt, das der Verwalter des Mechanismus der Republik Türkei mitgeteilt. The contributions of the Republic of Turkey to the joint costs of Operation Concordia shall be deposited by the Republic of Turkey into a bank account held by the administrator of the mechanism of the Republic of Turkey.
If one of the participating Parties fails to fulfil any of the obligations incumbent upon it under the preceding Articles, the other Party may denounce the Agreement and the period of denunciation shall be one month.
This Agreement shall enter into force upon its signature.
It shall remain in force as long as the Republic of Turkey contributes to Operation Concordia.
between the European Union and the Republic of Iceland on the participation of the Republic of Iceland in the European Union Police Mission (EUPM) in Bosnia and Herzegovina
hereinafter referred to as <unk> Participating Parties
- the United Nations International Police Intervention Force (IPTF) has been present in Bosnia and Herzegovina since 1996 and the European Union has offered to provide the follow-up mission to the IPTF mission in Bosnia and Herzegovina as from 1 January 2003,
- Bosnia and Herzegovina, by exchange of letters dated 2 and 4 March 2002, has accepted this offer, which provides, inter alia, for the EUPM planning team to enjoy the same status currently enjoyed by members of the European Union Monitoring Mission (EUMM) in Bosnia and Herzegovina,
- the Council of the European Union, on 11 March 2002, adopted Joint Action 2002 / 210 / CFSP on the Police Mission of the European Union (1), inviting non-EU European members of NATO and other States applying for accession to the Union, as well as other non-EU OSCE Member States currently providing staff to IPTF, to contribute to the EUPM,
- an Agreement between the EU and Bosnia and Herzegovina on the activities of the EUPM in Bosnia and Herzegovina (2) was concluded on 4 October 2002, including the status of EUPM staff;
The Republic of Iceland aligns itself with Joint Action 2002 / 210 / CFSP on the European Union Police Mission (EUPM) in Bosnia and Herzegovina, including the Annex concerning the mandate for EUPM, adopted by the Council of the European Union on 11 March 2002, in accordance with the following Articles.
( 1) Die Republik Island leistet einen Beitrag zur EUPM durch die AbDelegation von zwei Polizeiamte und von internationalem Zivilpersonal im Umfang von einer Person. The Republic of Iceland shall make a contribution to the EUPM by seconding two police officers and one person of international civilian staff.
Such staff should be seconded for at least one year, with due regard to rotation.
( 2) Die Republik Island sorgt dafür, daß das zur EUPM Delegation Personal seinen Auftrag im Einklang mit den Bestimmungen der Gemeinsamen Aktion 2002/ 210 / GFSP durchführt. The Republic of Iceland shall ensure that staff seconded to EUPM carry out their duties in accordance with the provisions of Joint Action 2002 / 210 / GFSP.
( 3) Die Republik Island unterrichtet die EUPM und das Generalsekretariat des Rates der Europäischen Union rechtzeitig über jede Änderung ihres Beitrags zur EUPM. The Republic of Iceland shall inform the EUPM and the General Secretariat of the Council of the European Union in good time of any amendment to its contribution to the EUPM.
( 4) Das zur EUPM seconded Personal wird einer umfassende ärztlichen Untersuchung unterzogen und erhält die erforderlichen Immunfungen; seine Tauglichkeit ist von einer hierzu befugten Behörde der Republik Island zu bescheinigen. The staff seconded to the EUPM shall undergo a comprehensive medical examination and shall receive the necessary vaccinations; its suitability shall be certified by a competent authority of the Republic of Iceland.
The staff seconded to the EUPM shall carry with them a copy of the certificate of medical fitness.
( 5) Die Republik Island trägt die Kosten für die posting der von ihr seconded PolizeiOfficers und / oder des von ihr seconded internationalen Zivilpersonals, einschließlich der Gehälter, Vergütungen, Krankenkosten, Versicherungen und Kosten der Reisen nach und aus Bosnia und Herzegovina. The Republic of Iceland shall bear the costs of secondment of its seconded police officers and / or of its seconded international civilian personnel, including salaries, remuneration, medical expenses, insurance and travel costs to and from Bosnia and Herzegovina.
( 1) Das von der Republik Island zur EUPM bezeichnete Personal fällt bis zum 31. Dezember 2002 unter das für das EUPM -Planungsteam geltende Abkommen und ab 1. Januar 2003 unter das Abkommen zwischen der Europäischen Union und Bosnia und Herzegovina vom 4. Oktober 2002 über die Tätigkeiten der EUPM in Bosnia und Herzegovina. The staff seconded by the Republic of Iceland to EUPM shall fall by 31 December 2002 under the Agreement applicable to the EUPM Planning Team and from 1 January 2003 under the Agreement between the European Union and Bosnia and Herzegovina of 4 October 2002 on EUPM activities in Bosnia and Herzegovina.
( 2) Die Republik Island ist für Ansprüche im Zusammenhang mit der AbDelegation eines Mitglieds des EUPM-Personals zuständig, die von einem Mitglied des Personals oder bezüglich eines Mitglieds des Personals erhoben werden. The Republic of Iceland shall be competent in respect of claims made by a member of the staff or relating to a member of the staff in connection with the delegation of a member of the EUPM staff.
The Republic of Iceland shall be competent to take legal action against the seconded person.
( 3) Die EUPM ist eine unbewaffnete Mission und hat als solche keine Einsatzregeln. The EUPM shall be an unarmed mission and shall have as such no rules of engagement.
( 4) Die delegated Polizeiamte tragen im Dienst ihre nationalen Polizeiuniformen. The seconded police officers shall wear their national police uniforms on duty.
Berets and badges shall be provided by the EUPM.
( 1) Der Beitrag der Republik Island zur EUPM erfolgt unbeschadet der Beschlussautonomie der Union. The contribution of the Republic of Iceland to the EUPM shall be made without prejudice to the decision-making autonomy of the Union.
In the performance of its functions and in its conduct, the staff seconded from the Republic of Iceland shall be guided by the interests of EUPM.
( 2) Alle Mitglieder des EUPM-Personals unterstehen weiterhin der jeweiligen nationalen Behörde. All members of EUPM staff shall continue to be subject to the respective national authority.
( 3) Die nationalen Behörden übertragen dem Leiter der Mission/ Polizeizeichef der EUPM die Einsatzleitung (OPCOM), der diese Leitung über eine hierarchische Struktur ausübt. The national authorities shall assign operational command and control (OPCOM) to the head of the mission / police chief of EUPM, who shall exercise such command and control through a hierarchical structure.
( 4) Der Leiter der Mission/ Polizeizeichef leitet die EUPM und führt die laufenden Geschäfte. The head of the mission / police chief shall head the EUPM and shall conduct the current operations.
( 5) Die Republik Island hat gemäß Artikel 8 Absatz 2 der Gemeinsamen Aktion 2002/ 210/ GFSP hinsichtlich der laufenden Durchführung des Einsatzes dieselben Rechte und Pflichten wie die an dem Einsatz beteiligten EU-Mitgliedstaaten. Pursuant to Article 8 (2) of Joint Action 2002 / 210 / CFSP, the Republic of Iceland shall have the same rights and obligations with respect to the ongoing implementation of the operation as the Member States of the EU participating in the operation.
This shall apply to the performance of normal operational tasks on the ground, including at the headquarters of the police mission.
( 6) Der Leiter der Mission/ Polizeizeichef der EUPM übt die disziplinargewalt über das EUPM -Personal aus. The head of the mission / police chief of the EUPM shall exercise disciplinary authority over the EUPM staff.
Where appropriate, the competence for disciplinary action shall lie with the relevant national authority.
( 7) Zur Vertretung ihres nationalen Kontingents im Rahmen der Mission ernennt die Republik Island einen nationalen Kontingentsleiter (NPC). For the representation of its national contingent within the framework of the mission, the Republic of Iceland shall appoint a national contingent leader (NPC).
The NPC shall report to the Head of Mission / Police of the EUPM on national matters and shall be responsible for the ongoing maintenance of discipline in their contingent.
( 8) Die Europäische Union beschließt die Beendigung des Einsatzes erst nach Hearing der Republik Island, sofern dieser Staat zum Zeitpunkt der Beendigung der Mission noch immer einen Beitrag zur EUPM leistet. The European Union shall decide on the termination of the mission only after consultation with the Republic of Iceland, provided that that State, at the time of the termination of the mission, is still making a contribution to the EUPM.
The Republic of Iceland shall take appropriate measures to ensure that staff seconded to EUPM, when handling classified EU information, comply with the safety requirements of the Council of the European Union as laid down in Council Decision 2001 / 264 / EC (3).
( 1) Die Republik Island stellt jedes Jahr 25000 EUR zur Deckung der laufenden Ausgaben der EUPM bereit. The Republic of Iceland shall provide EUR 25000 each year to cover the current expenditure of the EUPM.
The Republic of Iceland shall consider the voluntary provision of additional contributions, taking into account its resources and its level of participation.
( 2) Der Leiter der Mission/ Polizeizeichef der EUPM und die zuständigen Verwaltungsdienststellen der Republik Island unterzeichnen eine Vereinbarung über die Beiträge von Island zu den laufenden Ausgaben der EUPM. The head of the mission / police chief of the EUPM and the competent administrative services of the Republic of Iceland shall sign an agreement on the contributions of Iceland to the current expenditure of the EUPM.
This Arrangement shall establish that:
( a) the amount of the contribution in question, including any voluntary contributions;
( b) the arrangements for the payment and management of the amount concerned;
( c) where appropriate, the agreed control and verification procedures for the amount concerned.
( 3) Die Republik Island unterrichtet die EUPM und das Generalsekretariat des Rates der Europäischen Union zum 15. November 2002 und in den Folgejahre zum 1. November förmlich über den Gesamtbetrag ihrer Beteiligung an den laufenden Ausgaben und schließt die finanzielle Vereinbarung zum 15. Dezember jedes Jahres ab. The Republic of Iceland shall inform the EUPM and the General Secretariat of the Council of the European Union by 15 November 2002 and in the following years by 1 November formally of the total amount of its participation in current expenditure and shall conclude the financial arrangement by 15 December of each year.
( 4) Die Beiträge der Republik Island zu den laufenden Kosten der EUPM werden zum 31. März jedes Jahres auf ein diesem Staat mitzuteilendes Bankkonto eingezahlt. The contributions of the Republic of Iceland to the running costs of the EUPM shall be deposited by 31 March of each year into a bank account of that State.
If one of the participating Parties fails to fulfil any of the obligations incumbent upon it under the preceding Articles, the other Party may denounce the Agreement in writing with a period of notice of two months.
This Agreement shall enter into force upon its signature.
It shall remain in force as long as the Republic of Iceland contributes to the EUPM.
between the European Union and the Government of the Swiss Confederation, represented by the Federal Department of Foreign Affairs, on the participation of Switzerland in the European Union Police Mission (EUPM) in Bosnia and Herzegovina
hereinafter referred to as <unk> Participating Parties
- the United Nations International Police Intervention Force (IPTF) has been present in Bosnia and Herzegovina since 1996 and the European Union has offered to provide the follow-up mission to the IPTF mission in Bosnia and Herzegovina as from 1 January 2003,
- Bosnia and Herzegovina, by exchange of letters dated 2 and 4 March 2002, has accepted this offer, which provides, inter alia, for the EUPM planning team to enjoy the same status currently enjoyed by members of the European Union Monitoring Mission (EUMM) in Bosnia and Herzegovina,
- the Council of the European Union, on 11 March 2002, adopted Joint Action 2002 / 210 / CFSP on the Police Mission of the European Union (1), inviting non-EU European members of NATO and other States applying for accession to the Union, as well as other non-EU OSCE Member States currently providing staff to IPTF, to contribute to the EUPM,
