( 1) Romania stellt jedes Jahr 25000 EUR zur Deckung der laufenden Ausgaben der EUPM bereit. Romania shall provide EUR 25000 each year to cover EUPM <unk> s current expenditure.
Romania is considering the voluntary provision of additional contributions, taking into account its resources and its level of participation.
( 2) Der Leiter der Mission/ Polizeizeichef der EUPM und die zuständigen Verwaltungsdienststellen von Rumänien unterzeichnen eine Vereinbarung über die Beiträge von Rumänien zu den laufenden Ausgaben der EUPM. The head of the mission / police chief of EUPM and the relevant administrative services of Romania shall sign an agreement on the contributions of Romania to the current expenditure of EUPM.
This Arrangement shall establish that:
( a) the amount of the contribution in question, including any voluntary contributions;
( b) the arrangements for the payment and management of the amount concerned;
( c) where appropriate, the agreed control and verification procedures for the amount concerned.
( 3) Rumänien unterrichtet die EUPM und das Generalsekretariat des Rates der Europäischen Union zum 15. November 2002 und in den Folgejahre zum 1. November förmlich über den Gesamtbetrag seiner Beteiligung an den laufenden Ausgaben und schließt die finanzielle Vereinbarung zum 15. Dezember jedes Jahres ab. Romania shall inform the EUPM and the General Secretariat of the Council of the European Union by 15 November 2002 and in the following years by 1 November formally of the total amount of its participation in current expenditure and shall conclude the financial agreement by 15 December of each year.
( 4) Die Beiträge von Rumänien zu den laufenden Kosten der EUPM werden zum 31. März jedes Jahres auf ein diesem Staat mitzuteilendes Bankkonto eingezahlt. The contributions of Romania to the running costs of the EUPM shall be deposited by 31 March of each year into a bank account of that State.
If one of the participating Parties fails to fulfil any of the obligations incumbent upon it under the preceding Articles, the other Party may denounce the Agreement in writing with a period of notice of two months.
This Agreement shall enter into force upon its signature.
It shall remain in force as long as Romania contributes to the EUPM.
between the European Union and the Kingdom of Norway on the participation of the Kingdom of Norway in the European Union Police Mission (EUPM) in Bosnia and Herzegovina
hereinafter referred to as <unk> Participating Parties
- the United Nations International Police Intervention Force (IPTF) has been present in Bosnia and Herzegovina since 1996 and the European Union has offered to provide the follow-up mission to the IPTF mission in Bosnia and Herzegovina as from 1 January 2003,
- Bosnia and Herzegovina, by exchange of letters dated 2 and 4 March 2002, has accepted this offer, which provides, inter alia, for the EUPM planning team to enjoy the same status currently enjoyed by members of the European Union Monitoring Mission (EUMM) in Bosnia and Herzegovina,
- the Council of the European Union, on 11 March 2002, adopted Joint Action 2002 / 210 / CFSP on the Police Mission of the European Union (1), inviting non-EU European members of NATO and other States applying for accession to the Union, as well as other non-EU OSCE Member States currently providing staff to IPTF, to contribute to the EUPM,
- an Agreement between the EU and Bosnia and Herzegovina on the activities of the EUPM in Bosnia and Herzegovina (2) was concluded on 4 October 2002, including the status of EUPM staff;
The Kingdom of Norway aligns itself with Joint Action 2002 / 210 / CFSP on the European Union Police Mission (EUPM) in Bosnia and Herzegovina, including the Annex concerning the mandate for EUPM, adopted by the Council of the European Union on 11 March 2002, in accordance with the following Articles.
( 1) Das Königreich Norwegen leistet einen Beitrag zur EUPM durch die AbDelegation von sechs Polizeiamte und von internationalem Zivilpersonal im Umfang von zwei Personen. The Kingdom of Norway shall contribute to the EUPM by seconding six police officers and two international civilian personnel.
Such staff should be seconded for at least one year, with due regard to rotation.
( 2) Das Königreich Norwegen sorgt dafür, daß das zur EUPM Delegation Personal seinen Auftrag im Einklang mit den Bestimmungen der Gemeinsamen Aktion 2002/ 210 / GFSP durchführt. The Kingdom of Norway shall ensure that staff seconded to the EUPM carry out their duties in accordance with the provisions of Joint Action 2002 / 210 / GFSP.
( 3) Das Königreich Norwegen unterrichtet die EUPM und das Generalsekretariat des Rates der Europäischen Union rechtzeitig über jede Änderung seines Beitrags zur EUPM. The Kingdom of Norway shall inform the EUPM and the General Secretariat of the Council of the European Union in good time of any amendment to its contribution to the EUPM.
( 4) Das zur EUPM seconded Personal wird einer umfassende ärztlichen Untersuchung unterzogen und erhält die erforderlichen Immunfungen; seine Tauglichkeit ist von einer hierzu befugten Behörde des Königreichs Norwegen zu bescheinigen. The staff seconded to the EUPM shall undergo a comprehensive medical examination and shall receive the necessary vaccinations; its suitability shall be certified by a competent authority of the Kingdom of Norway.
The staff seconded to the EUPM shall carry with them a copy of the certificate of medical fitness.
( 5) Das Königreich Norwegen trägt die Kosten für die posting der von ihm seconded PolizeiOfficers und / oder des von ihm seconded internationalen Zivilpersonals, einschließlich der Gehälter, Vergütungen, Krankenkosten, Versicherungen und Kosten der Reisen nach und aus Bosnia und Herzegovina. The Kingdom of Norway shall bear the costs of seconded police officers and / or seconded international civilian personnel, including salaries, remuneration, medical expenses, insurance and travel expenses to and from Bosnia and Herzegovina.
( 1) Das von dem Königreich Norwegen zur EUPM Delegation Personal fällt bis zum 31. Dezember 2002 unter das für das EUPM -Planungsteam geltende Abkommen und ab 1. Januar 2003 unter das Abkommen zwischen der Europäischen Union und Bosnia und Herzegovina vom 4. Oktober 2002 über die Tätigkeiten der EUPM in Bosnia und Herzegovina. The staff seconded by the Kingdom of Norway to EUPM shall fall by 31 December 2002 under the Agreement applicable to the EUPM Planning Team and from 1 January 2003 under the Agreement between the European Union and Bosnia and Herzegovina of 4 October 2002 on EUPM activities in Bosnia and Herzegovina.
( 2) Das Königreich Norwegen ist für Ansprüche im Zusammenhang mit der AbDelegation eines Mitglieds des EUPM -Personals zuständig, die von einem Mitglied des Personals oder bezüglich eines Mitglieds des Personals erhoben werden. The Kingdom of Norway shall be competent in respect of claims relating to the delegation of a member of the EUPM staff raised by a member of the staff or relating to a member of the staff.
The Kingdom of Norway shall be competent to bring legal proceedings against the seconded person.
( 3) Die EUPM ist eine unbewaffnete Mission und hat als solche keine Einsatzregeln. The EUPM shall be an unarmed mission and shall have as such no rules of engagement.
( 4) Die delegated Polizeiamte tragen im Dienst ihre nationalen Polizeiuniformen. The seconded police officers shall wear their national police uniforms on duty.
Berets and badges shall be provided by the EUPM.
( 1) Der Beitrag des Königreichs Norwegen zur EUPM erfolgt unbeschadet der Beschlussfassungsautonomie der Union. The contribution of the Kingdom of Norway to the EUPM shall be made without prejudice to the decision making autonomy of the Union.
In the performance of its functions and in its conduct, the staff seconded by the Kingdom of Norway shall be guided by the interests of EUPM.
( 2) Alle Mitglieder des EUPM-Personals unterstehen weiterhin der jeweiligen nationalen Behörde. All members of EUPM staff shall continue to be subject to the respective national authority.
( 3) Die nationalen Behörden übertragen dem Leiter der Mission/ Polizeizeichef der EUPM die Einsatzleitung (OPCOM), der diese Leitung über eine hierarchische Struktur ausübt. The national authorities shall assign operational command and control (OPCOM) to the head of the mission / police chief of EUPM, who shall exercise such command and control through a hierarchical structure.
( 4) Der Leiter der Mission/ Polizeizeichef leitet die EUPM und führt die laufenden Geschäfte. The head of the mission / police chief shall head the EUPM and shall conduct the current operations.
( 5) Das Königreich Norwegen hat gemäß Artikel 8 Absatz 2 der Gemeinsamen Aktion 2002/ 210/ GFSP hinsichtlich der laufenden Durchführung des Einsatzes dieselben Rechte und Pflichten wie die an dem Einsatz beteiligten EU-Mitgliedstaaten. Pursuant to Article 8 (2) of Joint Action 2002 / 210 / CFSP, the Kingdom of Norway shall have the same rights and obligations with respect to the ongoing implementation of the deployment as the Member States of the EU participating in the deployment.
This shall apply to the performance of normal operational tasks on the ground, including at the headquarters of the police mission.
( 6) Der Leiter der Mission/ Polizeizeichef der EUPM übt die disziplinargewalt über das EUPM -Personal aus. The head of the mission / police chief of the EUPM shall exercise disciplinary authority over the EUPM staff.
Where appropriate, the competence for disciplinary action shall lie with the relevant national authority.
( 7) Zur Vertretung seines nationalen Kontingents im Rahmen der Mission ernennt das Königreich Norwegen einen nationalen Kontingsleiter (NPC). For the representation of its national contingent within the framework of the mission, the Kingdom of Norway shall appoint a national contingent leader (NPC).
The NPC shall report to the Head of Mission / Police of the EUPM on national matters and shall be responsible for the ongoing maintenance of discipline in their contingent.
( 8) Die Europäische Union beschließt die Beendigung des Einsatzes erst nach Hearing des Königreichs Norwegen, sofern dieser Staat zum Zeitpunkt der Beendigung der Mission noch immer einen Beitrag zur EUPM leistet. The European Union shall decide on the termination of the mission only after consultation with the Kingdom of Norway, provided that that State, at the time of the termination of the mission, is still making a contribution to the EUPM.
The Kingdom of Norway shall take appropriate measures to ensure that staff seconded to EUPM, when handling EU classified information, comply with the safety requirements of the Council of the European Union as laid down in Council Decision 2001 / 264 / EC (3).
( 1) Das Königreich Norwegen stellt jedes Jahr 25000 EUR zur Deckung der laufenden Ausgaben der EUPM bereit. The Kingdom of Norway shall provide EUR 25000 each year to cover EUPM <unk> s current expenditure.
The Kingdom of Norway shall consider the voluntary provision of additional contributions, taking into account its resources and its level of participation.
( 2) Der Leiter der Mission/ Polizeizeichef der EUPM und die zuständigen Verwaltungsdienststellen des Königreichs Norwegen unterzeichnen eine Vereinbarung über die Beiträge von Norwegen zu den laufenden Ausgaben der EUPM. The head of the mission / police chief of the EUPM and the relevant administrative services of the Kingdom of Norway shall sign an agreement on the contributions of Norway to the current expenditure of the EUPM.
This Arrangement shall establish that:
( a) the amount of the contribution in question, including any voluntary contributions;
( b) the arrangements for the payment and management of the amount concerned;
( c) where appropriate, the agreed control and verification procedures for the amount concerned.
( 3) Das Königreich Norwegen unterrichtet die EUPM und das Generalsekretariat des Rates der Europäischen Union zum 15. November 2002 und in den Folgejahre zum 1. November förmlich über den Gesamtbetrag seiner Beteiligung an den laufenden Ausgaben und schließt die finanzielle Vereinbarung zum 15. Dezember jedes Jahres ab. The Kingdom of Norway shall inform the EUPM and the General Secretariat of the Council of the European Union by 15 November 2002 and in the following years by 1 November formally of the total amount of its participation in current expenditure and shall conclude the financial arrangement by 15 December of each year.
( 4) Die Beiträge des Königreichs Norwegen zu den laufenden Kosten der EUPM werden zum 31. März jedes Jahres auf ein diesem Staat mitzuteilendes Bankkonto eingezahlt. The contributions of the Kingdom of Norway to the running costs of the EUPM shall be deposited by 31 March of each year into a bank account of that State.
If one of the participating Parties fails to fulfil any of the obligations incumbent upon it under the preceding Articles, the other Party may denounce the Agreement in writing with a period of notice of two months.
This Agreement shall enter into force upon its signature.
It shall remain in force as long as the Kingdom of Norway contributes to the EUPM.
between the European Union and the Republic of Turkey on the participation of the Republic of Turkey in the European Union Police Mission (EUPM) in Bosnia and Herzegovina
hereinafter referred to as <unk> Participating Parties
